67 #define MR_CMP(d1, d2) \
68  ((d1) < (d2) ? DB_LT : (d1) > (d2) ? DB_GT : DB_EQ)
69 
70 #define MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE(c) \
71  ((c) < 0 ? DB_LT : (c) > 0 ? DB_GT : DB_EQ)
72 
73 /*
74  * MR_OID_SIZE
75  * Hack so we don't have to conditionalize the type vector.
76  * On the server we don't have the structure definition for this.
77  */
78 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
79 #define MR_OID_SIZE sizeof(WS_MEMOID)
80 #else
81 #define MR_OID_SIZE 0
82 #endif
83 
84 #define VALUE_AREA_COUNT 1024
85 
86 /*
87  * PR_OID_PROMOTION_DEFAULT
88  *
89  * It is intended to allow some control over whether or not OIDs read
90  * by "readval" are automatically promoted to MOPs or not. This
91  * is used to prevent cluttering up the workspace with MOPs when we
92  * don't really need them. When this is enabled, callers of "readval"
93  * had better be prepared to see DB_VALUE structures containing unswizzled
94  * OIDs rather than MOPs. Not intended for use by by real applications.
95  * Think about this more, this may also be the mechanism by which the server
96  * can control reading of object values.
97  *
98  * Note that this makes sense only for the "readval" function, the "readmem
99  * function must be building a workspace instance memory representation
100  * and oid promotion cannot be controlled there.
101  *
102  */
103 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
104 #define PR_INHIBIT_OID_PROMOTION_DEFAULT 1
105 #else
106 #define PR_INHIBIT_OID_PROMOTION_DEFAULT 0
107 #endif
108 
109 /*
110  * These are currently fixed length widets of length DB_NUMERIC_BUF_SIZE.
111  * Ultimately they may be of variable size based on the precision and scale,
112  * in antipication of that move, use the followign function for copying.
113  */
114 #define OR_NUMERIC_SIZE(precision) DB_NUMERIC_BUF_SIZE
115 #define MR_NUMERIC_SIZE(precision) DB_NUMERIC_BUF_SIZE
116 
117 #define STR_SIZE(prec, codeset) \
118  (((codeset) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS) ? ((prec+7)/8) : \
119  INTL_CODESET_MULT (codeset) * (prec))
120 
121 
122 #define BITS_IN_BYTE 8
123 #define BITS_TO_BYTES(bit_cnt) (((bit_cnt) + 7) / 8)
124 
125 /* left for future extension */
126 #define DO_CONVERSION_TO_SRVR_STR(codeset) false
127 #define DO_CONVERSION_TO_SQLTEXT(codeset) false
128 
129 #define DB_DOMAIN_INIT_CHAR(value, precision) \
130  do { \
131  (value)->domain.general_info.type = DB_TYPE_CHAR; \
132  (value)->domain.general_info.is_null = 1; \
133  (value)->domain.char_info.length = \
134  (precision) == DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION ? \
135  TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE : (precision); \
136  (value)->need_clear = false; \
137  (value)->data.ch.info.codeset = LANG_SYS_CODESET; \
138  (value)->domain.char_info.collation_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION; \
139  } while (0)
140 
141 
142 #define IS_FLOATING_PRECISION(prec) \
143  ((prec) == TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE)

1825 /*
1826  * DB_VALUE MAINTENANCE
1827  */
1828 
1829 
1830 /*
1831  * pr_area_init - Initialize the area for allocation of value containers.
1832  * return: NO_ERROR or error code.
1833  * Note:
1834  * This must be called at a suitable point in system initialization.
1835  */
1836 int
1837 pr_area_init (void)
1838 {
1839  Value_area = area_create ("Value containers", sizeof (DB_VALUE), VALUE_AREA_COUNT);
1840  if (Value_area == NULL)
1841  {
1842  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1843  return er_errid ();
1844  }
1845 
1846  pr_init_ordered_mem_sizes ();
1847 
1848  return NO_ERROR;
1849 }
1850 
1851 /*
1852  * pr_area_final - Finalize the area for allocation of value containers.
1853  * return: none.
1854  */
1855 void
1856 pr_area_final (void)
1857 {
1858  if (Value_area != NULL)
1859  {
1860  area_destroy (Value_area);
1861  Value_area = NULL;
1862  }
1863 }
1864 
1865 /*
1866  * pr_make_value - create an internal value container
1867  * return: new value container
1868  * Note:
1869  * The value is allocated within the main workspace blocks so that
1870  * it will not serve as a root for the garbage collector.
1871  */
1872 DB_VALUE *
1873 pr_make_value (void)
1874 {
1875  DB_VALUE *value;
1876 
1877  value = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (NULL, sizeof (DB_VALUE));
1878 
1879  if (value != NULL)
1880  {
1881  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_NULL, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
1882  }
1883 
1884  return value;
1885 }
1886 
1887 /*
1888  * pr_make_ext_value - creates an external value container suitable for
1889  * passing beyond the interface layer to application programs.
1890  * return: new value container
1891  * Note:
1892  * It is allocated in the special Value_area so that it will serve as
1893  * a root to the garbage collector if the value contains a MOP.
1894  */
1895 DB_VALUE *
1896 pr_make_ext_value (void)
1897 {
1898  DB_VALUE *value;
1899 
1900  value = (DB_VALUE *) area_alloc (Value_area);
1901  if (value != NULL)
1902  {
1903  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_NULL, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
1904  }
1905  return value;
1906 }
1907 
1908 /*
1909  * pr_clear_value - clear an internal or external DB_VALUE and
1910  * initialize it to the NULL state.
1911  * return: NO_ERROR
1912  * value(in/out): value to initialize
1913  * Note:
1914  * Any external allocations (strings, sets, etc) will be freed.
1915  *
1916  * There is too much type specific stuff in here. We need to create a
1917  * "freeval" type vector function to do this work.
1918  */
1919 int
1920 pr_clear_value (DB_VALUE * value)
1921 {
1922  unsigned char *data;
1923  bool need_clear;
1924  DB_TYPE db_type;
1925 
1926  if (value == NULL)
1927  {
1928  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1929  }
1930 
1931  db_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
1932 
1933  need_clear = true;
1934 
1935  if (DB_IS_NULL (value))
1936  {
1937  need_clear = false;
1938  if (value->need_clear)
1939  {
1940  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ORACLE_STYLE_EMPTY_STRING))
1941  { /* need to check */
1942  if ((QSTR_IS_ANY_CHAR_OR_BIT (db_type) && value->data.ch.medium.buf != NULL)
1943  || db_type == DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
1944  {
1945  need_clear = true; /* need to free Empty-string */
1946  }
1947  }
1948  }
1949  }
1950 
1951  if (need_clear == false)
1952  {
1953  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1954  }
1955 
1956  switch (db_type)
1957  {
1958  case DB_TYPE_JSON:
1959  if (value->need_clear)
1960  {
1961  if (value->data.json.document != NULL)
1962  {
1963  db_json_delete_doc (value->data.json.document);
1964  value->data.json.document = NULL;
1965  }
1966  if (value->data.json.schema_raw != NULL)
1967  {
1968  db_private_free (NULL, const_cast < char *>(value->data.json.schema_raw));
1969  value->data.json.schema_raw = NULL;
1970  }
1971  }
1972  else
1973  {
1974  value->data.json.document = NULL;
1975  value->data.json.schema_raw = NULL;
1976  }
1977  break;
1978 
1979  case DB_TYPE_OBJECT:
1980  /* we need to be sure to NULL the object pointer so that this db_value does not cause garbage collection problems
1981  * by retaining an object pointer. */
1982  value->data.op = NULL;
1983  break;
1984 
1985  case DB_TYPE_SET:
1986  case DB_TYPE_MULTISET:
1987  case DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1988  case DB_TYPE_VOBJ:
1989  set_free (db_get_set (value));
1990  value->data.set = NULL;
1991  break;
1992 
1993  case DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY:
1994  data = (unsigned char *) value->data.midxkey.buf;
1995  if (data != NULL)
1996  {
1997  if (value->need_clear)
1998  {
1999  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, data);
2000  }
2001  /*
2002  * Ack, phfffft!!! why should we have to know about the
2003  * internals here?
2004  */
2005  value->data.midxkey.buf = NULL;
2006  }
2007  break;
2008 
2009  case DB_TYPE_VARCHAR:
2010  case DB_TYPE_CHAR:
2011  case DB_TYPE_NCHAR:
2012  case DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
2013  case DB_TYPE_BIT:
2014  case DB_TYPE_VARBIT:
2015  data = (unsigned char *) value->data.ch.medium.buf;
2016  if (data != NULL)
2017  {
2018  if (value->need_clear)
2019  {
2020  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, data);
2021  }
2022  /*
2023  * Ack, phfffft!!! why should we have to know about the
2024  * internals here?
2025  */
2026  value->data.ch.medium.buf = NULL;
2027  }
2028 
2029  /* Clear the compressed string since we are here for DB_TYPE_VARCHAR and DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR. */
2030  if (db_type == DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR || db_type == DB_TYPE_VARCHAR)
2031  {
2032  data = (unsigned char *) DB_GET_COMPRESSED_STRING (value);
2033  if (data != NULL)
2034  {
2035  if (value->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear != 0)
2036  {
2037  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, data);
2038  }
2039  }
2040  db_set_compressed_string (value, NULL, 0, false);
2041  }
2042  else if (db_type == DB_TYPE_CHAR || db_type == DB_TYPE_NCHAR)
2043  {
2044  assert (value->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear == 0);
2045  if (value->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf != NULL)
2046  {
2047  if (value->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear != 0)
2048  {
2049  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, value->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf);
2050  }
2051  }
2052 
2053  }
2054  break;
2055 
2056  case DB_TYPE_BLOB:
2057  case DB_TYPE_CLOB:
2058  if (value->need_clear)
2059  {
2060  elo_free_structure (db_get_elo (value));
2061  }
2062  break;
2063 
2064  case DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
2065  if (value->need_clear)
2066  {
2067  char *temp = db_get_enum_string (value);
2068  if (temp != NULL)
2069  {
2070  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, temp);
2071  }
2072  }
2073  db_make_enumeration (value, 0, NULL, 0, db_get_enum_codeset (value), db_get_enum_collation (value));
2074  break;
2075 
2076  default:
2077  break;
2078  }
2079 
2080  /* always make sure the value gets cleared */
2081  PRIM_SET_NULL (value);
2082  value->need_clear = false;
2083 
2084  return NO_ERROR;
2085 }
2086 
2087 /*
2088  * pr_free_value - free an internval value container any anything that it
2089  * references
2090  * return: NO_ERROR if successful, error code otherwise
2091  * value(in/out): value to clear & free
2092  */
2093 int
2094 pr_free_value (DB_VALUE * value)
2095 {
2096  int error = NO_ERROR;
2097 
2098  if (value != NULL)
2099  {
2100  /* some redundant checking but I want the semantics isolated */
2101  error = pr_clear_value (value);
2102  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, value);
2103  }
2104  return error;
2105 }
2106 
2107 /*
2108  * pr_free_ext_value - free an external value container and anything that it
2109  * references.
2110  * return:
2111  * value(in/out): external value to clear & free
2112  * Note:
2113  * Identical to pr_free_value except that it frees the value to the
2114  * Value_area instead of to the workspace.
2115  */
2116 int
2117 pr_free_ext_value (DB_VALUE * value)
2118 {
2119  int error = NO_ERROR;
2120 
2121  if (value != NULL)
2122  {
2123  /* some redundant checking but I want the semantics isolated */
2124  error = pr_clear_value (value);
2125  (void) area_free (Value_area, (void *) value);
2126  }
2127  return error;
2128 }
2129 
2130 /*
2131  * pr_clone_value - copy the contents of one value container to another.
2132  * return: none
2133  * src(in): source value
2134  * dest(out): destination value
2135  * Note:
2136  * For types that contain external allocations (like strings).
2137  * The contents are copied.
2138  */
2139 int
2140 pr_clone_value (const DB_VALUE * src, DB_VALUE * dest)
2141 {
2142  PR_TYPE *type;
2143  DB_TYPE src_dbtype;
2144 
2145  if (dest != NULL)
2146  {
2147  if (src == NULL)
2148  {
2149  db_make_null (dest);
2150  }
2151  else
2152  {
2153  src_dbtype = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (src);
2154 
2155  if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
2156  {
2157  db_value_domain_init (dest, src_dbtype, DB_VALUE_PRECISION (src), DB_VALUE_SCALE (src));
2158  }
2159  else if (src != dest)
2160  {
2161  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (src_dbtype);
2162  if (type != NULL)
2163  {
2164  /*
2165  * Formerly called "initval" here but that was removed as
2166  * "setval" is supposed to properly initialize the
2167  * destination domain. No need to do it twice.
2168  * Make sure the COPY flag is set in the setval call.
2169  */
2170  (*(type->setval)) (dest, src, true);
2171  }
2172  else
2173  {
2174  /*
2175  * can only get here in error conditions, initialize to NULL
2176  */
2177  db_make_null (dest);
2178  }
2179  }
2180  }
2181  }
2182 
2183  return NO_ERROR;
2184 }
2185 
2186 /*
2187  * pr_copy_value - This creates a new internal value container with a copy
2188  * of the contents of the source container.
2189  * return: new value
2190  * value(in): value to copy
2191  */
2192 DB_VALUE *
2193 pr_copy_value (DB_VALUE * value)
2194 {
2195  DB_VALUE *new_ = NULL;
2196 
2197  if (value != NULL)
2198  {
2199  new_ = pr_make_value ();
2200  if (pr_clone_value (value, new_) != NO_ERROR)
2201  {
2202  /*
2203  * oh well, couldn't allocate storage for the clone.
2204  * Note that pr_free_value can only return errors in the
2205  * case where the value has been initialized so it won't
2206  * stomp on the error code if we call it here
2207  */
2208  pr_free_value (new_);
2209  new_ = NULL;
2210  }
2211  }
2212  return new_;
2213 }
2214 
2215 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
2216 /*
2217  * pr_share_value - This is used to copy the contents of one value
2218  * container to another WITHOUT introducing a new copy of any indirect
2219  * data (like strings or sets).
2220  * return: new value
2221  * src(in): source value
2222  * dest(out): destination value
2223  * Note:
2224  * However, everything is set up properly so that the dst value
2225  * can follow the normal db_value_clear protocol.
2226  *
2227  * WARNING: src will be valid only as long as dst is. That is, after dst
2228  * gets cleared, src will have dangling pointers unless it has also been
2229  * cleared. Use with care.
2230  */
2231 int
2232 pr_share_value (DB_VALUE * src, DB_VALUE * dst)
2233 {
2234  if (src && dst && src != dst)
2235  {
2236  *dst = *src;
2237  dst->need_clear = false;
2238  if (pr_is_set_type (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (src)) && !DB_IS_NULL (src))
2239  {
2240  /*
2241  * This bites... isn't there a function for adding a
2242  * reference to a set?
2243  */
2244  src->data.set->ref_count += 1;
2245  }
2246  }
2247  return NO_ERROR;
2248 }
2249 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
2250 
2251 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
2252 /*
2253  * pr_copy_string - copy string
2254  * return: copied string
2255  * str(in): string to copy
2256  */
2257 char *
2258 pr_copy_string (const char *str)
2259 {
2260  char *copy;
2261 
2262  copy = NULL;
2263  if (str != NULL)
2264  {
2265  copy = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, strlen (str) + 1);
2266  if (copy != NULL)
2267  strcpy (copy, str);
2268  }
2269 
2270  return copy;
2271 }
2272 
2273  /*
2274  * pr_free_string - free copied string
2275  *
2276  * str(in): copied string
2277  */
2278 void
2279 pr_free_string (char *str)
2280 {
2281  if (str != NULL)
2282  {
2283  db_private_free (NULL, str);
2284  }
2285 }
2286 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

3947 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
3948 mr_cmpval_timestamptz (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
3949  int collation)
3950 {
3951  const DB_TIMESTAMPTZ *ts_tz1, *ts_tz2;
3952 
3953  /* TIMESTAMP with TZ compares the same as TIMESTAMP (zone is not taken into account); the first component of
3954  * TIMESTAMPTZ is a TIMESTAMP, it is safe to use the TIMESTAMP part of DB_DATA union to read it */
3955  ts_tz1 = db_get_timestamptz (value1);
3956  ts_tz2 = db_get_timestamptz (value2);
3957 
3958 #if defined (SA_MODE)
3959  if (tz_Compare_timestamptz_tz_id == true && ts_tz1->tz_id != ts_tz2->tz_id)
3960  {
3961  return DB_NE;
3962  }
3963 #endif
3964 
3965  return MR_CMP (ts_tz1->timestamp, ts_tz2->timestamp);
3966 }

4209 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
4210 mr_index_cmpdisk_datetime (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order,
4211  int *start_colp)
4212 {
4213  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
4214  DB_DATETIME dt1, dt2;
4215 
4216  assert (domain != NULL);
4217 
4218  if (mem1 == mem2)
4219  {
4220  return DB_EQ;
4221  }
4222 
4223  COPYMEM (unsigned int, &dt1.date, (char *)mem1 + OR_DATETIME_DATE);
4224  COPYMEM (unsigned int, &dt1.time, (char *) mem1 + OR_DATETIME_TIME);
4225  COPYMEM (unsigned int, &dt2.date, (char *) mem2 + OR_DATETIME_DATE);
4226  COPYMEM (unsigned int, &dt2.time, (char *) mem2 + OR_DATETIME_TIME);
4227 
4228  if (dt1.date < dt2.date)
4229  {
4230  c = DB_LT;
4231  }
4232  else if (dt1.date > dt2.date)
4233  {
4234  c = DB_GT;
4235  }
4236  else
4237  {
4238  if (dt1.time < dt2.time)
4239  {
4240  c = DB_LT;
4241  }
4242  else if (dt1.time > dt2.time)
4243  {
4244  c = DB_GT;
4245  }
4246  else
4247  {
4248  c = DB_EQ;
4249  }
4250  }
4251 
4252  return c;
4253 }
4254 
4255 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
4256 mr_data_cmpdisk_datetime (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
4257 {
4258  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
4259  DB_DATETIME dt1, dt2;
4260 
4261  assert (domain != NULL);
4262 
4263  if (mem1 == mem2)
4264  {
4265  return DB_EQ;
4266  }
4267 
4268  OR_GET_DATETIME (mem1, &dt1);
4269  OR_GET_DATETIME (mem2, &dt2);
4270 
4271  if (dt1.date < dt2.date)
4272  {
4273  c = DB_LT;
4274  }
4275  else if (dt1.date > dt2.date)
4276  {
4277  c = DB_GT;
4278  }
4279  else
4280  {
4281  if (dt1.time < dt2.time)
4282  {
4283  c = DB_LT;
4284  }
4285  else if (dt1.time > dt2.time)
4286  {
4287  c = DB_GT;
4288  }
4289  else
4290  {
4291  c = DB_EQ;
4292  }
4293  }
4294 
4295  return c;
4296 }
4297 
4298 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
4299 mr_cmpval_datetime (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
4300  int collation)
4301 {
4302  const DB_DATETIME *dt1, *dt2;
4303  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
4304 
4305  dt1 = db_get_datetime (value1);
4306  dt2 = db_get_datetime (value2);
4307 
4308  if (dt1->date < dt2->date)
4309  {
4310  c = DB_LT;
4311  }
4312  else if (dt1->date > dt2->date)
4313  {
4314  c = DB_GT;
4315  }
4316  else
4317  {
4318  if (dt1->time < dt2->time)
4319  {
4320  c = DB_LT;
4321  }
4322  else if (dt1->time > dt2->time)
4323  {
4324  c = DB_GT;
4325  }
4326  else
4327  {
4328  c = DB_EQ;
4329  }
4330  }
4331 
4332  return c;
4333 }

4514 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
4515 mr_cmpval_datetimetz (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
4516  int collation)
4517 {
4518  const DB_DATETIMETZ *dt_tz1, *dt_tz2;
4519  const DB_DATETIME *dt1, *dt2;
4520  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
4521 
4522  dt_tz1 = db_get_datetimetz (value1);
4523  dt_tz2 = db_get_datetimetz (value2);
4524 
4525  dt1 = &(dt_tz1->datetime);
4526  dt2 = &(dt_tz2->datetime);
4527 
4528 #if defined (SA_MODE)
4529  if (tz_Compare_datetimetz_tz_id == true && dt_tz1->tz_id != dt_tz2->tz_id)
4530  {
4531  return DB_NE;
4532  }
4533 #endif /* SA_MODE */
4534 
4535  if (dt1->date < dt2->date)
4536  {
4537  c = DB_LT;
4538  }
4539  else if (dt1->date > dt2->date)
4540  {
4541  c = DB_GT;
4542  }
4543  else
4544  {
4545  if (dt1->time < dt2->time)
4546  {
4547  c = DB_LT;
4548  }
4549  else if (dt1->time > dt2->time)
4550  {
4551  c = DB_GT;
4552  }
4553  else
4554  {
4555  c = DB_EQ;
4556  }
4557  }
4558 
4559  return c;
4560 }

4940 
4941 /*
4942  * TYPE OBJECT
4943  */
4944 
4945 /*
4946  * This is a bit different than the other primitive types in that the memory
4947  * value and the DB_VALUE representations are not the same. The memory value
4948  * will be represented with a WS_MEMOID structure to avoid creating MOPs until
4949  * they are actually needed.
4950  *
4951  * These types are not available on the server since there is no workspace
4952  * over there. Although in standalone mode, we could promote OIDs to MOPs
4953  * on both sides, use the db_on_server flag to control this so we make
4954  * both sides behave similarly even though we're in standalone mode.
4955  * The "mem" functions will in general be commented out since they
4956  * call things that don't exist on the server. THe "val" functions will
4957  * exist so that things tagged as DB_TYPE_OBJECT can be read as OID values.
4958  *
4959  */
4960 
4961 
4962 /*
4963  * mr_null_oid - This is used to set an OID to the NULL state.
4964  * return: void
4965  * oid(out): oid to initialize
4966  * Note:
4967  * SET_OID_NULL does the actual work by setting the volid to -1 but it
4968  * leaves garbage in the other fields which can be stored on disk and
4969  * generally looks alarming when you encounter it later. Before
4970  * calling SET_OID_NULL, initialize the fields to nice zero values.
4971  * Should be an inline function.
4972  */
4973 static void
4974 mr_null_oid (OID * oid)
4975 {
4976  oid->pageid = 0;
4977  oid->volid = 0;
4978  oid->slotid = 0;
4979

5024 static int
5025 mr_setmem_object (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
5026 {

5028 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)

5030  OID *oid;
5031  MOP op;
5032 
5033  if (value == NULL)

5036  mem->pointer = NULL;
5037  }
5038  else
5039  {

5044  }
5045  else

5048  mem->oid.volid = oid->volid;
5049  mem->oid.pageid = oid->pageid;
5050  mem->oid.slotid = oid->slotid;
5051  if (op->is_temp)
5052  {
5053  mem->pointer = NULL;
5054  }
5055  else
5056  {
5057  mem->pointer = op;
5058  }
5059  }
5060  }
5061 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
5062  return NO_ERROR;

5090  (void) db_make_object (value, NULL);
5091  }
5092  }

5094  else

5096 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */

5098  return error;

5101 
5102 static int
5103 mr_setval_object (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
5104 {
5105  int error = NO_ERROR;
5106  OID *oid;
5107 
5108 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5109  if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
5110  {
5111  PRIM_SET_NULL (dest);
5112  }
5113  /* can get here on the server when dispatching through set element domains */
5114  else if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (src) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5115  {
5116  /* make sure that the target type is set properly */
5117  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_OID, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5118  oid = (OID *) db_get_oid (src);
5119  error = db_make_oid (dest, oid);
5120  }
5121  else if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (src) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
5122  {
5123  /* If we're logically on the server, we probably shouldn't have gotten here but if we do, don't continue with the
5124  * object representation, de-swizzle it back to an OID. */
5125  if (db_on_server)
5126  {
5127  DB_OBJECT *obj;
5128  /* what should this do for ISVID mops? */
5129  obj = db_get_object (src);
5130  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_OID, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5131  oid = WS_OID (obj);
5132  error = db_make_oid (dest, oid);
5133  }
5134  else
5135  {
5136  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_OBJECT, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5137  error = db_make_object (dest, db_get_object (src));
5138  }
5139  }
5140 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
5141  /*
5142  * If we're really on the server, we can only get here when dispatching
5143  * through set element domains. The value must contain an OID.
5144  */
5145  if (DB_IS_NULL (src) || DB_VALUE_TYPE (src) != DB_TYPE_OID)
5146  {
5147  PRIM_SET_NULL (dest);
5148  }
5149  else
5150  {
5151  oid = (OID *) db_get_oid (src);
5152  error = db_make_oid (dest, oid);
5153  }
5154 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
5155 
5156  return error;
5157 }

5167 /*
5168  * mr_lengthval_object - checks if the object is virtual or not. and returns
5169  * property type size.
5170  * return: If it is virtual object returns calculated the DB_TYPE_VOBJ
5171  * packed size. returns DB_TYPE_OID otherwise
5172  * value(in): value to get length
5173  * disk(in): indicator that it is disk object
5174  */
5175 static int
5176 mr_data_lengthval_object (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
5177 {
5178 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5179  MOP mop;
5180 #endif
5181  int size;
5182 
5183  if (disk)
5184  {
5185  size = OR_OID_SIZE;
5186  }
5187  else
5188  {
5189  size = MR_OID_SIZE;
5190  }
5191 
5192 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5193  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT && disk)
5194  {
5195  mop = db_get_object (value);
5196  if ((mop == NULL) || (WS_IS_DELETED (mop)))
5197  {
5198  /* The size of a NULL is OR_OID_SIZE, which is already set (from Jeff L.) */
5199  }
5200  else if (WS_ISVID (mop))
5201  {
5202  DB_VALUE vmop_seq;
5203  int error;
5204 
5205  error = vid_object_to_vobj (mop, &vmop_seq);
5206  if (error >= 0)
5207  {
5208  size = mr_data_lengthval_set (&vmop_seq, disk);
5209  pr_clear_value (&vmop_seq);
5210  }
5211  }
5212  }
5213 #endif
5214 
5215  return size;
5216 }
5217 
5218 static void
5219 mr_data_writemem_object (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
5220 {
5221 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE) /* there is no need for writemem on the server */
5222  WS_MEMOID *mem = (WS_MEMOID *) memptr;
5223  OID *oidp;
5224 
5225  oidp = NULL;
5226  if (mem != NULL)
5227  {
5228  oidp = &mem->oid;
5229  }
5230 
5231  if (oidp == NULL)
5232  {
5233  /* construct an unbound oid */
5234  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5235  }
5236  else if (OID_ISTEMP (oidp))
5237  {
5238  /* Temporary oid, must get a permanent one. This should only happen if the MOID has a valid MOP. Check for
5239  * deletion */
5240  if ((mem->pointer == NULL) || (WS_IS_DELETED (mem->pointer)))
5241  {
5242  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5243  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_MR_TEMP_OID_WITHOUT_MOP, 0);
5244  }
5245  else
5246  {
5247  oidp = WS_OID (mem->pointer);
5248  if (OID_ISTEMP (oidp))
5249  {
5250  /* a MOP with a temporary OID, make an entry in the OID fixup table if we have one, otherwise, stop and
5251  * assign a permanent one. */
5252  oidp = tf_need_permanent_oid (buf, mem->pointer);
5253  if (oidp == NULL)
5254  {
5255  /* normally would have used or_abort by now */
5256  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5257  }
5258  }
5259  }
5260  }
5261  else
5262  {
5263  /* normal OID check for deletion */
5264  if ((mem->pointer != NULL) && (WS_IS_DELETED (mem->pointer)))
5265  {
5266  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5267  }
5268  }
5269 
5270  or_put_oid (buf, oidp);
5271 
5272 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
5273  /* should never get here but in case we do, dump a NULL OID into the buffer. */
5274  printf ("mr_writemem_object: called on the server !\n");
5275  or_put_oid (buf, (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid));
5276 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
5277 }

5299 #endif

5308 
5309 static int
5310 mr_data_writeval_object (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
5311 {
5312 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5313  MOP mop;
5314 #endif
5315  OID *oidp = NULL;
5316  int rc = NO_ERROR;
5317 
5318 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5319  if (db_on_server || pr_Inhibit_oid_promotion)
5320  {
5321  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5322  {
5323  oidp = db_get_oid (value);
5324  rc = or_put_oid (buf, oidp);
5325  return rc;
5326  }
5327  else
5328  {
5329  return ER_FAILED;
5330  }
5331  }
5332  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
5333  {
5334  mop = db_get_object (value);
5335  if ((mop == NULL) || (WS_IS_DELETED (mop)))
5336  {
5337  rc = or_put_oid (buf, (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid));
5338  }
5339  else if (WS_ISVID (mop))
5340  {
5341  DB_VALUE vmop_seq;
5342  int error;
5343 
5344  error = vid_object_to_vobj (mop, &vmop_seq);
5345  if (error >= 0)
5346  {
5347  rc = mr_data_writeval_set (buf, &vmop_seq);
5348  pr_clear_value (&vmop_seq);
5349  }
5350  else
5351  {
5352  rc = ER_FAILED;
5353  }
5354  }
5355  else
5356  {
5357  oidp = WS_OID (mop);
5358  if (OID_ISTEMP (oidp))
5359  {
5360  /* a MOP with a temporary OID, make an entry in the OID fixup table if we have one, otherwise, stop and
5361  * assign a permanent one. */
5362  oidp = tf_need_permanent_oid (buf, mop);
5363  if (oidp == NULL)
5364  {
5365  /* normally would have used or_abort by now */
5366  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5367  }
5368  }
5369  rc = or_put_oid (buf, oidp);
5370  }
5371  }
5372  else if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5373  {
5374  oidp = db_get_oid (value);
5375  rc = or_put_oid (buf, oidp);
5376  }
5377  else
5378  {
5379  /* should never get here ! */
5380  rc = or_put_oid (buf, (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid));
5381  }
5382 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
5383  /* on the server, the value must contain an OID */
5384  oidp = db_get_oid (value);
5385  rc = or_put_oid (buf, oidp);
5386 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
5387  return rc;
5388 }

5399 static int
5400 mr_data_readval_object (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
5401  int copy_buf_len)
5402 {
5403  OID oid;
5404  int rc = NO_ERROR;
5405 
5406 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5407  if (value == NULL)
5408  {
5409  rc = or_advance (buf, tp_Object.disksize);
5410  }
5411  else
5412  {
5413  if (db_on_server || pr_Inhibit_oid_promotion)
5414  {
5415  /* basically the same as mr_readval_server_oid, don't promote OIDs */
5416  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_OID, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5417  rc = or_get_oid (buf, &oid);
5418  db_make_oid (value, &oid);
5419  }
5420  else
5421  {
5422  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_OBJECT, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5423 
5424  rc = or_get_oid (buf, &oid);
5425  /*
5426  * if the OID is NULL, leave the value with the NULL bit set
5427  * and don't bother to put the OID inside.
5428  * I added this because it seemed logical, does it break anything ?
5429  */
5430  if (!OID_ISNULL (&oid))
5431  {
5432  db_make_object (value, ws_mop (&oid, NULL));
5433  if (db_get_object (value) == NULL)
5434  {
5435  or_abort (buf);
5436  return ER_FAILED;
5437  }
5438  }
5439  }
5440  }
5441 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
5442  /* on the server, we only read OIDs */
5443  if (value == NULL)
5444  {
5445  rc = or_advance (buf, tp_Object.disksize);
5446  }
5447  else
5448  {
5449  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_OID, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
5450  rc = or_get_oid (buf, &oid);
5451  /* should we be checking for the NULL OID here ? */
5452  db_make_oid (value, &oid);
5453  }
5454 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
5455  return rc;
5456 }

5466 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
5467 mr_data_cmpdisk_object (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
5468 {
5469  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
5470  OID o1, o2;
5471  int oidc;
5472 
5473  assert (domain != NULL);
5474 
5475  OR_GET_OID (mem1, &o1);
5476  OR_GET_OID (mem2, &o2);
5477  /* if we ever store virtual objects, this will need to be changed. However, since its known the only disk
5478  * representation of objects is an OID, this is a valid optimization */
5479

5481  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (oidc);

5485 
5486 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
5487 mr_cmpval_object (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
5488  int collation)
5489 {
5490 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
5491  const OID *o1, *o2;
5492  int oidc;
5493 
5494  /*
5495  * we need to be careful here because even though the domain may
5496  * say object, it may really be an OID (especially on the server).
5497  */
5498  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value1) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5499  {
5500  o1 = db_get_oid (value1);
5501  }
5502  else
5503  {
5504  assert (false);
5505  o1 = &oid_Null_oid;
5506  }
5507 
5508  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value2) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5509  {
5510  o2 = db_get_oid (value2);
5511  }
5512  else
5513  {
5514  assert (false);
5515  o2 = &oid_Null_oid;
5516  }
5517 
5518  oidc = oid_compare (o1, o2);
5519  return MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (oidc);
5520 #else /* !SERVER_MODE */
5521  /* on the client, we must also handle virtual db_object types */
5522  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
5523  OID *o1 = NULL, *o2 = NULL;
5524  DB_OBJECT *mop1 = NULL, *mop2 = NULL, *class1, *class2;
5525  int virtual_ = 0;
5526  int nonupdate = 0;
5527  DB_VALUE keys1, keys2;
5528 
5529  /*
5530  * we need to be careful here because even though the domain may
5531  * say object, it may really be an OID (especially on the server).
5532  */
5533  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value1) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5534  {
5535  o1 = db_get_oid (value1);
5536  }
5537  else
5538  {
5539  mop1 = db_get_object (value1);
5540  if (WS_ISVID (mop1))
5541  {
5542  if (db_is_updatable_object (mop1))
5543  {
5544  mop1 = db_real_instance (mop1);
5545  }
5546  else
5547  {
5548  nonupdate = 1;
5549  }
5550 
5551  if (mop1 != NULL)
5552  {
5553  if (WS_ISVID (mop1))
5554  {
5555  /* non updateble object or proxy object */
5556  virtual_ = 1;
5557  }
5558  else
5559  {
5560  o1 = WS_OID (mop1);
5561  }
5562  }
5563  else
5564  {
5565  o1 = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5566  }
5567  }
5568  else
5569  {
5570  o1 = WS_OID (mop1);
5571  }
5572  }
5573 
5574  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value2) == DB_TYPE_OID)
5575  {
5576  o2 = db_get_oid (value2);
5577  }
5578  else
5579  {
5580  mop2 = db_get_object (value2);
5581  if (WS_ISVID (mop2))
5582  {
5583  if (db_is_updatable_object (mop2))
5584  {
5585  mop2 = db_real_instance (mop2);
5586  }
5587  else
5588  {
5589  nonupdate += 2;
5590  }
5591 
5592  if (mop2 != NULL)
5593  {
5594  if (WS_ISVID (mop2))
5595  {
5596  /* non updateble object or proxy object */
5597  virtual_ += 2;
5598  }
5599  else
5600  {
5601  o2 = WS_OID (mop2);
5602  }
5603  }
5604  else
5605  {
5606  o2 = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5607  }
5608  }
5609  else
5610  {
5611  o2 = WS_OID (mop2);
5612  }
5613  }
5614 
5615  if (virtual_ == 0)
5616  {
5617  int oidc = oid_compare (o1, o2);
5618  return MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (oidc);
5619  }
5620 
5621  if (mop1 == mop2)
5622  {
5623  return DB_EQ; /* an optimization */
5624  }
5625 
5626  if (virtual_ == 1)
5627  {
5628  return DB_LT; /* consistent comparison of oids and */
5629  }
5630  if (virtual_ == 2)
5631  {
5632  return DB_GT; /* non-oid based vobjs, they are never equal */
5633  }
5634 
5635  /* virtual must be 3, meaning both objects are either proxies or non-updatable objects */
5636 
5637  if (nonupdate == 1)
5638  {
5639  return DB_LT; /* again, a consistent comparison */
5640  }
5641 
5642  if (nonupdate == 2)
5643  {
5644  return DB_GT; /* for proxy mop and non-updatable mop */
5645  }
5646 
5647  if (nonupdate == 0)
5648  {
5649  int oidc;
5650  /*
5651  * comparing two proxy mops, the must both be from the
5652  * same proxy class. Compare the proxy classes oids.
5653  * Note class mops are never virtual mops.
5654  */
5655  class1 = db_get_class (mop1);
5656  class2 = db_get_class (mop2);
5657  o1 = (class1) ? WS_OID (class1) : (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5658  o2 = (class2) ? WS_OID (class2) : (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
5659  oidc = oid_compare (o1, o2);
5660  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (oidc);
5661 
5662  /*
5663  * as long as the result is not equal, we are done
5664  * If its equal, we need to continue with a key test below.
5665  */
5666  if (c != DB_EQ)
5667  {
5668  return c;
5669  }
5670  }
5671 
5672  /*
5673  * here, nonupdate must be 3 or 0 and
5674  * we must have two non-updatable mops, or two proxy mops
5675  * from the same proxy. Consequently, their keys are comparable
5676  * to identify the object.
5677  */
5678  vid_get_keys (mop1, &keys1);
5679  vid_get_keys (mop2, &keys2);
5680  return tp_value_compare (&keys1, &keys2, do_coercion, total_order);
5681 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
5682 }
5683 
5684 
5685 
5686 
5687 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
5688 
5689 /*
5690  * pr_write_mop - write an OID to a disk representation buffer given a MOP
5691  * instead of a WS_MEMOID.
5692  * return:
5693  * buf(): transformer buffer
5694  * mop(): mop to transform
5695  * Note:
5696  * mr_write_object can't be used because it takes a WS_MEMOID as is the
5697  * case for object references in instances.
5698  * This must stay in sync with mr_write_object above !
5699  */
5700 void
5701 pr_write_mop (OR_BUF * buf, MOP mop)
5702 {
5703  DB_VALUE value;
5704 
5705  mr_initval_object (&value, 0, 0);
5706  db_make_object (&value, mop);
5707  mr_data_writeval_object (buf, &value);
5708  mr_setval_object (&value, NULL, false);
5709 }
5710 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */

5744 static int
5745 mr_setmem_elo (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
5746 {
5747  int rc;
5748  DB_ELO *elo, *e;
5749 
5750  if (memptr != NULL)
5751  {
5752  mr_freemem_elo (memptr);
5753  mr_initmem_elo (memptr, domain);
5754 
5755  if (value != NULL && (e = db_get_elo (value)) != NULL)
5756  {
5757  elo = (DB_ELO *) db_private_alloc (NULL, sizeof (DB_ELO));
5758  if (elo == NULL)
5759  {
5760  return ((er_errid () == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : er_errid ());
5761  }
5762  rc = elo_copy_structure (e, elo);
5763  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
5764  {
5765  if (elo != NULL)
5766  {
5767  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, elo);
5768  }
5769  return rc;
5770  }
5771 
5772  *((DB_ELO **) memptr) = elo;
5773  }
5774  }
5775  else
5776  {
5777  assert_release (0);
5778  }
5779 
5780  return NO_ERROR;
5781 }

5783 static int
5784 getmem_elo_with_type (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy, DB_TYPE type)
5785 {
5786  DB_ELO *elo;
5787  int r = NO_ERROR;
5788 
5789  if (memptr == NULL)
5790  {
5791  PRIM_SET_NULL (value);
5792  return r;
5793  }
5794 
5795  elo = *((DB_ELO **) memptr);
5796 
5797  if (elo == NULL || elo->size < 0)
5798  {
5799  PRIM_SET_NULL (value);
5800  return r;
5801  }
5802 
5803  if (copy)
5804  {
5805  DB_ELO e;
5806 
5807  r = elo_copy_structure (elo, &e);
5808  if (r == NO_ERROR)
5809  {
5810  db_make_elo (value, type, &e);
5811  value->need_clear = true;
5812  }
5813  }
5814  else
5815  {
5816  db_make_elo (value, type, elo);
5817  }
5818 
5819  return r;
5820 }

5892 static int
5893 mr_data_lengthmem_elo (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
5894 {
5895  int len = 0;
5896 
5897  if (!disk)
5898  {
5899  assert (tp_Elo.size == tp_Blob.size);
5900  assert (tp_Blob.size == tp_Clob.size);
5901  len = tp_Elo.size;
5902  }
5903  else if (memptr != NULL)
5904  {
5905  DB_ELO *elo = *((DB_ELO **) memptr);
5906 
5907  if (elo != NULL && elo->type != ELO_NULL)
5908  {
5909  len = (OR_BIGINT_SIZE
5910  + or_packed_string_length (elo->locator, NULL)
5911  + or_packed_string_length (elo->meta_data, NULL) + OR_INT_SIZE);
5912  }
5913  }
5914  else
5915  {
5916  assert_release (0);
5917  }
5918 
5919  return len;
5920 }
5921 
5922 static int
5923 mr_data_lengthval_elo (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
5924 {
5925  DB_ELO *elo;
5926 
5927  if (value != NULL)
5928  {
5929  elo = db_get_elo (value);
5930  return mr_data_lengthmem_elo ((void *) &elo, NULL, disk);
5931  }
5932  else
5933  {
5934  return 0;
5935  }
5936 }
5937 
5938 static void
5939 mr_data_writemem_elo (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
5940 {
5941  DB_ELO *elo;
5942 
5943  if (memptr == NULL)
5944  {
5945  assert_release (0);
5946  return;
5947  }
5948 
5949  elo = *((DB_ELO **) memptr);
5950 
5951  if (elo != NULL && elo->type != ELO_NULL)
5952  {
5953  /* size */
5954  or_put_bigint (buf, elo->size);
5955 
5956  /* locator */
5957  assert (elo->locator != NULL);
5958  or_put_int (buf, or_packed_string_length (elo->locator, NULL) - OR_INT_SIZE);
5959  if (elo->locator != NULL)
5960  {
5961  or_put_string_aligned (buf, elo->locator);
5962  }
5963 
5964  /* meta_data */
5965  or_put_int (buf, or_packed_string_length (elo->meta_data, NULL) - OR_INT_SIZE);
5966  if (elo->meta_data != NULL)
5967  {
5968  or_put_string_aligned (buf, elo->meta_data);
5969  }
5970 
5971  /* type */
5972  or_put_int (buf, elo->type);
5973  }
5974 }
5975 
5976 static void
5977 peekmem_elo (OR_BUF * buf, DB_ELO * elo)
5978 {
5979  int locator_len, meta_data_len;
5980  int rc = NO_ERROR;
5981 
5982  /* size */
5983  elo->size = or_get_bigint (buf, &rc);
5984 
5985  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
5986  {
5987  assert (false);
5988  goto error;
5989  }
5990 
5991  /* locator */
5992  locator_len = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
5993  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
5994  {
5995  assert (false);
5996  goto error;
5997  }
5998  if (locator_len > 0)
5999  {
6000  elo->locator = buf->ptr;
6001  }
6002  else
6003  {
6004  assert (false);
6005  goto error;
6006  }
6007  rc = or_advance (buf, locator_len);
6008  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
6009  {
6010  assert (false);
6011  goto error;
6012  }
6013 
6014  /* meta_data */
6015  meta_data_len = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
6016  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
6017  {
6018  assert (false);
6019  goto error;
6020  }
6021  if (meta_data_len > 0)
6022  {
6023  elo->meta_data = buf->ptr;
6024  }
6025  else
6026  {
6027  elo->meta_data = NULL;
6028  }
6029  rc = or_advance (buf, meta_data_len);
6030  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
6031  {
6032  assert (false);
6033  goto error;
6034  }
6035 
6036  /* type */
6037  elo->type = (DB_ELO_TYPE) or_get_int (buf, &rc);
6038  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
6039  {
6040  assert (false);
6041  goto error;
6042  }
6043 
6044  return;
6045 
6046 error:
6047  elo->locator = NULL;
6048  elo->meta_data = NULL;
6049  elo->size = 0;
6050  elo->type = ELO_NULL;
6051 }
6052 
6053 static void
6054 mr_data_readmem_elo (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
6055 {
6056  DB_ELO *elo;
6057  DB_ELO e;
6058  int rc = NO_ERROR;
6059 
6060  if (size == 0)
6061  {
6062  return;
6063  }
6064 
6065  if (memptr == NULL)
6066  {
6067  or_advance (buf, size);
6068  return;
6069  }
6070 
6071  elo = (DB_ELO *) db_private_alloc (NULL, sizeof (DB_ELO));
6072  if (elo == NULL)
6073  {
6074  or_abort (buf);
6075  }
6076  else
6077  {
6078  peekmem_elo (buf, &e);
6079 
6080  rc = elo_copy_structure (&e, elo);
6081  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
6082  {
6083  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, elo);
6084  or_abort (buf);
6085  }
6086  }
6087 
6088  *((DB_ELO **) memptr) = elo;
6089 }
6090 
6091 static int
6092 mr_data_writeval_elo (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
6093 {
6094  DB_ELO *elo;
6095 
6096  elo = db_get_elo (value);
6097  mr_data_writemem_elo (buf, (void *) &elo, NULL);
6098  return NO_ERROR;
6099 }

6101 static int
6102 readval_elo_with_type (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
6103  int copy_buf_len, DB_TYPE type)
6104 {
6105  int rc = NO_ERROR;
6106 
6107  if (value == NULL)
6108  {
6109  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
6110  return rc;
6111  }
6112 
6113  if (size != 0)
6114  {
6115  if (copy)
6116  {
6117  DB_ELO *e = NULL;
6118 
6119  mr_data_readmem_elo (buf, (void *) &e, NULL, size);
6120  /* structure copy - to value->data.elo */
6121  rc = db_make_elo (value, type, e);
6122  if (e != NULL)
6123  {
6124  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, e);
6125  }
6126 
6127  value->need_clear = true;
6128  }
6129  else
6130  {
6131  DB_ELO elo;
6132 
6133  peekmem_elo (buf, &elo);
6134  /* structure copy - to value->data.elo */
6135  rc = db_make_elo (value, type, &elo);
6136  }
6137  }
6138 
6139  return rc;
6140 }

6384 static int
6385 mr_setmem_ptr (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)

6388

6628 /*
6629  * TYPE OID

6631  * DB_TYPE_OID is not really a "domain" type, it is rather a physical

6633  * on DB_TYPE_ codes however, we need a fleshed out type vector
6634  * for this.

6636  * This is used by the server where we have no DB_OBJECT handles.
6637  * It can also be used on the client in places where we defer
6638  * the "swizzling" of OID references (e.g. inside sets).
6639  *
6640  * We don't have to handle the case where values come in with DB_TYPE_OBJECT
6641  * as we do in the _object handlers, true ?
6642  *
6643  */

6826 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
6827 mr_index_cmpdisk_oid (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)

6832

6834

6836  COPYMEM (short, &o1.slotid, (char *) mem1 + OR_OID_SLOTID);
6837  COPYMEM (short, &o1.volid, (char *) mem1 + OR_OID_VOLID);
6838

6840  COPYMEM (short, &o2.slotid, (char *) mem2 + OR_OID_SLOTID);
6841  COPYMEM (short, &o2.volid, (char *) mem2 + OR_OID_VOLID);
6842 
6843  oidc = oid_compare (&o1, &o2);
6844  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (oidc);
6845 
6846  return c;
6847 }

6887 
6888 /*
6889  * TYPE SET
6890  *
6891  * This is easily the most complicated primitive type.
6892  * Sets are defined to be owned by an object.
6893  * They may be checked out of an object and accessed directly through the
6894  * set structure. We need to move maintenance of set ownership down
6895  * from the object layer to this layer. This will avoid a lot of special
6896  * cases for sets that now exist in the pr_ and obj_ layers.
6897  */
6898 
6899 
6900 static void
6901 mr_initmem_set (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
6902 {
6903  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
6904 
6905  *mem = NULL;
6906 }
6907 
6908 static void
6909 mr_initval_set (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)
6910 {
6911  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_SET, precision, scale);
6912  db_make_set (value, NULL);
6913 }
6914 
6915 static int
6916 mr_setmem_set (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
6917 {
6918  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
6919  int error = NO_ERROR;
6920  SETOBJ *set;
6921  SETREF *ref;
6922 
6923  /*
6924  * NOTE: assumes ownership info has already been placed
6925  * in the set reference by the caller
6926  */
6927  if ((value != NULL) && ((ref = db_get_set (value)) != NULL))
6928  {
6929  set = ref->set;
6930  if (*mem != set)
6931  {
6932  if (*mem != NULL)
6933  {
6934  error = setobj_release (*mem);
6935  }
6936  *mem = set;
6937  }
6938  }
6939  else
6940  {
6941  if (*mem != NULL)
6942  {
6943  error = setobj_release (*mem);
6944  }
6945  mr_initmem_set (mem, domain);
6946  }
6947  return error;
6948 }
6949 
6950 static int
6951 mr_getmem_set (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
6952 {
6953  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
6954  int error = NO_ERROR;
6955  SETOBJ *set;
6956  SETREF *ref;
6957 
6958  set = *mem;
6959  if (set == NULL)
6960  {
6961  error = db_make_set (value, NULL);
6962  }
6963  else
6964  {
6965  ref = setobj_get_reference (set);
6966  if (ref)
6967  {
6968  error = db_make_set (value, ref);
6969  }
6970  else
6971  {
6972  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6973  error = er_errid ();
6974  (void) db_make_set (value, NULL);
6975  }
6976  }
6977  /*
6978  * NOTE: assumes that ownership info will already have been set or will
6979  * be set by the caller
6980  */
6981 
6982  return error;
6983 }
6984 
6985 static int
6986 mr_setval_set_internal (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy, DB_TYPE set_type)
6987 {
6988  int error = NO_ERROR;
6989  SETREF *src_ref, *ref;
6990 
6991  if (src != NULL && !DB_IS_NULL (src) && ((src_ref = db_get_set (src)) != NULL))
6992  {
6993  if (!copy)
6994  {
6995  ref = src_ref;
6996  /* must increment the reference count */
6997  ref->ref_count++;
6998  }
6999  else
7000  {
7001  /* need to check if we have a disk_image, if so we just copy it */
7002  if (src_ref->disk_set)
7003  {
7004  ref = set_make_reference ();
7005  if (ref == NULL)
7006  {
7007  goto err_set;
7008  }
7009  else
7010  {
7011  /* Copy the bits into a freshly allocated buffer. */
7012  ref->disk_set = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_ref->disk_size);
7013  if (ref->disk_set == NULL)
7014  {
7015  goto err_set;
7016  }
7017  else
7018  {
7019  ref->need_clear = true;
7020  ref->disk_size = src_ref->disk_size;
7021  ref->disk_domain = src_ref->disk_domain;
7022  memcpy (ref->disk_set, src_ref->disk_set, src_ref->disk_size);
7023  }
7024  }
7025  }
7026  else
7027  {
7028  ref = set_copy (src_ref);
7029  if (ref == NULL)
7030  {
7031  goto err_set;
7032  }
7033  }
7034  }
7035 
7036  switch (set_type)
7037  {
7038  case DB_TYPE_SET:
7039  db_make_set (dest, ref);
7040  break;
7041  case DB_TYPE_MULTISET:
7042  db_make_multiset (dest, ref);
7043  break;
7044  case DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
7045  db_make_sequence (dest, ref);
7046  break;
7047  default:
7048  break;
7049  }
7050  }
7051  else
7052  {
7053  db_value_domain_init (dest, set_type, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
7054  }
7055  return error;
7056 
7057 err_set:
7058  /* couldn't allocate storage for set */
7059  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7060  error = er_errid ();
7061  switch (set_type)
7062  {
7063  case DB_TYPE_SET:
7064  db_make_set (dest, NULL);
7065  break;
7066  case DB_TYPE_MULTISET:
7067  db_make_multiset (dest, NULL);
7068  break;
7069  case DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
7070  db_make_sequence (dest, NULL);
7071  break;
7072  default:
7073  break;
7074  }
7075  PRIM_SET_NULL (dest);
7076  return error;
7077 }
7078 
7079 static int
7080 mr_setval_set (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
7081 {
7082  return mr_setval_set_internal (dest, src, copy, DB_TYPE_SET);
7083 }
7084 
7085 static int
7086 mr_data_lengthmem_set (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
7087 {
7088  int size;
7089 
7090  if (!disk)
7091  {
7092  size = tp_Set.size;
7093  }
7094  else
7095  {
7096  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
7097 
7098  size = or_packed_set_length (*mem, 0);
7099  }
7100 
7101  return size;
7102 }
7103 
7104 static int
7105 mr_data_lengthval_set (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
7106 {
7107  SETREF *ref;
7108  SETOBJ *set;
7109  int size;
7110 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7111  int pin;
7112 #endif
7113 
7114  size = 0;
7115 
7116  if (!disk)
7117  {
7118  size = sizeof (DB_SET *);
7119  }
7120  else
7121  {
7122  ref = db_get_set (value);
7123  if (ref != NULL)
7124  {
7125  /* should have a set_ function for this ! */
7126  if (ref->disk_set)
7127  {
7128  size = ref->disk_size;
7129  }
7130  else if (set_get_setobj (ref, &set, 0) == NO_ERROR)
7131  {
7132  if (set != NULL)
7133  {
7134  /* probably no need to pin here but it can't hurt */
7135 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7136  pin = ws_pin (ref->owner, 1);
7137 #endif
7138  size = or_packed_set_length (set, 1);
7139 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7140  (void) ws_pin (ref->owner, pin);
7141 #endif
7142  }
7143  }
7144  }
7145  }
7146  return size;
7147 }
7148 
7149 static void
7150 mr_data_writemem_set (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
7151 {
7152  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
7153 
7154  if (*mem != NULL)
7155  {
7156  /* note that we don't have to pin the object here since that will have been handled above this leve. */
7157  or_put_set (buf, *mem, 0);
7158  }
7159 }
7160 
7161 static int
7162 mr_data_writeval_set (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
7163 {
7164  SETREF *ref;
7165  SETOBJ *set;
7166  int size;
7167 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7168  int pin;
7169 #endif
7170  int rc = NO_ERROR;
7171 
7172  ref = db_get_set (value);
7173  if (ref != NULL)
7174  {
7175  /* If we have a disk image of the set, we can just copy those bits here. This assumes very careful maintenance
7176  * of the disk and memory images. Currently, we only have one or the other. That is, when we transform the disk
7177  * image to memory, we clear the disk image. */
7178  if (ref->disk_set)
7179  {
7180  /* check for overflow */
7181  if ((((ptrdiff_t) (buf->endptr - buf->ptr)) < (ptrdiff_t) ref->disk_size))
7182  {
7183  return or_overflow (buf);
7184  }
7185  else
7186  {
7187  memcpy (buf->ptr, ref->disk_set, ref->disk_size);
7188  rc = or_advance (buf, ref->disk_size);
7189  }
7190  }
7191  else if (set_get_setobj (ref, &set, 0) == NO_ERROR)
7192  {
7193  if (set != NULL)
7194  {
7195  if (ref->owner == NULL)
7196  {
7197  or_put_set (buf, set, 1);
7198  }
7199  else
7200  {
7201 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7202  pin = ws_pin (ref->owner, 1);
7203 #endif
7204  size = or_packed_set_length (set, 1);
7205  /* remember the Windows pointer problem ! */
7206  if (((ptrdiff_t) (buf->endptr - buf->ptr)) < (ptrdiff_t) size)
7207  {
7208  /* unpin the owner before we abort ! */
7209 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7210  (void) ws_pin (ref->owner, pin);
7211 #endif
7212  return or_overflow (buf);
7213  }
7214  else
7215  {
7216  /* the buffer is ok, do the transformation */
7217  or_put_set (buf, set, 1);
7218  }
7219 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
7220  (void) ws_pin (ref->owner, pin);
7221 #endif
7222  }
7223  }
7224  }
7225  }
7226  return rc;
7227 }
7228 
7229 static void
7230 mr_data_readmem_set (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
7231 {
7232  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
7233  SETOBJ *set;
7234 
7235  if (mem == NULL)
7236  {
7237  if (size >= 0)
7238  {
7239  or_advance (buf, size);
7240  }
7241  else
7242  {
7243  set = or_get_set (buf, domain);
7244  if (set != NULL)
7245  {
7246  setobj_free (set);
7247  }
7248  }
7249  }
7250  else
7251  {
7252  if (!size)
7253  {
7254  *mem = NULL;
7255  }
7256  else
7257  {
7258  set = or_get_set (buf, domain);
7259  if (set != NULL)
7260  {
7261  *mem = set;
7262  }
7263  else
7264  {
7265  or_abort (buf);
7266  }
7267  }
7268  }
7269 }
7270 
7271 static int
7272 mr_data_readval_set (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
7273  int copy_buf_len)
7274 {
7275  SETOBJ *set;
7276  SETREF *ref;
7277  int rc = NO_ERROR;
7278 
7279  if (value == NULL)
7280  {
7281  if (size == -1)
7282  {
7283  /* don't know the true size, must unpack the set and throw it away */
7284  set = or_get_set (buf, domain);
7285  if (set != NULL)
7286  {
7287  setobj_free (set);
7288  }
7289  else
7290  {
7291  or_abort (buf);
7292  return ER_FAILED;
7293  }
7294  }
7295  else
7296  {
7297  if (size)
7298  {
7299  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
7300  }
7301  }
7302  }
7303  else
7304  {
7305  /* In some cases, like VOBJ reading, the domain passed is NULL here so be careful when initializing the value.
7306  * If it is NULL, it will be read when the set is unpacked. */
7307  if (!domain)
7308  {
7309  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_SET, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
7310  }
7311  else
7312  {
7313  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), domain->precision, domain->scale);
7314  }
7315 
7316  /* If size is zero, we have nothing to do, if size is -1, just go ahead and unpack the set. */
7317  if (!size)
7318  {
7319  db_make_set (value, NULL);
7320  }
7321  else if (copy)
7322  {
7323  set = or_get_set (buf, domain);
7324  if (set == NULL)
7325  {
7326  or_abort (buf);
7327  return ER_FAILED;
7328  }
7329  else
7330  {
7331  ref = setobj_get_reference (set);
7332  if (ref == NULL)
7333  {
7334  or_abort (buf);
7335  return ER_FAILED;
7336  }
7337  else
7338  {
7339  switch (set_get_type (ref))
7340  {
7341  case DB_TYPE_SET:
7342  db_make_set (value, ref);
7343  break;
7344  case DB_TYPE_MULTISET:
7345  db_make_multiset (value, ref);
7346  break;
7347  case DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
7348  db_make_sequence (value, ref);
7349  break;
7350  default:
7351  break;
7352  }
7353  }
7354  }
7355  }
7356  else
7357  {
7358  /* copy == false, which means don't translate it into memory rep */
7359  ref = set_make_reference ();
7360  if (ref == NULL)
7361  {
7362  or_abort (buf);
7363  return ER_FAILED;
7364  }
7365  else
7366  {
7367  int disk_size;
7368  DB_TYPE set_type;
7369 
7370  if (size != -1)
7371  {
7372  char *set_st;
7373  int num_elements, has_domain, bound_bits, offset_tbl, el_tags;
7374 
7375  disk_size = size;
7376 
7377  /* unfortunately, we still need to look at the header to find out the set type. */
7378  set_st = buf->ptr;
7379  or_get_set_header (buf, &set_type, &num_elements, &has_domain, &bound_bits, &offset_tbl, &el_tags,
7380  NULL);
7381 
7382  /* reset the OR_BUF */
7383  buf->ptr = set_st;
7384  }
7385  else
7386  {
7387  /* we have to go figure the size out */
7388  disk_size = or_disk_set_size (buf, domain, &set_type);
7389  }
7390 
7391  /* Record the pointer to the disk bits */
7392  ref->disk_set = buf->ptr;
7393  ref->need_clear = false;
7394  ref->disk_size = disk_size;
7395  ref->disk_domain = domain;
7396 
7397  /* advance the buffer as if we had read the set */
7398  rc = or_advance (buf, disk_size);
7399 
7400  switch (set_type)
7401  {
7402  case DB_TYPE_SET:
7403  db_make_set (value, ref);
7404  break;
7405  case DB_TYPE_MULTISET:
7406  db_make_multiset (value, ref);
7407  break;
7408  case DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
7409  db_make_sequence (value, ref);
7410  break;
7411  default:
7412  break;
7413  }
7414  }
7415  }
7416  }
7417  return rc;
7418 }
7419 
7420 static void
7421 mr_freemem_set (void *memptr)
7422 {
7423  /* since we aren't explicitly setting the set to NULL, we must set up the reference structures so they will get the
7424  * new set when it is brought back in, this is the only primitive type for which the free function is semantically
7425  * different than using the setmem function with a NULL value */
7426 
7427  SETOBJ **mem = (SETOBJ **) memptr;
7428 
7429  if (*mem != NULL)
7430  {
7431  setobj_free (*mem); /* free storage, NULL references */
7432  }
7433 }

7435 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
7436 mr_data_cmpdisk_set (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
7437 {
7438  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
7439  SETOBJ *set1 = NULL, *set2 = NULL;
7440 
7441  assert (domain != NULL);
7442 
7443  /* is not index type */
7444  assert (!domain->is_desc && !tp_valid_indextype (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain)));
7445 
7446  mem1 = or_unpack_set ((char *) mem1, &set1, domain);
7447  mem2 = or_unpack_set ((char *) mem2, &set2, domain);
7448 
7449  if (set1 == NULL || set2 == NULL)
7450  {
7451  return DB_UNK;
7452  }
7453 
7454  c = setobj_compare_order (set1, set2, do_coercion, total_order);
7455 
7456  setobj_free (set1);
7457  setobj_free (set2);
7458 
7459  return c;
7460 }

7463 mr_cmpval_set (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp, int collation)

7505  }
7506  /* NOTE: assumes that ownership info will already have been set or will be set by the caller */
7507

7615 static int
7616 mr_setval_midxkey (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
7617 {
7618  int error = NO_ERROR;
7619  int src_precision;
7620 
7621  DB_MIDXKEY dst_idx;
7622  DB_MIDXKEY *src_idx;
7623 
7624  if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
7625  {
7626  return db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0);
7627  }
7628 
7629  /* Get information from the value. */
7630  src_idx = db_get_midxkey (src);
7631  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
7632  if (src_idx == NULL)
7633  {
7634  return db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, src_precision, 0);
7635  }
7636 
7637  if (src_idx->size < 0)
7638  {
7639  dst_idx.size = strlen (src_idx->buf);
7640  }
7641  else
7642  {
7643  dst_idx.size = src_idx->size;
7644  }
7645 
7646  dst_idx.ncolumns = src_idx->ncolumns;
7647 
7648  dst_idx.domain = src_idx->domain;
7649 
7650  dst_idx.min_max_val.position = src_idx->min_max_val.position;
7651  dst_idx.min_max_val.type = src_idx->min_max_val.type;
7652 
7653  /* should we be paying attention to this? it is extremely dangerous */
7654  if (!copy)
7655  {
7656  dst_idx.buf = src_idx->buf;
7657 
7658  error = db_make_midxkey (dest, &dst_idx);
7659  dest->need_clear = false;
7660  }
7661  else
7662  {
7663  dst_idx.buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, dst_idx.size);
7664  if (dst_idx.buf == NULL)
7665  {
7666  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, src_precision, 0);
7667 
7668  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7669  return er_errid ();
7670  }
7671 
7672  memcpy (dst_idx.buf, src_idx->buf, dst_idx.size);
7673  error = db_make_midxkey (dest, &dst_idx);
7674  dest->need_clear = true;
7675  }
7676 
7677  return error;
7678 }

7704 mr_data_readval_midxkey (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
7705  int copy_buf_len)
7706 {
7707  return mr_index_readval_midxkey (buf, value, domain, size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len);
7708 }
7709 
7710 static int
7711 mr_index_readval_midxkey (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
7712  int copy_buf_len)
7713 {
7714  char *new_;
7715  DB_MIDXKEY midxkey;
7716  int rc = NO_ERROR;
7717  TP_DOMAIN *dom;
7718 
7719  if (size == -1)
7720  { /* unknown size */
7721  size = mr_index_lengthmem_midxkey (buf->ptr, domain);
7722  }
7723 
7724  if (size <= 0)
7725  {
7726  assert (false);
7727  return ER_FAILED;
7728  }
7729 
7730  if (value == NULL)
7731  {
7732  return or_advance (buf, size);
7733  }
7734 
7735  midxkey.size = size;
7736  midxkey.ncolumns = 0;
7737  midxkey.domain = domain;
7738  midxkey.min_max_val.position = -1;
7739  midxkey.min_max_val.type = MIN_COLUMN;
7740 
7741  for (dom = domain->setdomain; dom; dom = dom->next)
7742  {
7743  midxkey.ncolumns += 1;
7744  }
7745 
7746  if (!copy)
7747  {
7748  midxkey.buf = buf->ptr;
7749  db_make_midxkey (value, &midxkey);
7750  value->need_clear = false;
7751  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
7752  }
7753  else
7754  {
7755  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= size)
7756  {
7757  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
7758  new_ = copy_buf;
7759  }
7760  else
7761  {
7762  /*
7763  * Allocate storage for the string
7764  * do not include the kludge NULL terminator
7765  */
7766  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, size);
7767  }
7768 
7769  if (new_ == NULL)
7770  {
7771  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
7772  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
7773  or_abort (buf);
7774  return ER_FAILED;
7775  }
7776  else
7777  {
7778  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, size);
7779  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
7780  {
7781  /* round up to a word boundary */
7782  /* rc = or_get_align32 (buf); *//* need ?? */
7783  }
7784  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
7785  {
7786  if (new_ != copy_buf)
7787  {
7788  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
7789  }
7790  return rc;
7791  }
7792  midxkey.buf = new_;
7793  db_make_midxkey (value, &midxkey);
7794  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
7795  }
7796  }
7797 
7798  return rc;
7799 }
7800 
7801 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
7802 pr_midxkey_compare_element (char *mem1, char *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * dom1, TP_DOMAIN * dom2, int do_coercion,
7803  int total_order)
7804 {
7805  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
7806  DB_VALUE val1, val2;
7807  bool error = false;
7808  OR_BUF buf_val1, buf_val2;
7809  bool comparable = true;
7810 
7811  if (dom1->is_desc != dom2->is_desc)
7812  {
7813  assert (false);
7814  return DB_UNK; /* impossible case */
7815  }
7816 
7817  OR_BUF_INIT (buf_val1, mem1, -1);
7818  OR_BUF_INIT (buf_val2, mem2, -1);
7819 
7820  db_make_null (&val1);
7821  db_make_null (&val2);
7822 
7823  if ((*(dom1->type->index_readval)) (&buf_val1, &val1, dom1, -1, false, NULL, 0) != NO_ERROR)
7824  {
7825  error = true;
7826  goto clean_up;
7827  }
7828 
7829  if ((*(dom2->type->index_readval)) (&buf_val2, &val2, dom2, -1, false, NULL, 0) != NO_ERROR)
7830  {
7831  error = true;
7832  goto clean_up;
7833  }
7834 
7835  c = tp_value_compare_with_error (&val1, &val2, do_coercion, total_order, &comparable);
7836 
7837 clean_up:
7838  if (DB_NEED_CLEAR (&val1))
7839  {
7840  pr_clear_value (&val1);
7841  }
7842 
7843  if (DB_NEED_CLEAR (&val2))
7844  {
7845  pr_clear_value (&val2);
7846  }
7847 
7848  if (!comparable || error == true)
7849  {
7850  return DB_UNK;
7851  }
7852 
7853  return c;
7854 }
7855 
7856 
7857 DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
7858 pr_midxkey_compare (DB_MIDXKEY * mul1, DB_MIDXKEY * mul2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int num_index_term,
7859  int *start_colp, int *result_size1, int *result_size2, int *diff_column, bool * dom_is_desc,
7860  bool * next_dom_is_desc)
7861 {
7862  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
7863  int i;
7864  int adv_size1, adv_size2;
7865  int size1, size2;
7866  TP_DOMAIN *dom1, *dom2;
7867  char *bitptr1, *bitptr2;
7868  char *mem1, *mem2;
7869  int last;
7870 
7871  assert (total_order == 1);
7872  if (total_order == 0)
7873  {
7874  /* unknown case */
7875  return DB_UNK;
7876  }
7877 
7878  assert (mul1->domain != NULL);
7879  assert (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (mul1->domain) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
7880  assert (mul1->domain->setdomain != NULL);
7881 
7882  assert (mul2->domain != NULL);
7883  assert (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (mul2->domain) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
7884  assert (mul2->domain->setdomain != NULL);
7885 
7886  assert (mul1->ncolumns == mul2->ncolumns);
7887  assert (mul1->domain->precision == mul2->domain->precision);
7888 
7889  /* safe guard */
7890  if (mul1->domain == NULL || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (mul1->domain) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY || mul1->domain->setdomain == NULL)
7891  {
7892  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_MR_NULL_DOMAIN, 0);
7893  return DB_UNK;
7894  }
7895 
7896  /* safe guard */
7897  if (mul2->domain == NULL || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (mul2->domain) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY || mul2->domain->setdomain == NULL)
7898  {
7899  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_MR_NULL_DOMAIN, 0);
7900  return DB_UNK;
7901  }
7902 
7903  /* safe guard */
7904  if (mul1->ncolumns != mul2->ncolumns || mul1->domain->precision != mul2->domain->precision)
7905  {
7906  return DB_UNK;
7907  }
7908 
7909 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
7910  {
7911  int dom_ncols = 0; /* init */
7912 
7913  for (dom1 = mul1->domain->setdomain; dom1; dom1 = dom1->next)
7914  {
7915  dom_ncols++;
7916  }
7917 
7918  if (dom_ncols <= 0)
7919  {
7920  assert (false);
7921  return DB_UNK;
7922  }
7923 
7924  assert (dom_ncols == mul1->domain->precision);
7925  }
7926 #endif /* NDEBUG */
7927 
7928  size1 = size2 = 0;
7929 
7930  mem1 = bitptr1 = mul1->buf;
7931  mem2 = bitptr2 = mul2->buf;
7932 
7933  adv_size1 = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (mul1->domain->precision);
7934 
7935  mem1 += adv_size1;
7936  mem2 += adv_size1;
7937  size1 += adv_size1;
7938  size2 += adv_size1;
7939 
7940  dom1 = mul1->domain->setdomain;
7941  dom2 = mul2->domain->setdomain;
7942 
7943  if (num_index_term > 0)
7944  {
7945  last = num_index_term;
7946  }
7947  else
7948  {
7949  last = mul1->ncolumns;
7950  }
7951 
7952  for (i = 0; start_colp && i < *start_colp; i++, dom1 = dom1->next, dom2 = dom2->next)
7953  {
7954  if (dom1 == NULL || dom2 == NULL || dom1->is_desc != dom2->is_desc)
7955  {
7956  assert (false);
7957  return DB_UNK;
7958  }
7959 
7960  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr1, i))
7961  {
7962  adv_size1 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem1, dom1);
7963  mem1 += adv_size1;
7964  size1 += adv_size1;
7965  }
7966 
7967  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr2, i))
7968  {
7969  adv_size2 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem2, dom2);
7970  mem2 += adv_size2;
7971  size2 += adv_size2;
7972  }
7973  }
7974 
7975  for (c = DB_EQ; i < last; i++, dom1 = dom1->next, dom2 = dom2->next)
7976  {
7977  if (dom1 == NULL || dom2 == NULL || dom1->is_desc != dom2->is_desc)
7978  {
7979  assert (false);
7980  return DB_UNK;
7981  }
7982 
7983  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr1, i) && OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr2, i))
7984  {
7985  /* check for val1 and val2 same domain */
7986  if (dom1 == dom2 || tp_domain_match (dom1, dom2, TP_EXACT_MATCH))
7987  {
7988  c = (*(dom1->type->index_cmpdisk)) (mem1, mem2, dom1, do_coercion, total_order, NULL);
7989  }
7990  else
7991  { /* coercion and comparison */
7992  /* val1 and val2 have different domain */
7993  c = pr_midxkey_compare_element (mem1, mem2, dom1, dom2, do_coercion, total_order);
7994  }
7995  }
7996  else
7997  {
7998  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr1, i))
7999  {
8000  /* val 1 bound, val 2 unbound */
8001  if (mul2->min_max_val.position == i)
8002  {
8003  /* safeguard */
8004  assert (mul2->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN || mul2->min_max_val.type == MAX_COLUMN);
8005  if (mul2->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN)
8006  {
8007  c = DB_GT;
8008  }
8009  else
8010  {
8011  c = DB_LT;
8012  }
8013  }
8014  else
8015  {
8016  c = DB_GT;
8017  }
8018  }
8019  else if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr2, i))
8020  {
8021  /* val 1 unbound, val 2 bound */
8022  if (mul1->min_max_val.position == i)
8023  {
8024  /* safeguard */
8025  assert (mul1->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN || mul1->min_max_val.type == MAX_COLUMN);
8026  if (mul1->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN)
8027  {
8028  c = DB_LT;
8029  }
8030  else
8031  {
8032  c = DB_GT;
8033  }
8034  }
8035  else
8036  {
8037  c = DB_LT;
8038  }
8039  }
8040  else
8041  {
8042  /* val 1 unbound, val 2 unbound */
8043  /* SPECIAL_COLUMN_MIN > NULL */
8044  if (mul1->min_max_val.position == i)
8045  {
8046  if (mul2->min_max_val.position == i)
8047  {
8048  MIN_MAX_COLUMN_TYPE type1 = mul1->min_max_val.type;
8049  MIN_MAX_COLUMN_TYPE type2 = mul2->min_max_val.type;
8050  if (type1 == type2)
8051  {
8052  c = DB_EQ;
8053  }
8054  else if (type1 == MIN_COLUMN)
8055  {
8056  c = DB_LT;
8057  }
8058  else
8059  {
8060  c = DB_GT;
8061  }
8062  }
8063  else
8064  {
8065  assert (mul1->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN || mul1->min_max_val.type == MAX_COLUMN);
8066  if (mul1->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN)
8067  {
8068  c = DB_LT;
8069  }
8070  else
8071  {
8072  c = DB_GT;
8073  }
8074  }
8075  }
8076  else if (mul2->min_max_val.position == i)
8077  {
8078  assert (mul2->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN || mul2->min_max_val.type == MAX_COLUMN);
8079  if (mul2->min_max_val.type == MIN_COLUMN)
8080  {
8081  c = DB_GT;
8082  }
8083  else
8084  {
8085  c = DB_LT;
8086  }
8087  }
8088  else
8089  {
8090  c = DB_EQ;
8091  }
8092  }
8093  }
8094 
8095  if (c != DB_EQ)
8096  {
8097  break; /* exit for-loop */
8098  }
8099 
8100  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr1, i))
8101  {
8102  adv_size1 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem1, dom1);
8103  mem1 += adv_size1;
8104  size1 += adv_size1;
8105  }
8106 
8107  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr2, i))
8108  {
8109  adv_size2 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem2, dom2);
8110  mem2 += adv_size2;
8111  size2 += adv_size2;
8112  }
8113  }
8114 
8115  if (start_colp != NULL)
8116  {
8117  if (c != DB_EQ)
8118  {
8119  /* save the start position of non-equal-value column */
8120  *start_colp = i;
8121  }
8122  }
8123 
8124  adv_size1 = adv_size2 = 0;
8125  if (c != DB_EQ)
8126  {
8127  if (dom1 != NULL && OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr1, i))
8128  {
8129  adv_size1 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem1, dom1);
8130  }
8131 
8132  if (dom2 != NULL && OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (bitptr2, i))
8133  {
8134  adv_size2 = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem2, dom2);
8135  }
8136  }
8137 
8138  *result_size1 = size1 + adv_size1;
8139  *result_size2 = size2 + adv_size2;
8140 
8141  *diff_column = i;
8142 
8143  *dom_is_desc = *next_dom_is_desc = false;
8144 
8145  if (dom1)
8146  {
8147  if (dom1->is_desc)
8148  {
8149  *dom_is_desc = true;
8150  }
8151 
8152  if (dom1->next && dom1->next->is_desc)
8153  {
8154  *next_dom_is_desc = true;
8155  }
8156  }
8157 
8158  return c;
8159 }
8160 
8161 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8162 mr_cmpval_midxkey (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
8163  int collation)
8164 {
8165  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
8166  DB_MIDXKEY *midxkey1;
8167  DB_MIDXKEY *midxkey2;
8168  int dummy_size1, dummy_size2, dummy_diff_column;
8169  bool dummy_dom_is_desc, dummy_next_dom_is_desc;
8170 
8171  midxkey1 = db_get_midxkey (value1);
8172  midxkey2 = db_get_midxkey (value2);
8173 
8174  if (midxkey1 == NULL || midxkey2 == NULL)
8175  {
8176  assert_release (false); /* error */
8177  return DB_UNK;
8178  }
8179 
8180  if (midxkey1 == midxkey2)
8181  {
8182  if (total_order)
8183  {
8184  return DB_EQ;
8185  }
8186 
8187  assert_release (false); /* error */
8188  return DB_UNK;
8189  }
8190 
8191  assert_release (midxkey1->domain != NULL);
8192  assert_release (midxkey1->domain->precision == midxkey1->ncolumns);
8193  assert_release (midxkey2->domain != NULL);
8194  assert_release (midxkey2->domain->precision == midxkey2->ncolumns);
8195 
8196  c = (DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT) pr_midxkey_compare (midxkey1, midxkey2, do_coercion, total_order, -1, start_colp,
8197  &dummy_size1, &dummy_size2, &dummy_diff_column, &dummy_dom_is_desc,
8198  &dummy_next_dom_is_desc);
8199 
8200  assert_release (c == DB_UNK || (DB_LT <= c && c <= DB_GT));
8201 
8202  return c;
8203 }
8204 
8205 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8206 mr_data_cmpdisk_midxkey (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
8207 {
8208  assert (false);
8209 
8210  assert (domain != NULL);
8211 
8212  return mr_index_cmpdisk_midxkey (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp);
8213 }
8214 
8215 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8216 mr_index_cmpdisk_midxkey (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
8217 {
8218  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
8219  DB_MIDXKEY midxkey1;
8220  DB_MIDXKEY midxkey2;
8221  TP_DOMAIN *cmp_dom;
8222  int n_atts = 0;
8223  int dummy_size1, dummy_size2, dummy_diff_column;
8224  bool dummy_dom_is_desc = false, dummy_next_dom_is_desc;
8225 
8226  assert (false);
8227 
8228  assert (domain != NULL && !domain->is_desc);
8229 
8230  assert (mem1 != NULL);
8231  assert (mem2 != NULL);
8232 
8233  if (mem1 == NULL || mem2 == NULL)
8234  {
8235  assert (false); /* error */
8236  return DB_UNK;
8237  }
8238 
8239  if (mem1 == mem2)
8240  {
8241  if (total_order)
8242  {
8243  return DB_EQ;
8244  }
8245 
8246  assert (false); /* error */
8247  return DB_UNK;
8248  }
8249 
8250  midxkey1.buf = (char *) mem1;
8251  midxkey2.buf = (char *) mem2;
8252 
8253  n_atts = 0;
8254  for (cmp_dom = domain->setdomain; cmp_dom; cmp_dom = cmp_dom->next)
8255  {
8256  n_atts++;
8257  }
8258 
8259  midxkey1.size = midxkey2.size = -1; /* is dummy */
8260  midxkey1.ncolumns = midxkey2.ncolumns = n_atts;
8261  midxkey1.domain = midxkey2.domain = domain;
8262 
8263  c = pr_midxkey_compare (&midxkey1, &midxkey2, do_coercion, total_order, -1, start_colp, &dummy_size1, &dummy_size2,
8264  &dummy_diff_column, &dummy_dom_is_desc, &dummy_next_dom_is_desc);
8265  assert (c == DB_UNK || (DB_LT <= c && c <= DB_GT));
8266 
8267  return c;
8268 }

8270 static int
8271 mr_data_lengthmem_midxkey (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
8272 {
8273  return mr_index_lengthmem_midxkey (memptr, domain);
8274 }
8275 
8276 static int
8277 mr_index_lengthmem_midxkey (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
8278 {
8279  char *buf, *bitptr;
8280  TP_DOMAIN *dom;
8281  int idx_ncols = 0, i, adv_size;
8282  int len;
8283 
8284  /* There is no difference between the disk & memory sizes. */
8285  buf = (char *) memptr;
8286 
8287  idx_ncols = domain->precision;
8288  if (idx_ncols <= 0)
8289  {
8290  assert (false);
8291  goto exit_on_error; /* give up */
8292  }
8293 
8294 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
8295  {
8296  int dom_ncols = 0;
8297  for (dom = domain->setdomain; dom; dom = dom->next)
8298  {
8299  dom_ncols++;
8300  }
8301 
8302  if (dom_ncols <= 0)
8303  {
8304  assert (false);
8305  goto exit_on_error;
8306  }
8307  assert (dom_ncols == idx_ncols);
8308  }
8309 #endif /* NDEBUG */
8310 
8311  adv_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (idx_ncols);
8312 
8313  bitptr = buf;
8314  buf += adv_size;
8315  assert (CAST_BUFLEN (buf - bitptr) > 0);
8316 
8317  for (i = 0, dom = domain->setdomain; i < idx_ncols; i++, dom = dom->next)
8318  {
8319  /* check for val is NULL */
8320  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr, i))
8321  {
8322  continue; /* zero size; go ahead */
8323  }
8324 
8325  /* at here, val is non-NULL */
8326 
8327  adv_size = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (buf, dom);
8328  buf += adv_size;
8329  }
8330 
8331  /* set buf size */
8332  len = CAST_BUFLEN (buf - bitptr);
8333 
8334 exit_on_end:
8335 
8336  return len;
8337 
8338 exit_on_error:
8339 
8340  len = -1; /* set error */
8341  goto exit_on_end;
8342 }
8343 
8344 static int
8345 mr_data_lengthval_midxkey (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
8346 {
8347  return mr_index_lengthval_midxkey (value);
8348 }

8350 static int
8351 mr_index_lengthval_midxkey (DB_VALUE * value)
8352 {
8353  int len;
8354 
8355  if (DB_IS_NULL (value))
8356  {
8357  return 0;
8358  }
8359  len = value->data.midxkey.size;
8360 
8361  return len;
8362 }

8437 /*
8438  * TYPE NUMERIC
8439  */
8440 
8441 static void
8442 mr_initmem_numeric (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
8443 {
8444  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
8445 
8446  memset (memptr, 0, MR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision));
8447 }
8448 
8449 /*
8450  * Due to the "within tolerance" domain comparison used during attribute
8451  * assignment validation, we may receive a numeric whose precision is less
8452  * then the actual precision of the attribute. In that case we should be doing
8453  * an on-the-fly coercion here.
8454  */
8455 static int
8456 mr_setmem_numeric (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
8457 {
8458  int error = NO_ERROR;
8459  int src_precision, src_scale, byte_size;
8460  DB_C_NUMERIC num, src_num;
8461 
8462  if (value == NULL)
8463  {
8464  mr_initmem_numeric (mem, domain);
8465  }
8466  else
8467  {
8468  src_num = db_get_numeric (value);
8469 
8470  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
8471  src_scale = db_value_scale (value);
8472 
8473  /* this should have been handled by now */
8474  if (src_num == NULL || src_precision != domain->precision || src_scale != domain->scale)
8475  {
8476  error = ER_OBJ_DOMAIN_CONFLICT;
8477  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "");
8478  }
8479  else
8480  {
8481  num = (DB_C_NUMERIC) mem;
8482  byte_size = MR_NUMERIC_SIZE (src_precision);
8483  memcpy (num, src_num, byte_size);
8484  }
8485  }
8486  return error;
8487 }
8488 
8489 static int
8490 mr_getmem_numeric (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
8491 {
8492  int error = NO_ERROR;
8493  DB_C_NUMERIC num;
8494 
8495  if (value == NULL)
8496  {
8497  return error;
8498  }
8499 
8500  num = (DB_C_NUMERIC) mem;
8501  error = db_make_numeric (value, num, domain->precision, domain->scale);
8502  value->need_clear = false;
8503 
8504  return error;
8505 }
8506 
8507 static void
8508 mr_data_writemem_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
8509 {
8510  int disk_size;
8511 
8512  disk_size = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8513  or_put_data (buf, (char *) mem, disk_size);
8514 }
8515 
8516 static void
8517 mr_data_readmem_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
8518 {
8519  /* if stored size is unknown, the domain precision must be set correctly */
8520  if (size < 0)
8521  {
8522  size = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8523  }
8524 
8525  if (mem == NULL)
8526  {
8527  if (size)
8528  {
8529  or_advance (buf, size);
8530  }
8531  }
8532  else if (size)
8533  {
8534  if (size != OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision))
8535  {
8536  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
8537  or_abort (buf);
8538  }
8539  else
8540  {
8541  or_get_data (buf, (char *) mem, size);
8542  }
8543  }
8544 }
8545 
8546 static int
8547 mr_index_lengthmem_numeric (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
8548 {
8549  return mr_data_lengthmem_numeric (mem, domain, 1);
8550 }
8551 
8552 static int
8553 mr_data_lengthmem_numeric (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
8554 {
8555  int len;
8556 
8557  /* think about caching this in the domain so we don't have to calculate it */
8558  if (disk)
8559  {
8560  len = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8561  }
8562  else
8563  {
8564  len = MR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8565  }
8566 
8567  return len;
8568 }

8570 static void
8571 mr_initval_numeric (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)
8572 {
8573  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, precision, scale);
8574 }
8575 
8576 static int
8577 mr_setval_numeric (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
8578 {
8579  int error = NO_ERROR;
8580  int src_precision, src_scale;
8581  DB_C_NUMERIC src_numeric;
8582 
8583  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
8584  if (src == NULL || DB_IS_NULL (src))
8585  {
8586  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
8587  }
8588  else
8589  {
8590  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
8591  src_scale = db_value_scale (src);
8592  src_numeric = (DB_C_NUMERIC) db_get_numeric (src);
8593 
8594  if (DB_IS_NULL (src) || src_numeric == NULL)
8595  {
8596  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, src_precision, src_scale);
8597  }
8598  else
8599  {
8600  /*
8601  * Because numerics are stored in an inline buffer, there is no
8602  * difference between the copy and non-copy operations, this may
8603  * need to change.
8604  */
8605  error = db_make_numeric (dest, src_numeric, src_precision, src_scale);
8606  }
8607  }
8608  return error;
8609 }
