8611 static int
8612 mr_index_lengthval_numeric (DB_VALUE * value)
8613 {
8614  return mr_data_lengthval_numeric (value, 1);
8615 }
8616 
8617 static int
8618 mr_data_lengthval_numeric (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
8619 {
8620  int precision, len;
8621 
8622  len = 0;
8623  if (value != NULL)
8624  {
8625  /* better have a non-NULL value by the time writeval is called ! */
8626  precision = db_value_precision (value);
8627  if (disk)
8628  {
8629  len = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (precision);
8630  }
8631  else
8632  {
8633  len = MR_NUMERIC_SIZE (precision);
8634  }
8635  }
8636  return len;
8637 }

8639 static int
8640 mr_index_writeval_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
8641 {
8642  return mr_data_writeval_numeric (buf, value);
8643 }
8644 
8645 static int
8646 mr_data_writeval_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
8647 {
8648  DB_C_NUMERIC numeric;
8649  int precision, disk_size;
8650  int rc = NO_ERROR;
8651 
8652  if (value != NULL)
8653  {
8654  numeric = db_get_numeric (value);
8655  if (numeric != NULL)
8656  {
8657  precision = db_value_precision (value);
8658  disk_size = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (precision);
8659  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) numeric, disk_size);
8660  }
8661  }
8662  return rc;
8663 }

8665 static int
8666 mr_index_readval_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
8667  int copy_buf_len)
8668 {
8669  return mr_data_readval_numeric (buf, value, domain, size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len);
8670 }
8671 
8672 static int
8673 mr_data_readval_numeric (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
8674  int copy_buf_len)
8675 {
8676  int rc = NO_ERROR;
8677 
8678  if (domain == NULL)
8679  {
8680  return ER_FAILED;
8681  }
8682 
8683  /*
8684  * If size is -1, the caller doesn't know the size and we must determine
8685  * it from the domain.
8686  */
8687  if (size == -1)
8688  {
8689  size = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8690  }
8691 
8692  if (size == 1)
8693  {
8694  size = OR_NUMERIC_SIZE (domain->precision);
8695  }
8696 
8697  if (value == NULL)
8698  {
8699  if (size)
8700  {
8701  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
8702  }
8703  }
8704  else
8705  {
8706  /*
8707  * the copy and no copy cases are identical because db_make_numeric
8708  * will copy the bits into its internal buffer.
8709  */
8710  (void) db_make_numeric (value, (DB_C_NUMERIC) buf->ptr, domain->precision, domain->scale);
8711  value->need_clear = false;
8712  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
8713  }
8714 
8715  return rc;
8716 }
8717 
8718 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8719 mr_index_cmpdisk_numeric (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
8720 {
8721  assert (domain != NULL);
8722 
8723  return mr_data_cmpdisk_numeric (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp);
8724 }
8725 
8726 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8727 mr_data_cmpdisk_numeric (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
8728 {
8729  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
8730  OR_BUF buf;
8731  DB_VALUE value1, value2;
8732  DB_VALUE answer;
8733  int rc = NO_ERROR;
8734 
8735  assert (domain != NULL);
8736 
8737  or_init (&buf, (char *) mem1, 0);
8738  rc = mr_data_readval_numeric (&buf, &value1, domain, -1, 0, NULL, 0);
8739  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
8740  {
8741  return DB_UNK;
8742  }
8743 
8744  or_init (&buf, (char *) mem2, 0);
8745  rc = mr_data_readval_numeric (&buf, &value2, domain, -1, 0, NULL, 0);
8746  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
8747  {
8748  return DB_UNK;
8749  }
8750 
8751  rc = numeric_db_value_compare (&value1, &value2, &answer);
8752  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
8753  {
8754  return DB_UNK;
8755  }
8756 
8757  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (db_get_int (&answer));
8758 
8759  return c;
8760 }
8761 
8762 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
8763 mr_cmpval_numeric (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
8764  int collation)
8765 {
8766  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
8767  DB_VALUE answer;
8768 
8769  if (numeric_db_value_compare (value1, value2, &answer) != NO_ERROR)
8770  {
8771  return DB_UNK;
8772  }
8773 
8774  if (db_get_int (&answer) < 0)
8775  {
8776  c = DB_LT;
8777  }
8778  else
8779  {
8780  if (db_get_int (&answer) > 0)
8781  {
8782  c = DB_GT;
8783  }
8784  else
8785  {
8786  c = DB_EQ;
8787  }
8788  }
8789 
8790  return c;
8791 }

8798 
8799 /*
8800  * pr_init_ordered_mem_sizes - orders the sizes of primitive types in
8801  * descending order.
8802  * return: void
8803  */
8804 static void
8805 pr_init_ordered_mem_sizes (void)
8806 {
8807  int t, last_size, cur_size;
8808 
8809  pr_ordered_mem_size_total = 0;
8810 
8811  last_size = 500;
8812  while (1)
8813  {
8814  cur_size = -1;
8815  for (t = 0; t < PR_TYPE_TOTAL; ++t)
8816  {
8817  if (tp_Type_id_map[t]->size > cur_size && tp_Type_id_map[t]->size < last_size)
8818  {
8819  cur_size = tp_Type_id_map[t]->size;
8820  }
8821  }
8822  pr_ordered_mem_sizes[pr_ordered_mem_size_total++] = last_size = cur_size;
8823  if (cur_size <= 0)
8824  {
8825  break;
8826  }
8827  }
8828 }

8831 /*
8832  * pr_type_from_id - maps a type identifier such as DB_TYPE_INTEGER into its
8833  * corresponding primitive type descriptor structures.
8834  * return: type descriptor
8835  * id(in): type identifier constant
8836  */
8837 PR_TYPE *
8838 pr_type_from_id (DB_TYPE id)
8839 {
8840  PR_TYPE *type = NULL;
8841 
8842  if (id <= DB_TYPE_LAST && id != DB_TYPE_TABLE)
8843  {
8844  type = tp_Type_id_map[(int) id];
8845  }
8846 
8847  return type;
8848 }

8852  * pr_type_name - Returns the string type name associated with a type constant.

8855  * Note:
8856  * The string must not be freed after use.

8858 const char *
8859 pr_type_name (DB_TYPE id)

8872 }

8874 /*
8875  * pr_is_set_type - Test to see if a type identifier is one of the set types.

8878  * Note:

8888 /*
8889  * pr_is_string_type - Test to see if a type identifier is one of the string
8890  * types.

8892  * type(in): type to check

8894 int
8895 pr_is_string_type (DB_TYPE type)
8896 {
8897  int status = 0;
8898 
8899  if (type == DB_TYPE_VARCHAR || type == DB_TYPE_CHAR || type == DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR || type == DB_TYPE_NCHAR
8900  || type == DB_TYPE_VARBIT || type == DB_TYPE_BIT)
8901  {
8902  status = 1;
8903  }
8904 
8905  return status;
8906 }

8909  * pr_is_prefix_key_type -
8910  * types.

8920 /*
8921  * pr_is_variable_type - determine whether or not a type is fixed or variable
8922  * width on disk.
8923  * return: non-zero if this is a variable width type
8924  * id(in): type id
8925  * Note:
8926  * With the advent of parameterized types like CHAR(n), NUMERIC(p,s) etc.
8927  * this doesn't mean that all values of this type will be the same size,
8928  * it means that for any particular attribute of a class, they will all be
8929  * the same size and the value will be stored in the "fixed" region of the
8930  * disk representation.
8931  */
8932 int
8933 pr_is_variable_type (DB_TYPE id)
8934 {
8935  PR_TYPE *type;
8936  int is_variable = 0;
8937 
8938  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (id);
8939  if (type != NULL)
8940  {
8941  is_variable = type->variable_p;
8942  }
8943 
8944  return is_variable;
8945 }
8946 
8947 /*
8948  * pr_find_type - Locate a type descriptor given a name.
8949  * return: type structure
8950  * name(in): type name
8951  * Note:
8952  * Called by the schema manager to map a domain name into a primitive
8953  * type.
8954  * This now recognizes some alias names for a few of the types.
8955  * The aliases should be more centrally defined so the parser can
8956  * check for them.
8957  *
8958  */
8959 PR_TYPE *
8960 pr_find_type (const char *name)
8961 {
8962  PR_TYPE *type, *found;
8963  int i;
8964 
8965  if (name == NULL)
8966  {
8967  return NULL;
8968  }
8969 
8970  found = NULL;
8971  for (i = DB_TYPE_FIRST; i <= DB_TYPE_LAST && found == NULL; i++)
8972  {
8973  type = tp_Type_id_map[i];
8974  if (type->name != NULL)
8975  {
8976  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, type->name) == 0)
8977  {
8978  found = type;
8979  }
8980  }
8981  }
8982 
8983  /* alias kludge */
8984  if (found == NULL)
8985  {
8986  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "int") == 0)
8987  {
8988  found = tp_Type_integer;
8989  }
8990  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "multi_set") == 0)
8991  {
8992  found = tp_Type_multiset;
8993  }
8994 
8995  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "short") == 0)
8996  {
8997  found = tp_Type_short;
8998  }
8999 
9000  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "string") == 0)
9001  {
9002  found = tp_Type_string;
9003  }
9004  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "utime") == 0)
9005  {
9006  found = tp_Type_utime;
9007  }
9008 
9009  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "list") == 0)
9010  {
9011  found = tp_Type_sequence;
9012  }
9013  }
9014 
9015  return found;
9016 }

9024 /*
9025  * pr_mem_size - Determine the number of bytes required for the memory
9026  * representation of a particular type.
9027  * return: memory size of type
9028  * type(in): PR_TYPE structure
9029  * Note:
9030  * This only determines the size for an attribute value in contiguous
9031  * memory storage for an instance.
9032  * It does not include the size of any reference memory (like strings.
9033  * For strings, it returns the size of the pointer NOT the length
9034  * of the string.
9035  *
9036  */
9037 int
9038 pr_mem_size (PR_TYPE * type)
9039 {
9040  return type->size;
9041 }
9042 
9043 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
9044 /*
9045  * pr_disk_size - Determine the number of bytes of disk storage required for
9046  * a value.
9047  * return: disk size of an instance attribute
9048  * type(in): type identifier
9049  * mem(in): pointer to memory for value
9050  * Note:
9051  * The value must be in instance memory format, NOT DB_VALUE format.
9052  * If you have a DB_VALUE, use pr_value_disk_size.
9053  * This is called by the transformer when calculating sizes and offset
9054  * tables for instances.
9055  */
9056 int
9057 pr_disk_size (PR_TYPE * type, void *mem)
9058 {
9059  int size;
9060 
9061  if (type->lengthmem != NULL)
9062  {
9063  size = (*type->lengthmem) (mem, NULL, 1);
9064  }
9065  else
9066  {
9067  size = type->disksize;
9068  }
9069  return size;
9070 }
9071 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

9073 /*
9074  * pr_total_mem_size - returns the total amount of storage used for a memory
9075  * attribute including any external allocatons (for strings etc.).
9076  * return: total memory size of type
9077  * type(in): type identifier
9078  * mem(in): pointer to memory for value
9079  * Note:
9080  * The length function is not defined to accept a DB_VALUE so
9081  * this had better be in memory format!
9082  * Called by sm_object_size to calculate total size for an object.
9083  *
9084  */
9085 int
9086 pr_total_mem_size (PR_TYPE * type, void *mem)

9091  {
9092  size = (*type->data_lengthmem) (mem, NULL, 0);
9093  }
9094  else
9095  {
9096  size = type->size;
9097  }
9098

9100 }

9102 /*

9107  * be used at attribute values as well.
9108  *

9120 /*
9121  * pr_value_mem_size - Returns the amount of storage necessary to hold the
9122  * contents of a DB_VALUE.
9123  * return: byte size used by contents of DB_VALUE
9124  * value(in): value to examine
9125  * Note:
9126  * Does not include the amount of space necessary for the DB_VALUE.
9127  * Used by some statistics modules that calculate memory sizes of strucures.
9128  */
9129 int
9130 pr_value_mem_size (DB_VALUE * value)
9131 {
9132  PR_TYPE *type;
9133  int size;
9134  DB_TYPE dbval_type;
9135

9137  dbval_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
9138  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (dbval_type);
9139  if (type != NULL)
9140  {
9141  if (type->data_lengthval != NULL)
9142  {
9143  size = (*type->data_lengthval) (value, 0);
9144  }
9145  else
9146  {
9147  size = type->size;
9148  }
9149  }
9150 
9151  return size;
9152 }

9154 /*
9155  * pr_midxkey_element_disk_size - returns the number of bytes that will be
9156  * written by the "index_write" type function for this memory buffer.
9157  * return: byte size of disk representation
9158  * mem(in): memory buffer
9159  * domain(in): type domain
9160  */
9161 int
9162 pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (char *mem, DB_DOMAIN * domain)
9163 {
9164  int disk_size = 0;
9165 
9166  /*
9167  * variable types except VARCHAR, VARNCHAR, and VARBIT
9168  * cannot be a member of midxkey
9169  */
9170  assert (!(domain->type->variable_p && !QSTR_IS_VARIABLE_LENGTH (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain))));
9171 
9172  if (domain->type->index_lengthmem != NULL)
9173  {
9174  disk_size = (*(domain->type->index_lengthmem)) (mem, domain);
9175  }
9176  else
9177  {
9178  assert (!domain->type->variable_p);
9179 
9180  disk_size = domain->type->disksize;
9181  }
9182 
9183  return disk_size;
9184 }

9186 /*
9187  * pr_midxkey_get_vals_size() -
9188  * return: int
9189  * domains(in) :
9190  * dbvals(in) :
9191  * total(in) :
9192  *
9193  */
9194 
9195 static int
9196 pr_midxkey_get_vals_size (TP_DOMAIN * domains, DB_VALUE * dbvals, int total)
9197 {
9198  TP_DOMAIN *dom;
9199  int i;
9200 
9201  for (dom = domains, i = 0; dom; dom = dom->next, i++)
9202  {
9203  if (DB_IS_NULL (&dbvals[i]))
9204  {
9205  continue;
9206  }
9207 
9208  total += pr_index_writeval_disk_size (&dbvals[i]);
9209  }
9210 
9211  return total;
9212 }

9214 
9215 /*
9216  * pr_midxkey_get_element_offset - Returns element offset of midxkey
9217  * return:
9218  * midxkey(in):
9219  * index(in):
9220  */
9221 int
9222 pr_midxkey_get_element_offset (const DB_MIDXKEY * midxkey, int index)
9223 {
9224  int idx_ncols = 0, i;
9225  int advance_size;
9226  int error = NO_ERROR;
9227 
9228  TP_DOMAIN *domain;
9229 
9230  OR_BUF buf_space;
9231  OR_BUF *buf;
9232  char *bitptr;
9233 
9234  idx_ncols = midxkey->domain->precision;
9235  if (idx_ncols <= 0)
9236  {
9237  assert (false);
9238  goto exit_on_error;
9239  }
9240 
9241  if (index >= midxkey->ncolumns)
9242  {
9243  assert (false);
9244  goto exit_on_error;
9245  }
9246 
9247  /* get bit-mask */
9248  bitptr = midxkey->buf;
9249  /* get domain list, attr number */
9250  domain = midxkey->domain->setdomain; /* first element's domain */
9251 
9252  buf = &buf_space;
9253  or_init (buf, midxkey->buf, midxkey->size);
9254 
9255  advance_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (idx_ncols);
9256  if (or_advance (buf, advance_size) != NO_ERROR)
9257  {
9258  goto exit_on_error;
9259  }
9260 
9261  for (i = 0; i < index; i++, domain = domain->next)
9262  {
9263  /* check for element is NULL */
9264  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr, i))
9265  {
9266  continue; /* skip and go ahead */
9267  }
9268 
9269  advance_size = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (buf->ptr, domain);
9270  or_advance (buf, advance_size);
9271  }
9272 
9273  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9274  {
9275  goto exit_on_error;
9276  }
9277 
9278  return CAST_BUFLEN (buf->ptr - buf->buffer);
9279 
9280 exit_on_error:
9281 
9282  assert (false);
9283  return -1;
9284 }
9285 
9286 /*
9287  * pr_midxkey_add_prefix -
9288  *
9289  * return:
9290  * prefix(in):
9291  * postfix(in):
9292  * result(out):
9293  * n_prefix(in):
9294  */
9295 int
9296 pr_midxkey_add_prefix (DB_VALUE * result, DB_VALUE * prefix, DB_VALUE * postfix, int n_prefix)
9297 {
9298  int i, offset_postfix, offset_prefix;
9299  DB_MIDXKEY *midx_postfix, *midx_prefix;
9300  DB_MIDXKEY midx_result;
9301 
9302  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (prefix) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
9303  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (postfix) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
9304 
9305  midx_prefix = db_get_midxkey (prefix);
9306  midx_postfix = db_get_midxkey (postfix);
9307 
9308  offset_prefix = pr_midxkey_get_element_offset (midx_prefix, n_prefix);
9309  offset_postfix = pr_midxkey_get_element_offset (midx_postfix, n_prefix);
9310 
9311  midx_result.size = offset_prefix + (midx_postfix->size - offset_postfix);
9312  midx_result.buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, midx_result.size);
9313  midx_result.domain = midx_postfix->domain;
9314  midx_result.ncolumns = midx_postfix->ncolumns;
9315 
9316  memcpy (midx_result.buf, midx_prefix->buf, offset_prefix);
9317 
9318 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
9319  for (i = 0; i < n_prefix; i++)
9320  {
9321  assert (!OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (midx_postfix->buf, i));
9322  }
9323 #endif
9324 
9325  for (i = n_prefix; i < midx_result.ncolumns; i++)
9326  {
9327  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_BOUND (midx_postfix->buf, i))
9328  {
9329  OR_MULTI_ENABLE_BOUND_BIT (midx_result.buf, i);
9330  }
9331  else
9332  {
9333  OR_MULTI_CLEAR_BOUND_BIT (midx_result.buf, i);
9334  }
9335  }
9336 
9337  memcpy (midx_result.buf + offset_prefix, midx_postfix->buf + offset_postfix, midx_postfix->size - offset_postfix);
9338 
9339  midx_result.min_max_val.position = -1;
9340  midx_result.min_max_val.type = MIN_COLUMN;
9341  db_make_midxkey (result, &midx_result);
9342  result->need_clear = true;
9343 
9344  return NO_ERROR;
9345 }
9346 
9347 /*
9348  * pr_midxkey_remove_prefix -
9349  *
9350  * return:
9351  * key(in):
9352  * prefix(in):
9353  */
9354 int
9355 pr_midxkey_remove_prefix (DB_VALUE * key, int prefix)
9356 {
9357  DB_MIDXKEY *midx_key;
9358  int i, start, offset;
9359 
9360  midx_key = db_get_midxkey (key);
9361 
9362  start = pr_midxkey_get_element_offset (midx_key, 0);
9363  offset = pr_midxkey_get_element_offset (midx_key, prefix);
9364 
9365  memmove (midx_key->buf + start, midx_key->buf + offset, midx_key->size - offset);
9366 
9367  for (i = 0; i < prefix; i++)
9368  {
9369  OR_MULTI_CLEAR_BOUND_BIT (midx_key->buf, i);
9370  }
9371 
9372  midx_key->size = midx_key->size - offset + start;
9373 
9374  return NO_ERROR;
9375 }

9377 /*
9378  * pr_midxkey_common_prefix -
9379  *
9380  * return:
9381  * key1(in):
9382  * key2(in):
9383  */
9384 int
9385 pr_midxkey_common_prefix (DB_VALUE * key1, DB_VALUE * key2)
9386 {
9387  int size1, size2, diff_column, ret;
9388  bool dom_is_desc = false, next_dom_is_desc = false;
9389  DB_MIDXKEY *midx_lf_key, *midx_uf_key;
9390 
9391  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (key1) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
9392  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (key2) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
9393 
9394  diff_column = 0; /* init */
9395 
9396  midx_lf_key = db_get_midxkey (key1);
9397  midx_uf_key = db_get_midxkey (key2);
9398 
9399  ret = pr_midxkey_compare (midx_lf_key, midx_uf_key, 0, 1, -1, NULL, &size1, &size2, &diff_column, &dom_is_desc,
9400  &next_dom_is_desc);
9401 
9402  if (ret == DB_UNK)
9403  {
9404  assert (false);
9405  diff_column = 0;
9406  }
9407 
9408  return diff_column;
9409 }
9410 
9411 /*
9412  * pr_midxkey_get_element_internal()
9413  * return:
9414  * midxkey(in) :
9415  * index(in) :
9416  * value(in) :
9417  * copy(in) :
9418  * prev_indexp(in) :
9419  * prev_ptrp(in) :
9420  */
9421 
9422 static int
9423 pr_midxkey_get_element_internal (const DB_MIDXKEY * midxkey, int index, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy, int *prev_indexp,
9424  char **prev_ptrp)
9425 {
9426  int idx_ncols = 0, i;
9427  int advance_size;
9428  int error = NO_ERROR;
9429 
9430  TP_DOMAIN *domain;
9431 
9432  OR_BUF buf_space;
9433  OR_BUF *buf;
9434  char *bitptr;
9435 
9436  idx_ncols = midxkey->domain->precision;
9437  if (idx_ncols <= 0)
9438  {
9439  assert (false);
9440  goto exit_on_error;
9441  }
9442 
9443  if (index >= midxkey->ncolumns)
9444  {
9445  assert (false);
9446  goto exit_on_error;
9447  }
9448 
9449 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
9450  {
9451  int dom_ncols = 0;
9452 
9453  for (domain = midxkey->domain->setdomain; domain; domain = domain->next)
9454  {
9455  dom_ncols++;
9456  }
9457 
9458  if (dom_ncols <= 0)
9459  {
9460  assert (false);
9461  goto exit_on_error;
9462  }
9463  assert (dom_ncols == idx_ncols);
9464  }
9465 #endif /* NDEBUG */
9466 
9467  /* get bit-mask */
9468  bitptr = midxkey->buf;
9469  /* get domain list, attr number */
9470  domain = midxkey->domain->setdomain; /* first element's domain */
9471 
9472  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr, index))
9473  {
9474  db_make_null (value);
9475  }
9476  else
9477  {
9478  buf = NULL; /* init */
9479  i = 0; /* init */
9480 
9481  /* 1st phase: check for prev info */
9482  if (prev_indexp && prev_ptrp)
9483  {
9484  int j, offset;
9485 
9486  j = *prev_indexp;
9487  offset = CAST_BUFLEN (*prev_ptrp - midxkey->buf);
9488  if (j <= 0 || j > index || offset <= 0)
9489  { /* invalid info */
9490  /* nop */
9491  }
9492  else
9493  {
9494  buf = &buf_space;
9495  or_init (buf, *prev_ptrp, midxkey->size - offset);
9496 
9497  /* consume prev domain */
9498  for (; i < j; i++)
9499  {
9500  domain = domain->next;
9501  }
9502  }
9503  }
9504 
9505  /* 2nd phase: need to set buf info */
9506  if (buf == NULL)
9507  {
9508  buf = &buf_space;
9509  or_init (buf, midxkey->buf, midxkey->size);
9510 
9511  advance_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (idx_ncols);
9512  if (or_advance (buf, advance_size) != NO_ERROR)
9513  {
9514  goto exit_on_error;
9515  }
9516  }
9517 
9518  for (; i < index; i++, domain = domain->next)
9519  {
9520  /* check for element is NULL */
9521  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr, i))
9522  {
9523  continue; /* skip and go ahead */
9524  }
9525 
9526  advance_size = pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (buf->ptr, domain);
9527  or_advance (buf, advance_size);
9528  }
9529 
9530  error = (*(domain->type->index_readval)) (buf, value, domain, -1, copy, NULL, 0);
9531  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9532  {
9533  goto exit_on_error;
9534  }
9535 
9536  /* save the next index info */
9537  if (prev_indexp && prev_ptrp)
9538  {
9539  *prev_indexp = index + 1;
9540  *prev_ptrp = buf->ptr;
9541  }
9542  }
9543 
9544 exit_on_end:
9545 
9546  return error;
9547 
9548 exit_on_error:
9549 
9550  if (error == NO_ERROR)
9551  {
9552  error = -1; /* set error */
9553  }
9554 
9555  goto exit_on_end;
9556 }
9557 
9558 /*
9559  * pr_midxkey_unique_prefix () -
9560  * return: NO_ERROR or error code.
9561  *
9562  * db_midxkey1(in) : Left side of compare.
9563  * db_midxkey2(in) : Right side of compare.
9564  * db_result(out) : midxkey such that > midxkey1, and <= midxkey2.
9565  * or < midxkey1, and >= midxkey2 (desc)
9566  *
9567  * Note:
9568  *
9569  */
9570 int
9571 pr_midxkey_unique_prefix (const DB_VALUE * db_midxkey1, const DB_VALUE * db_midxkey2, DB_VALUE * db_result)
9572 {
9573  int c = DB_UNK;
9574  int i;
9575  int size1, size2, diff_column;
9576  int result_size = 0;
9577  char *result_buf;
9578  DB_MIDXKEY *midxkey1, *midxkey2;
9579  DB_MIDXKEY result_midxkey;
9580  bool dom_is_desc = false, next_dom_is_desc = false;
9581 
9582  /* Assertions */
9583  assert (db_midxkey1 != (DB_VALUE *) NULL);
9584  assert (db_midxkey2 != (DB_VALUE *) NULL);
9585  assert (db_result != (DB_VALUE *) NULL);
9586 
9587  midxkey1 = db_get_midxkey (db_midxkey1);
9588  midxkey2 = db_get_midxkey (db_midxkey2);
9589 
9590  assert (midxkey1->size != -1);
9591  assert (midxkey2->size != -1);
9592  assert (midxkey1->ncolumns == midxkey2->ncolumns);
9593  assert (midxkey1->domain == midxkey2->domain);
9594  assert (midxkey1->domain->setdomain == midxkey2->domain->setdomain);
9595 
9596  c = pr_midxkey_compare (midxkey1, midxkey2, 0, 1, -1, NULL, &size1, &size2, &diff_column, &dom_is_desc,
9597  &next_dom_is_desc);
9598  if (dom_is_desc)
9599  {
9600  c = ((c == DB_GT) ? DB_LT : (c == DB_LT) ? DB_GT : c);
9601  }
9602 
9603  assert (c == DB_LT);
9604  if (c != DB_LT)
9605  {
9606  return (er_errid () == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : er_errid ();
9607  }
9608 
9609  if (size1 == midxkey1->size || size2 == midxkey2->size
9610  || OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (midxkey1->buf, diff_column + 1)
9611  || OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (midxkey2->buf, diff_column + 1))
9612  {
9613  /* not found separator: give up */
9614  pr_clone_value (db_midxkey2, db_result);
9615  }
9616  else
9617  {
9618  assert (size1 < midxkey1->size);
9619  assert (size2 < midxkey2->size);
9620 
9621  if (!next_dom_is_desc)
9622  {
9623  result_buf = midxkey2->buf;
9624  result_size = size2;
9625  }
9626  else
9627  {
9628  result_buf = midxkey1->buf;
9629  result_size = size1;
9630  }
9631 
9632  result_midxkey.buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, result_size);
9633  if (result_midxkey.buf == NULL)
9634  {
9635  /* will already be set by memory mgr */
9636  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9637  return er_errid ();
9638  }
9639 
9640  (void) memcpy (result_midxkey.buf, result_buf, result_size);
9641  result_midxkey.size = result_size;
9642  result_midxkey.domain = midxkey2->domain;
9643  result_midxkey.ncolumns = midxkey2->ncolumns;
9644  for (i = diff_column + 1; i < result_midxkey.ncolumns; i++)
9645  {
9646  OR_MULTI_CLEAR_BOUND_BIT (result_midxkey.buf, i);
9647  }
9648 
9649  result_midxkey.min_max_val.position = -1;
9650  result_midxkey.min_max_val.type = MIN_COLUMN;
9651  db_make_midxkey (db_result, &result_midxkey);
9652 
9653  db_result->need_clear = true;
9654 
9655 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
9656  /* midxkey1 < result_midxkey */
9657  c = pr_midxkey_compare (midxkey1, &result_midxkey, 0, 1, -1, NULL, &size1, &size2, &diff_column, &dom_is_desc,
9658  &next_dom_is_desc);
9659  assert (c == DB_UNK || (DB_LT <= c && c <= DB_GT));
9660  if (dom_is_desc)
9661  {
9662  c = ((c == DB_GT) ? DB_LT : (c == DB_LT) ? DB_GT : c);
9663  }
9664  assert (c == DB_LT);
9665 
9666  /* result_midxkey <= midxkey2 */
9667  c = pr_midxkey_compare (&result_midxkey, midxkey2, 0, 1, -1, NULL, &size1, &size2, &diff_column, &dom_is_desc,
9668  &next_dom_is_desc);
9669  assert (c == DB_UNK || (DB_LT <= c && c <= DB_GT));
9670  if (dom_is_desc)
9671  {
9672  c = ((c == DB_GT) ? DB_LT : (c == DB_LT) ? DB_GT : c);
9673  }
9674 
9675  assert (c == DB_LT || c == DB_EQ);
9676 #endif
9677  }
9678 
9679  return NO_ERROR;
9680 }
9681 
9682 /*
9683  * pr_midxkey_get_element_nocopy() -
9684  * return: error code
9685  * midxkey(in) :
9686  * index(in) :
9687  * value(in) :
9688  * prev_indexp(in) :
9689  * prev_ptrp(in) :
9690  */
9691 
9692 int
9693 pr_midxkey_get_element_nocopy (const DB_MIDXKEY * midxkey, int index, DB_VALUE * value, int *prev_indexp,
9694  char **prev_ptrp)
9695 {
9696  return pr_midxkey_get_element_internal (midxkey, index, value, false /* not copy */ ,
9697  prev_indexp, prev_ptrp);
9698 }

9700 /*
9701  * pr_midxkey_init_boundbits() -
9702  * return: int
9703  * bufptr(in) :
9704  * n_atts(in) :
9705  *
9706  */
9707 
9708 int
9709 pr_midxkey_init_boundbits (char *bufptr, int n_atts)
9710 {
9711  unsigned char *bits;
9712  int i, nbytes;
9713 
9714  nbytes = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (n_atts);
9715  bits = (unsigned char *) bufptr;
9716 
9717  for (i = 0; i < nbytes; i++)
9718  {
9719  bits[i] = (unsigned char) 0;
9720  }
9721 
9722  return nbytes;
9723 }
9724 
9725 /*
9726  * pr_midxkey_add_elements() -
9727  * return:
9728  * keyval(in) :
9729  * dbvals(in) :
9730  * num_dbvals(in) :
9731  * dbvals_domain_list(in) :
9732  * domain(in) :
9733  */
9734 
9735 int
9736 pr_midxkey_add_elements (DB_VALUE * keyval, DB_VALUE * dbvals, int num_dbvals, TP_DOMAIN * dbvals_domain_list)
9737 {
9738  int i;
9739  TP_DOMAIN *dom;
9740  DB_MIDXKEY *midxkey;
9741  int total_size = 0;
9742  int bitmap_size = 0;
9743  char *new_IDXbuf;
9744  char *bound_bits;
9745  OR_BUF buf;
9746 
9747  /* phase 1: find old */
9748  midxkey = db_get_midxkey (keyval);
9749  if (midxkey == NULL)
9750  {
9751  return ER_FAILED;
9752  }
9753 
9754  if (midxkey->ncolumns > 0 && midxkey->size > 0)
9755  {
9756  /* bitmap is always fully sized */
9757  bitmap_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (midxkey->ncolumns);
9758  total_size = midxkey->size;
9759  }
9760  else
9761  {
9762  bitmap_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (num_dbvals);
9763  total_size = bitmap_size;
9764  }
9765 
9766  /* phase 2: calculate how many bytes need */
9767  total_size = pr_midxkey_get_vals_size (dbvals_domain_list, dbvals, total_size);
9768 
9769  /* phase 3: initialize new_IDXbuf */
9770  new_IDXbuf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, total_size);
9771  if (new_IDXbuf == NULL)
9772  {
9773  goto error;
9774  }
9775 
9776  or_init (&buf, new_IDXbuf, -1);
9777  bound_bits = buf.ptr;
9778 
9779  /* phase 4: copy new_IDXbuf from old */
9780  if (midxkey->ncolumns > 0 && midxkey->size > 0)
9781  {
9782  or_put_data (&buf, midxkey->buf, midxkey->size);
9783  }
9784  else
9785  {
9786  /* bound bits */
9787  (void) pr_midxkey_init_boundbits (bound_bits, bitmap_size);
9788  or_advance (&buf, bitmap_size);
9789  }
9790 
9791  for (i = 0, dom = dbvals_domain_list; i < num_dbvals; i++, dom = dom->next)
9792  {
9793  /* check for added val is NULL */
9794  if (DB_IS_NULL (&dbvals[i]))
9795  {
9796  continue; /* skip and go ahead */
9797  }
9798 
9799  (*((dom->type)->index_writeval)) (&buf, &dbvals[i]);
9800 
9801  OR_ENABLE_BOUND_BIT (bound_bits, midxkey->ncolumns + i);
9802  } /* for (i = 0, ...) */
9803 
9804  assert (total_size == CAST_BUFLEN (buf.ptr - buf.buffer));
9805 
9806  /* phase 5: make new multiIDX */
9807  if (midxkey->size > 0)
9808  {
9809  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, midxkey->buf);
9810  midxkey->buf = NULL;
9811  }
9812 
9813  midxkey->buf = buf.buffer;
9814  midxkey->size = CAST_BUFLEN (buf.ptr - buf.buffer);
9815  midxkey->ncolumns += num_dbvals;
9816 
9817  return NO_ERROR;
9818 
9819 error:
9820 
9821  if (midxkey->buf)
9822  {
9823  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, midxkey->buf);
9824  midxkey->buf = NULL;
9825  }
9826  return ER_FAILED;
9827 }
9828 
9829 /*
9830  * pr_data_writeval_disk_size - returns the number of bytes that will be
9831  * written by the "writeval" type function for this value.
9832  * return: byte size of disk representation
9833  * value(in): db value
9834  * Note:
9835  * It is generally used prior to writing the value to pre-calculate the
9836  * required size.
9837  * Formerly called pr_value_disk_size.
9838  *
9839  * Note that "writeval" is used for the construction of disk objects,
9840  * and it will leave space for fixed width types that are logically
9841  * NULL. If you need a compressed representation for random values,
9842  * look at the or_put_value family of functions.
9843  */
9844 int
9845 pr_data_writeval_disk_size (DB_VALUE * value)
9846 {
9847  PR_TYPE *type;
9848  DB_TYPE dbval_type;
9849 
9850  dbval_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
9851  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (dbval_type);
9852 
9853  assert (type != NULL);
9854 
9855  if (type)
9856  {
9857  if (type->data_lengthval == NULL)
9858  {
9859  return type->disksize;
9860  }
9861  else
9862  {
9863  return (*(type->data_lengthval)) (value, 1);
9864  }
9865  }
9866 
9867  return 0;
9868 }
9869 
9870 /*
9871  * pr_index_writeval_disk_size - returns the number of bytes that will be
9872  * written by the "index_write" type function for this value.
9873  * return: byte size of disk representation
9874  * value(in): db value
9875  * Note:
9876  */
9877 int
9878 pr_index_writeval_disk_size (DB_VALUE * value)
9879 {
9880  PR_TYPE *type;
9881  DB_TYPE dbval_type;
9882 
9883  dbval_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
9884  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (dbval_type);
9885 
9886  assert (type != NULL);
9887 
9888  if (type)
9889  {
9890  if (type->index_lengthval == NULL)
9891  {
9892  assert (!type->variable_p);
9893 
9894  return type->disksize;
9895  }
9896  else
9897  {
9898  return (*(type->index_lengthval)) (value);
9899  }
9900  }
9901 
9902  return 0;
9903 }
9904 
9905 void
9906 pr_data_writeval (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
9907 {

9913  if (type == NULL)
9914  {
9915  type = tp_Type_null; /* handle strange arguments with NULL */
9916  }
9917  (*(type->data_writeval)) (buf, value);
9918 }

9925 #if defined (SERVER_MODE) || defined (SA_MODE)
9926 /*
9927  * pr_valstring - Take the value and formats it using the sptrfunc member of
9928  * the pr_type vector for the appropriate type.
9929  * return: a freshly db_private_realloc()'ed string with a printed rep of "val" in it
9930  * val(in): some DB_VALUE
9931  * Note:
9932  * The caller is responsible for eventually freeing the memory using db_private_free()
9933  *
9934  * This is really just a debugging helper; it probably doesn't do enough
9935  * serious formatting for external use. Use it to get printed DB_VALUE
9936  * representations into error messages and the like.
9937  */
9938 char *
9939 pr_valstring (THREAD_ENTRY * threade, DB_VALUE * val)
9940 {
9941 /* *INDENT-OFF* */
9942  string_buffer sb {
9943  [&threade] (mem::block &block, size_t len)
9944  {
9945  block.ptr = (char *) db_private_realloc (threade, block.ptr, block.dim + len);
9946  block.dim += len;
9947  },
9948  [&threade] (mem::block &block)
9949  {
9950  db_private_free (threade, block.ptr);
9951  block = {};
9952  }
9953  };
9954 /* *INDENT-ON* */
9955 
9956  if (val == NULL)
9957  {
9958  /* space with terminating NULL */
9959  sb ("(null)");
9960  return sb.move_ptr ();
9961  }
9962 
9963  if (DB_IS_NULL (val))
9964  {
9965  /* space with terminating NULL */
9966  sb ("NULL");
9967  return sb.move_ptr ();
9968  }
9969 
9970  DB_TYPE dbval_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (val);
9971  PR_TYPE *pr_type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (dbval_type);
9972 
9973  if (pr_type == NULL)
9974  {
9975  return NULL;
9976  }
9977 
9978  (*(pr_type->sptrfunc)) (val, sb);
9979  return sb.move_ptr (); //caller should use db_private_free() to deallocate it
9980 }
9981 #endif //defined (SERVER_MODE) || defined (SA_MODE)
9982 
9983 /*
9984  * pr_complete_enum_value - Sets both index and string of a enum value in case
9985  * one of them is missing.
9986  * return: NO_ERROR or error code.
9987  * value(in/out): enumeration value.
9988  * domain(in): enumeration domain against which the value is checked.
9989  */
9990 int
9991 pr_complete_enum_value (DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
9992 {
9993  unsigned short short_val;
9994  char *str_val;
9995  int enum_count, str_val_size, idx;
9996  DB_ENUM_ELEMENT *db_elem = 0;
9997 
9998  if (value == NULL || domain == NULL || DB_IS_NULL (value))
9999  {
10000  return NO_ERROR;
10001  }
10002 
10003  if (value->domain.general_info.type != DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION || domain->type->id != DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
10004  {
10005  return ER_FAILED;
10006  }
10007 
10008  short_val = db_get_enum_short (value);
10009  str_val = db_get_enum_string (value);
10010  str_val_size = db_get_enum_string_size (value);
10011  enum_count = DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEMS_COUNT (domain);
10012  if (short_val > enum_count)
10013  {
10014  return ER_FAILED;
10015  }
10016 
10017  if (short_val > 0)
10018  {
10019  db_elem = &DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEM (domain, short_val);
10020  if (str_val != NULL && DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING_SIZE (db_elem) == str_val_size
10021  && !memcmp (str_val, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_elem), str_val_size))
10022  {
10023  db_make_enumeration (value, short_val, str_val, str_val_size, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_CODESET (db_elem),
10024  db_get_enum_collation (value));
10025  return NO_ERROR;
10026  }
10027  pr_clear_value (value);
10028 
10029  str_val_size = DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING_SIZE (db_elem);
10030  str_val = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str_val_size + 1);
10031  if (str_val == NULL)
10032  {
10033  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10034  }
10035  memcpy (str_val, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_elem), str_val_size);
10036  str_val[str_val_size] = 0;
10037  db_make_enumeration (value, short_val, str_val, str_val_size, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_CODESET (db_elem),
10038  db_get_enum_collation (value));
10039  value->need_clear = true;
10040 
10041  return NO_ERROR;
10042  }
10043  else if (str_val == NULL)
10044  {
10045  /* empty string enum value with index 0 */
10046  return NO_ERROR;
10047  }
10048 
10049  for (idx = 0; idx < enum_count; idx++)
10050  {
10051  db_elem = &DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEM (domain, idx + 1);
10052  if (DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING_SIZE (db_elem) == str_val_size
10053  && !memcmp (DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_elem), str_val, str_val_size))
10054  {
10055  db_make_enumeration (value, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_SHORT (db_elem), str_val, str_val_size,
10056  DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_CODESET (db_elem), db_get_enum_collation (value));
10057  break;
10058  }
10059  }
10060 
10061  return NO_ERROR;
10062 }

10200 
10201 
10202 /*
10203  * The main difference between "memory" strings and "value" strings is that
10204  * the length tag is stored as an in-line prefix in the memory block allocated
10205  * to hold the string characters.
10206  */
10207 static int
10208 mr_setmem_string (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
10209 {
10210  int error = NO_ERROR;
10211  char *src, *cur, *new_, **mem;
10212  int src_precision, src_length, new_length;
10213 
10214  /* get the current memory contents */
10215  mem = (char **) memptr;
10216  cur = *mem;
10217 
10218  if (value == NULL || (src = db_get_string (value)) == NULL)
10219  {
10220  /* remove the current value */
10221  if (cur != NULL)
10222  {
10223  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
10224  mr_initmem_string (memptr, domain);
10225  }
10226  }
10227  else
10228  {
10229  /*
10230  * Get information from the value. Ignore precision for the time being
10231  * since we really only care about the byte size of the value for varchar.
10232  * Whether or not the value "fits" should have been checked by now.
10233  */
10234  src_precision = DB_GET_STRING_PRECISION (value);
10235  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
10236 
10237  if (src_length < 0)
10238  {
10239  src_length = strlen (src);
10240  }
10241 
10242  /* Currently we NULL terminate the workspace string. Could try to do the single byte size hack like we have in
10243  * the disk representation. */
10244  new_length = src_length + sizeof (int) + 1;
10245  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, new_length);
10246  if (new_ == NULL)
10247  {
10248  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10249  error = er_errid ();
10250  }
10251  else
10252  {
10253  if (cur != NULL)
10254  {
10255  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
10256  }
10257 
10258  /* pack in the length prefix */
10259  *(int *) new_ = src_length;
10260  cur = new_ + sizeof (int);
10261  /* store the string */
10262  memcpy (cur, src, src_length);
10263  /* NULL terminate the stored string for safety */
10264  cur[src_length] = '\0';
10265  *mem = new_;
10266  }
10267  }
10268 
10269  return error;
10270 }
10271 
10272 static int
10273 mr_getmem_string (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
10274 {
10275  int error = NO_ERROR;
10276  int mem_length;
10277  char **mem, *cur, *new_;
10278 
10279  /* get to the current value */
10280  mem = (char **) memptr;
10281  cur = *mem;
10282 
10283  if (cur == NULL)
10284  {
10285  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, domain->precision, 0);
10286  value->need_clear = false;
10287  }
10288  else
10289  {
10290  /* extract the length prefix and the pointer to the actual string data */
10291  mem_length = *(int *) cur;
10292  cur += sizeof (int);
10293 
10294  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
10295  {
10296  assert (false);
10297  return ER_FAILED;
10298  }
10299 
10300  if (!copy)
10301  {
10302  db_make_varchar (value, domain->precision, cur, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
10303  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
10304  value->need_clear = false;
10305  }
10306  else
10307  {
10308  /* return it with a NULL terminator */
10309  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
10310  if (new_ == NULL)
10311  {
10312  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10313  error = er_errid ();
10314  }
10315  else
10316  {
10317  memcpy (new_, cur, mem_length);
10318  new_[mem_length] = '\0';
10319  db_make_varchar (value, domain->precision, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
10320  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
10321  value->need_clear = true;
10322  }
10323  }
10324  }
10325  return error;
10326 }
10327 
10328 
10329 /*
10330  * For the disk representation, we may be adding pad bytes to round up to a
10331  * word boundary.
10332  *
10333  * We are currently adding a NULL terminator to the disk representation
10334  * for some code on the server that still manufactures pointers directly into
10335  * the disk buffer and assumes it is a NULL terminated string. This terminator
10336  * can be removed after the server has been updated. The logic for maintaining
10337  * the terminator is actually in the or_put_varchar, family of functions.
10338  */
10339 static int
10340 mr_data_lengthmem_string (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
10341 {
10342  char **mem, *cur;
10343  int len;
10344 
10345  len = 0;
10346  if (!disk)
10347  {
10348  len = tp_String.size;
10349  }
10350  else if (memptr != NULL)
10351  {
10352  mem = (char **) memptr;
10353  cur = *mem;
10354  if (cur != NULL)
10355  {
10356  len = *(int *) cur;
10357  if (len >= OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
10358  {
10359  /* Skip the length of the string */
10360  len = pr_get_compression_length ((cur + sizeof (int)), len) + PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10361  len = or_packed_varchar_length (len) - PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10362  }
10363  else
10364  {
10365  len = or_packed_varchar_length (len);
10366  }
10367  }
10368  }
10369 
10370  return len;
10371 }
10372 
10373 static int
10374 mr_index_lengthmem_string (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
10375 {
10376  OR_BUF buf;
10377  int charlen;
10378  int rc = NO_ERROR, compressed_length = 0, decompressed_length = 0, length = 0;
10379 
10380  /* generally, index key-value is short enough */
10381  charlen = OR_GET_BYTE (memptr);
10382  if (charlen < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
10383  {
10384  return or_varchar_length (charlen);
10385  }
10386 
10387  assert (charlen == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
10388 
10389  or_init (&buf, (char *) memptr, -1);
10390 
10391  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (&buf, &compressed_length, &decompressed_length);
10392 
10393  if (compressed_length > 0)
10394  {
10395  charlen = compressed_length;
10396  }
10397  else
10398  {
10399  charlen = decompressed_length;
10400  }
10401  /* Temporary disk size in case the length of the current buffer is less than 255.
10402  * Therefore the or_varchar_length will always add the 8 bytes consisting the compressed_length
10403  * and decompressed_length stored in buffer.
10404  */
10405 
10406  charlen += PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10407 
10408  length = or_varchar_length (charlen);
10409 
10410  return length - PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10411 }
10412 
10413 static void
10414 mr_data_writemem_string (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
10415 {
10416  char **mem, *cur;
10417  int len;
10418 
10419  mem = (char **) memptr;
10420  cur = *mem;
10421  if (cur != NULL)
10422  {
10423  len = *(int *) cur;
10424  cur += sizeof (int);
10425  or_packed_put_varchar (buf, cur, len);
10426  }
10427 }
10428 
10429 
10430 /*
10431  * The amount of memory requested is currently calculated based on the
10432  * stored size prefix. If we ever go to a system where we avoid storing the
10433  * size, then we could use the size argument passed in to this function but
10434  * that may also include any padding byte that added to bring us up to a word
10435  * boundary.
10436  * Might want some way to determine which bytes at the end of a string are
10437  * padding.
10438  */
10439 static void
10440 mr_data_readmem_string (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
10441 {
10442  char **mem, *cur, *new_;
10443  int len;
10444  int mem_length, pad;
10445  char *start;
10446  int rc = NO_ERROR;
10447 
10448  /*
10449  * we must have an explicit size here as it can't be determined from the
10450  * domain
10451  */
10452  if (size < 0)
10453  {
10454  return;
10455  }
10456 
10457  if (memptr == NULL)
10458  {
10459  if (size)
10460  {
10461  or_advance (buf, size);
10462  }
10463  }
10464  else
10465  {
10466  mem = (char **) memptr;
10467  cur = *mem;
10468  /* should we be checking for existing strings ? */
10469 #if 0
10470  if (cur != NULL)
10471  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
10472 #endif
10473 
10474  new_ = NULL;
10475  if (size)
10476  {
10477  int compressed_size;
10478  start = buf->ptr;
10479 
10480  /* KLUDGE, we have some knowledge of how the thing is stored here in order have some control over the
10481  * conversion between the packed length prefix and the full word memory length prefix. Might want to put this
10482  * in another specialized or_ function. */
10483 
10484  /* Get just the length prefix. */
10485  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (buf, &compressed_size, &len);
10486  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10487  {
10488  or_abort (buf);
10489  return;
10490  }
10491 
10492  /*
10493  * Allocate storage for this string, including our own full word size
10494  * prefix and a NULL terminator.
10495  */
10496  mem_length = len + sizeof (int) + 1;
10497 
10498  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length);
10499  if (new_ == NULL)
10500  {
10501  or_abort (buf);
10502  }
10503  else
10504  {
10505  /* store the length in our memory prefix */
10506  *(int *) new_ = len;
10507  cur = new_ + sizeof (int);
10508 
10509  /* decompress buffer (this also writes nul terminator) */
10510  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (buf, cur, compressed_size, len);
10511  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10512  {
10513  db_private_free (NULL, new_);
10514  or_abort (buf);
10515  return;
10516  }
10517  /* align like or_get_varchar */
10518  or_get_align32 (buf);
10519  }
10520 
10521  /* If we were given a size, check to see if for some reason this is larger than the already word aligned
10522  * string that we have now extracted. This shouldn't be the case but since we've got a length, we may as
10523  * well obey it. */
10524  pad = size - (int) (buf->ptr - start);
10525  if (pad > 0)
10526  {
10527  or_advance (buf, pad);
10528  }
10529  }
10530  *mem = new_;
10531  }
10532 }
10533 
10534 static void
10535 mr_freemem_string (void *memptr)
10536 {
10537  char *cur;
10538 
10539  if (memptr != NULL)
10540  {
10541  cur = *(char **) memptr;
10542  if (cur != NULL)
10543  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
10544  }
10545 }

10547 static void
10548 mr_initval_string (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)
10549 {
10550  db_make_varchar (value, precision, NULL, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET, LANG_SYS_COLLATION);
10551  value->need_clear = false;
10552 }
10553 
10554 static int
10555 mr_setval_string (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
10556 {
10557  int error = NO_ERROR;
10558  int src_precision, src_length;
10559  char *src_str, *new_, *new_compressed_buf;
10560 
10561  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
10562  if (src == NULL || (DB_IS_NULL (src) && db_value_precision (src) == 0))
10563  {
10564  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0);
10565  }
10566  else if (DB_IS_NULL (src) || (src_str = db_get_string (src)) == NULL)
10567  {
10568  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, db_value_precision (src), 0);
10569  if (!DB_IS_NULL (src) && src->data.ch.info.is_max_string)
10570  {
10571  dest->data.ch.info.is_max_string = true;
10572  dest->domain.general_info.is_null = 0;
10573  dest->domain.char_info.collation_id = db_get_string_collation (src);
10574  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf = NULL;
10575  dest->data.ch.medium.codeset = db_get_string_codeset (src);
10576  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_size = DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE;
10577  dest->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear = false;
10578  }
10579  }
10580  else
10581  {
10582  /* Get information from the value. */
10583  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
10584  src_length = db_get_string_size (src);
10585  if (src_length < 0)
10586  src_length = strlen (src_str);
10587 
10588  assert (src->data.ch.info.is_max_string == false);
10589 
10590  /* should we be paying attention to this? it is extremely dangerous */
10591  if (!copy)
10592  {
10593  error =
10594  db_make_varchar (dest, src_precision, src_str, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
10595  db_get_string_collation (src));
10596  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf = src->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf;
10597  dest->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear = false;
10598  }
10599  else
10600  {
10601  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
10602  if (new_ == NULL)
10603  {
10604  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, src_precision, 0);
10605  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10606  error = er_errid ();
10607  }
10608  else
10609  {
10610  memcpy (new_, src_str, src_length);
10611  new_[src_length] = '\0';
10612  db_make_varchar (dest, src_precision, new_, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
10613  db_get_string_collation (src));
10614  dest->need_clear = true;
10615  }
10616 
10617  if (src->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf == NULL)
10618  {
10619  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf = NULL;
10620  dest->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear = false;
10621  }
10622  else
10623  {
10624  new_compressed_buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src->data.ch.medium.compressed_size + 1);
10625  if (new_compressed_buf == NULL)
10626  {
10627  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, src_precision, 0);
10628  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10629  error = er_errid ();
10630  }
10631  else
10632  {
10633  memcpy (new_compressed_buf, src->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf, src->data.ch.medium.compressed_size);
10634  new_compressed_buf[src->data.ch.medium.compressed_size] = '\0';
10635  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf = new_compressed_buf;
10636  dest->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear = true;
10637  }
10638  }
10639  }
10640 
10641  dest->data.ch.medium.compressed_size = src->data.ch.medium.compressed_size;
10642  }
10643 
10644  return error;
10645 }

10648 mr_index_lengthval_string (DB_VALUE * value)
10649 {
10650  return mr_lengthval_string_internal (value, 1, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);

10684 
10685 /*
10686  * Ignoring precision as byte size is really the only important thing for
10687  * varchar.
10688  */
10689 static int
10690 mr_lengthval_string_internal (DB_VALUE * value, int disk, int align)
10691 {
10692  int len;
10693  bool is_temporary_data = false;
10694  const char *str;
10695  int rc = NO_ERROR;
10696  int compressed_size = 0;
10697 
10698  if (DB_IS_NULL (value))
10699  {
10700  return 0;
10701  }
10702  str = value->data.ch.medium.buf;
10703  len = value->data.ch.medium.size;
10704  if (!str)
10705  {
10706  return 0;
10707  }
10708  if (len < 0)
10709  {
10710  len = strlen (str);
10711  }
10712 
10713  if (disk == 0)
10714  {
10715  return len;
10716  }
10717  else
10718  {
10719  /* Test and try compression. */
10720  if (!DB_TRIED_COMPRESSION (value))
10721  {
10722  /* It means that the value has never passed through a compression process. */
10723  rc = pr_do_db_value_string_compression (value);
10724  }
10725  /* We are now sure that the value has been through the process of compression */
10726  compressed_size = db_get_compressed_size (value);
10727 
10728  /* If the compression was successful, then we use the compression size value */
10729  if (compressed_size > 0)
10730  {
10731  len = compressed_size + PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10732  is_temporary_data = true;
10733  }
10734  else
10735  {
10736  /* Compression failed so we are using the uncompressed size */
10737  len = value->data.ch.medium.size;
10738  }
10739 
10740  if (len >= OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION && is_temporary_data == false)
10741  {
10742  /* The compression failed but the size of the string calls for the new encoding. */
10743  len += PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10744  is_temporary_data = true;
10745  }
10746 
10747  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
10748  {
10749  len = or_packed_varchar_length (len);
10750  }
10751  else
10752  {
10753  len = or_varchar_length (len);
10754  }
10755 
10756  if (is_temporary_data == true)
10757  {
10758  return len - PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
10759  }
10760  return len;
10761  }
10762 }
10763 
10764 
10765 /*
10766  * Ignoring precision as byte size is really the only important thing for
10767  * varchar.
10768  */
10769 static int
10770 mr_writeval_string_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
10771 {
10772  int src_length, compressed_size;
10773  char *str, *compressed_string;
10774  int rc = NO_ERROR;
10775  char *string;
10776  int size;
10777 
10778  if (value != NULL && (str = db_get_string (value)) != NULL)
10779  {
10780  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
10781  if (src_length < 0)
10782  {
10783  src_length = strlen (str);
10784  }
10785 
10786  /* Test for possible compression. */
10787  if (!DB_TRIED_COMPRESSION (value))
10788  {
10789  /* It means that the value has never passed through a compression process. */
10790  rc = pr_do_db_value_string_compression (value);
10791  }
10792 
10793  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10794  {
10795  return rc;
10796  }
10797 
10798  compressed_size = db_get_compressed_size (value);
10799  compressed_string = DB_GET_COMPRESSED_STRING (value);
10800 
10801  if (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE && src_length < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
10802  {
10803  rc = pr_write_uncompressed_string_to_buffer (buf, str, src_length, align);
10804  }
10805  else
10806  {
10807  /* String has been prompted to compression before. */
10808 
10809  if (compressed_string == NULL)
10810  {
10811  /* The value passed through a compression process but it failed due to its size. */
10812  assert (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE);
10813  string = value->data.ch.medium.buf;
10814  }
10815  else
10816  {
10817  /* Compression successful. */
10818  assert (compressed_size > 0);
10819  string = compressed_string;
10820  }
10821  if (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE)
10822  {
10823  size = 0;
10824  }
10825  else
10826  {
10827  size = compressed_size;
10828  }
10829  rc = pr_write_compressed_string_to_buffer (buf, string, size, src_length, align);
10830  }
10831  }
10832  return rc;
10833 }
10834 
10835 static int
10836 mr_readval_string_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
10837  int copy_buf_len, int align)
10838 {
10839  int pad, precision;
10840  char *new_ = NULL, *start = NULL;
10841  int str_length;
10842  int rc = NO_ERROR;
10843  int compressed_size = 0, decompressed_size = 0;
10844  char *decompressed_string = NULL, *string = NULL, *compressed_string = NULL;
10845  lzo_uint decompression_size = 0;
10846  bool compressed_need_clear = false;
10847 
10848  if (value == NULL)
10849  {
10850  if (size == -1)
10851  {
10852  rc = or_skip_varchar (buf, align);
10853  }
10854  else
10855  {
10856  if (size)
10857  {
10858  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
10859  }
10860  }
10861  }
10862  else
10863  {
10864  if (domain != NULL)
10865  {
10866  precision = domain->precision;
10867  }
10868  else
10869  {
10870  precision = DB_MAX_VARCHAR_PRECISION;
10871  }
10872 
10873  if (!copy)
10874  {
10875  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
10876  {
10877  assert (false);
10878  return ER_FAILED;
10879  }
10880  /* Get the compressed size and uncompressed size from the buffer, and point the buf->ptr
10881  * towards the data stored in the buffer */
10882  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (buf, &compressed_size, &decompressed_size);
10883  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10884  {
10885  return rc;
10886  }
10887 
10888  if (compressed_size > 0)
10889  {
10890  str_length = compressed_size;
10891 
10892  string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, decompressed_size + 1);
10893  if (string == NULL)
10894  {
10895  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
10896  decompressed_size * sizeof (char));
10897  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10898  goto cleanup;
10899  }
10900 
10901  start = buf->ptr;
10902 
10903  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (buf, string, compressed_size, decompressed_size);
10904  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10905  {
10906  goto cleanup;
10907  }
10908  string[decompressed_size] = '\0';
10909  db_make_varchar (value, precision, string, decompressed_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
10910  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
10911  value->need_clear = true;
10912 
10913  compressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, compressed_size + 1);
10914  if (compressed_string == NULL)
10915  {
10916  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
10917  (compressed_size + 1) * sizeof (char));
10918  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10919  goto cleanup;
10920  }
10921 
10922  memcpy (compressed_string, start, compressed_size);
10923  compressed_string[compressed_size] = '\0';
10924 
10925  db_set_compressed_string (value, compressed_string, compressed_size, true);
10926  }
10927  else
10928  {
10929  assert (compressed_size == 0);
10930 
10931  str_length = decompressed_size;
10932  db_make_varchar (value, precision, buf->ptr, decompressed_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
10933  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
10934  value->need_clear = false;
10935  db_set_compressed_string (value, NULL, DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE, false);
10936  }
10937 
10938  or_skip_varchar_remainder (buf, str_length, align);
10939  }
10940  else
10941  {
10942  if (size == 0)
10943  {
10944  /* its NULL */
10945  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, precision, 0);
10946  }
10947  else
10948  { /* size != 0 */
10949  if (size == -1)
10950  {
10951  /* Standard packed varchar with a size prefix */
10952  ; /* do nothing */
10953  }
10954  else
10955  { /* size != -1 */
10956  /* Standard packed varchar within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the disk
10957  * representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the additional
10958  * padding. */
10959  start = buf->ptr;
10960  } /* size != -1 */
10961 
10962  /* Get the length of the string, be it compressed or uncompressed. */
10963  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (buf, &compressed_size, &decompressed_size);
10964  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
10965  {
10966  return ER_FAILED;
10967  }
10968  if (compressed_size <= 0)
10969  {
10970  assert (compressed_size == 0);
10971  str_length = decompressed_size;
10972  }
10973  else
10974  {
10975  str_length = compressed_size;
10976  }
10977 
10978  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= str_length + 1)
10979  {
10980  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
10981  new_ = copy_buf;
10982  }
10983  else
10984  {
10985  /*
10986  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge
10987  * NULL terminator
10988  */
10989  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str_length + 1);
10990  }
10991 
10992  if (new_ == NULL)
10993  {
10994  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
10995  if (domain)
10996  {
10997  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
10998  }
10999  or_abort (buf);
11000  return ER_FAILED;
11001  }
11002  else
11003  {
11004  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
11005  {
11006  /* read the kludge NULL terminator */
11007  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, str_length + 1);
11008 
11009  /* round up to a word boundary */
11010  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
11011  {
11012  rc = or_get_align32 (buf);
11013  }
11014  }
11015  else
11016  {
11017  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, str_length);
11018  }
11019 
11020  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11021  {
11022  if (new_ != copy_buf)
11023  {
11024  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
11025  }
11026  return ER_FAILED;
11027  }
11028 
11029  /* Handle decompression if there was any */
11030  if (compressed_size > 0)
11031  {
11032  /* String was compressed */
11033  assert (decompressed_size > 0);
11034 
11035  decompression_size = 0;
11036 
11037  /* Handle decompression */
11038  decompressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, decompressed_size + 1);
11039  if (decompressed_string == NULL)
11040  {
11041  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
11042  (size_t) decompressed_size * sizeof (char));
11043  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
11044  goto cleanup;
11045  }
11046 
11047  /* decompressing the string */
11048  rc = lzo1x_decompress ((lzo_bytep) new_, (lzo_uint) compressed_size,
11049  (lzo_bytep) decompressed_string, &decompression_size, NULL);
11050  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
11051  {
11052  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL, 0);
11053  rc = ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL;
11054  goto cleanup;
11055  }
11056  if (decompression_size != (lzo_uint) decompressed_size)
11057  {
11058  /* Decompression failed. It shouldn't. */
11059  assert (false);
11060  }
11061 
11062  compressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, compressed_size + 1);
11063  if (compressed_string == NULL)
11064  {
11065  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
11066  (size_t) (compressed_size + 1) * sizeof (char));
11067  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
11068  goto cleanup;
11069  }
11070 
11071  memcpy (compressed_string, new_, compressed_size);
11072  compressed_string[compressed_size] = '\0';
11073  compressed_need_clear = true;
11074 
11075  if (new_ != copy_buf)
11076  {
11077  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
11078  }
11079 
11080  new_ = decompressed_string;
11081  str_length = decompressed_size;
11082  }
11083 
11084  new_[str_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
11085  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
11086  {
11087  rc = ER_FAILED;
11088  goto cleanup;
11089  }
11090 
11091  db_make_varchar (value, precision, new_, str_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
11092  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
11093  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
11094 
11095  if (compressed_string == NULL)
11096  {
11097  compressed_size = DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE;
11098  compressed_need_clear = false;
11099  }
11100 
11101  db_set_compressed_string (value, compressed_string, compressed_size, compressed_need_clear);
11102 
11103  if (size == -1)
11104  {
11105  /* Standard packed varchar with a size prefix */
11106  ; /* do nothing */
11107  }
11108  else
11109  { /* size != -1 */
11110  /* Standard packed varchar within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the
11111  * disk representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the
11112  * additional padding. */
11113  pad = size - (int) (buf->ptr - start);
11114  if (pad > 0)
11115  {
11116  rc = or_advance (buf, pad);
11117  }
11118  } /* size != -1 */
11119  } /* else */
11120  } /* size != 0 */
11121  }
11122  }
11123 
11124 cleanup:
11125  if (new_ != NULL && new_ != copy_buf && rc != NO_ERROR)
11126  {
11127  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
11128  }
11129 
11130  if (decompressed_string != NULL && rc != NO_ERROR)
11131  {
11132  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, decompressed_string);
11133  }
11134 
11135  if (rc != NO_ERROR && compressed_string != NULL)
11136  {
11137  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, compressed_string);
11138  }
11139 
11140  return rc;
11141 }
11142 
11143 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
11144 mr_index_cmpdisk_string (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
11145 {
11146  assert (domain != NULL);
11147 
11148  return mr_data_cmpdisk_string (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp);
11149 }
11150 
11151 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
11152 mr_data_cmpdisk_string (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
11153 {
11154  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
11155  char *str1, *str2;
11156  int str_length1, str1_compressed_length = 0, str1_decompressed_length = 0;
11157  int str_length2, str2_compressed_length = 0, str2_decompressed_length = 0;
11158  OR_BUF buf1, buf2;
11159  int rc = NO_ERROR;
11160  char *string1 = NULL, *string2 = NULL;
11161  bool alloced_string1 = false, alloced_string2 = false;
11162  int strc;
11163 
11164  assert (domain != NULL);
11165 
11166  str1 = (char *) mem1;
11167  str2 = (char *) mem2;
11168 
11169  /* generally, data is short enough */
11170  str_length1 = OR_GET_BYTE (str1);
11171  str_length2 = OR_GET_BYTE (str2);
11172  if (str_length1 < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION && str_length2 < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
11173  {
11174  str1 += OR_BYTE_SIZE;
11175  str2 += OR_BYTE_SIZE;
11176  strc =
11177  QSTR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) str1, str_length1, (unsigned char *) str2, str_length2);
11178  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
11179  return c;
11180  }
11181 
11182  assert (str_length1 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION
11183  || str_length2 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
11184 
11185  /* String 1 */
11186  or_init (&buf1, str1, 0);
11187  if (str_length1 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
11188  {
11189  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (&buf1, &str1_compressed_length, &str1_decompressed_length);
11190  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11191  {
11192  goto cleanup;
11193  }
11194 
11195  string1 = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str1_decompressed_length + 1);
11196  if (string1 == NULL)
11197  {
11198  /* Error report */
11199  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, str1_decompressed_length);
11200  goto cleanup;
11201  }
11202 
11203  alloced_string1 = true;
11204 
11205  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (&buf1, string1, str1_compressed_length, str1_decompressed_length);
11206  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11207  {
11208  goto cleanup;
11209  }
11210 
11211  str_length1 = str1_decompressed_length;
11212  string1[str_length1] = '\0';
11213  }
11214  else
11215  {
11216  /* Skip the size byte */
11217  string1 = buf1.ptr + OR_BYTE_SIZE;
11218  }
11219 
11220  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11221  {
11222  ASSERT_ERROR ();
11223  goto cleanup;
11224  }
11225 
11226  /* String 2 */
11227 
11228  or_init (&buf2, str2, 0);
11229 
11230  if (str_length2 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
11231  {
11232  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (&buf2, &str2_compressed_length, &str2_decompressed_length);
11233  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11234  {
11235  goto cleanup;
11236  }
11237 
11238  string2 = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str2_decompressed_length + 1);
11239  if (string2 == NULL)
11240  {
11241  /* Error report */
11242  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, str2_decompressed_length);
11243  goto cleanup;
11244  }
11245 
11246  alloced_string2 = true;
11247 
11248  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (&buf2, string2, str2_compressed_length, str2_decompressed_length);
11249  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11250  {
11251  goto cleanup;
11252  }
11253 
11254  str_length2 = str2_decompressed_length;
11255  string2[str_length2] = '\0';
11256  }
11257  else
11258  {
11259  /* Skip the size byte */
11260  string2 = buf2.ptr + OR_BYTE_SIZE;
11261  }
11262 
11263  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11264  {
11265  ASSERT_ERROR ();
11266  goto cleanup;
11267  }
11268 
11269  /* Compare the strings */
11270 
11271  strc =
11272  QSTR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) string1, str_length1, (unsigned char *) string2, str_length2);
11273  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
11274 
11275  /* Clean up the strings */
11276  if (string1 != NULL && alloced_string1 == true)
11277  {
11278  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string1);
11279  }
11280 
11281  if (string2 != NULL && alloced_string2 == true)
11282  {
11283  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string2);
11284  }
11285 
11286  return c;
11287 
11288 cleanup:
11289  if (string1 != NULL && alloced_string1 == true)
11290  {
11291  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string1);
11292  }
11293 
11294  if (string2 != NULL && alloced_string2 == true)
11295  {
11296  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string2);
11297  }
11298 
11299  return DB_UNK;
11300 }
11301 
11302 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
11303 mr_cmpval_string (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
11304  int collation)
11305 {
11306  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
11307  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
11308  int size1, size2;
11309  int strc;
11310 
11311  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
11312  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
11313 
11314 
11315  /*
11316  * Check if the is_max_string flag set for each DB_VALUE.
11317  * If "value1" has the flag set, return 1, meaning that "value2" is Less Than "value1".
11318  * If "value2" has the flag set, return -1, meaning that "value1" is Greater Than "value2".
11319  */
11320 
11321  if (value1->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
11322  {
11323  if (value2->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
11324  {
11325  /* Both strings are max_string. Therefore equal. Even though this should not happen. */
11326  assert (false);
11327  return DB_EQ;
11328  }
11329  return DB_GT;
11330  }
11331  else
11332  {
11333  if (value2->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
11334  {
11335  return DB_LT;
11336  }
11337  }
11338 
11339  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL || db_get_string_codeset (value1) != db_get_string_codeset (value1))
11340  {
11341  return DB_UNK;
11342  }
11343 
11344  size1 = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
11345  size2 = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
11346 
11347  if (size1 < 0)
11348  {
11349  size1 = strlen ((char *) string1);
11350  }
11351 
11352  if (size2 < 0)
11353  {
11354  size2 = strlen ((char *) string2);
11355  }
11356 
11357  if (collation == -1)
11358  {
11359  assert (false);
11360  return DB_UNK;
11361  }
11362 
11363  strc = QSTR_COMPARE (collation, string1, size1, string2, size2);
11364  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
11365 
11366  return c;
11367 }
11368 
11369 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
11370 static int
11371 mr_cmpval_string2 (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int length, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
11372 {
11373  int c;
11374  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
11375  int len1, len2, string_size;
11376 
11377  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
11378  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
11379 
11380  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
11381  {
11382  return DB_UNK;
11383  }
11384 
11385  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
11386  len1 = MIN (string_size, length);
11387  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
11388  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);
11389 
11390  c = QSTR_COMPARE (string1, len1, string2, len2);
11391  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (c);
11392 
11393  return c;
11394 }
11395 #endif

11428 static void
11429 mr_initmem_char (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
11430 {
11431 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
11432  int mem_length;
11433 
11434  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));

11437  memset (memptr, 0, mem_length);

11440 
11441 
11442 /*
11443  * Note! Due to the "within tolerance" comparison of domains used for
11444  * assignment validation, we may get values in here whose precision is
11445  * less than the precision of the actual attribute. This prevents
11446  * having to copy a string just to coerce a value into a larger precision.
11447  * Note that the precision of the source value may also come in as -1 here
11448  * which is used to mean a "floating" precision that is assumed to be
11449  * compatible with the destination domain as long as the associated value
11450  * is within tolerance. This case is generally only seen for string
11451  * literals that have been produced by the parser. These literals will
11452  * not contain blank padding and strlen() or db_get_string_size() can be
11453  * used to determine the number of significant characters.
11454  *
11455  */
11456 static int
11457 mr_setmem_char (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
11458 {
11459  int error = NO_ERROR;
11460  char *src, *mem;
11461  int src_precision, src_length, mem_length, pad;
11462 
11463  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
11464 
11465  if (value == NULL)
11466  {
11467  return NO_ERROR;
11468  }
11469 
11470  /* Get information from the value */
11471  src = db_get_string (value);
11472  src_precision = DB_GET_STRING_PRECISION (value);
11473  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
11474 
11475  if (src == NULL)
11476  {
11477  return NO_ERROR;
11478  }
11479 
11480  /* Check for special NTS flag. This may not be necessary any more. */
11481  if (src_length < 0)
11482  {
11483  src_length = strlen (src);
11484  }
11485 
11486 
11487  /* The only thing we really care about at this point, is the byte length of the string. The precision could be
11488  * checked here but it really isn't necessary for this operation. Calculate the maximum number of bytes we have
11489  * available here. The multiplier is dependent on codeset */
11490  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11491 
11492  if (mem_length < src_length)
11493  {
11494  /*
11495  * should never get here, this is supposed to be caught during domain
11496  * validation, need a better error message.
11497  */
11498  error = ER_OBJ_DOMAIN_CONFLICT;
11499  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "");
11500  }
11501  else
11502  {
11503  /* copy the value into memory */
11504  mem = (char *) memptr;
11505  memcpy (mem, src, src_length);
11506 
11507  /*
11508  * Check for space padding, if this were a national string, we would
11509  * need to be padding with the appropriate space character !
11510  */
11511  pad = mem_length - src_length;
11512  if (pad)
11513  {
11514  int i;
11515 
11516  for (i = src_length; i < mem_length; i++)
11517  {
11518  mem[i] = ' ';
11519  }
11520  }
11521  }
11522  return error;
11523 }
11524

11526 static int
11527 mr_getmem_char (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
11528 {
11529  int mem_length;
11530  char *new_;
11531 
11532  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
11533  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
11534  {
11535  assert (false);
11536  return ER_FAILED;
11537  }
11538 
11539  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) mem, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &mem_length);
11540  if (mem_length == 0)
11541  {
11542  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11543  }
11544 
11545  if (!copy)
11546  {
11547  new_ = (char *) mem;
11548  }
11549  else
11550  {
11551  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
11552  if (new_ == NULL)
11553  {
11554  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
11555  return er_errid ();
11556  }
11557  memcpy (new_, (char *) mem, mem_length);
11558  /* make sure that all outgoing strings are NULL terminated */
11559  new_[mem_length] = '\0';
11560  }
11561 
11562  db_make_char (value, domain->precision, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
11563  if (copy)
11564  {
11565  value->need_clear = true;
11566  }
11567 
11568  return NO_ERROR;
11569 }

11583 static int
11584 mr_index_lengthmem_char (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
11585 {

11587 
11588  assert (!(IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision) && memptr == NULL));
11589 
11590  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
11591  {
11592  memcpy (&mem_length, memptr, OR_INT_SIZE);
11593  mem_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
11594  }
11595  else
11596  {
11597  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11598  }

11601 }

11603 static void
11604 mr_data_writemem_char (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
11605 {
11606  int mem_length;
11607 
11608  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
11609 
11610  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11611 
11612  /*
11613  * We simply dump the memory image to disk, it will already have been padded.
11614  * If this were a national character string, at this point, we'd have to
11615  * decide now to perform a character set conversion.
11616  */
11617  or_put_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
11618 }
11619 
11620 static void
11621 mr_data_readmem_char (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
11622 {
11623  int mem_length, padding;
11624 
11625  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
11626 
11627  if (mem == NULL)
11628  {
11629  /*
11630  * If we passed in a size, then use it. Otherwise, determine the
11631  * size from the domain.
11632  */
11633  if (size > 0)
11634  {
11635  or_advance (buf, size);
11636  }
11637  else
11638  {
11639  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11640  or_advance (buf, mem_length);
11641  }
11642  }
11643  else
11644  {
11645  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
11646 
11647  if (size != -1 && mem_length > size)
11648  {
11649  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
11650  or_abort (buf);
11651  }
11652  or_get_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
11653 
11654  /*
11655  * We should only see padding if the string is contained within a packed
11656  * value that had extra padding to ensure alignment. If we see these,
11657  * just pop them out of the buffer. This shouldn't ever happen for the
11658  * "getmem" function, only for the "getval" function.
11659  */
11660  if (size != -1)
11661  {
11662  padding = size - mem_length;
11663  if (padding > 0)
11664  {
11665  or_advance (buf, padding);
11666  }
11667  }
11668  }
11669 }

11674 }

11682 static int
11683 mr_setval_char (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
11684 {
11685  int error = NO_ERROR;
11686  int src_precision, src_length;
11687  char *src_string, *new_;
11688 
11689  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
11690  if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
11691  {
11692  DB_DOMAIN_INIT_CHAR (dest, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE);
11693  }
11694  else
11695  {
11696  src_precision = DB_GET_STRING_PRECISION (src);
11697  if (src_precision == 0)
11698  {
11699  src_precision = TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE;
11700  }
11701  DB_DOMAIN_INIT_CHAR (dest, src_precision);
11702  /* Get information from the value */
11703  src_string = db_get_string (src);
11704  src_length = db_get_string_size (src); /* size in bytes */
11705 
11706  /* shouldn't see a NULL string at this point, treat as NULL */
11707  if (src_string != NULL)
11708  {
11709  if (!copy)
11710  {
11711  db_make_char (dest, src_precision, src_string, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
11712  db_get_string_collation (src));
11713  }
11714  else
11715  {
11716  /* Check for NTS marker, may not need to do this any more */
11717  if (src_length < 0)
11718  {
11719  src_length = strlen (src_string);
11720  }
11721 
11722  /* make sure the copy gets a NULL terminator */
11723  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
11724  if (new_ == NULL)
11725  {
11726  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
11727  error = er_errid ();
11728  }
11729  else
11730  {
11731  memcpy (new_, src_string, src_length);
11732  new_[src_length] = '\0';
11733  db_make_char (dest, src_precision, new_, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
11734  db_get_string_collation (src));
11735  dest->need_clear = true;
11736  }
11737  }
11738  }
11739  }
11740 
11741  return error;
11742 }

11745 mr_index_lengthval_char (DB_VALUE * value)

11747  return mr_data_lengthval_char (value, 1);
