11749 
11750 /*
11751  */
11752 static int
11753 mr_data_lengthval_char (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
11754 {
11755  int packed_length, src_precision;
11756  char *src;
11757 
11758  src = db_get_string (value);
11759  if (src == NULL)
11760  {
11761  return 0;
11762  }
11763 
11764  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
11765  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
11766  {
11767  packed_length = STR_SIZE (src_precision, db_get_string_codeset (value));
11768  }
11769  else
11770  {
11771  /*
11772  * Precision is "floating", calculate the effective precision based on the
11773  * string length.
11774  * Should be rounding this up so it is a proper multiple of the charset
11775  * width ?
11776  */
11777  packed_length = db_get_string_size (value);
11778  if (packed_length < 0)
11779  {
11780  packed_length = strlen (src);
11781  }
11782 
11783  /* add in storage for a size prefix on the packed value. */
11784  packed_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
11785  }
11786 
11787  /*
11788  * NOTE: We do NOT perform padding here, if this is used in the context
11789  * of a packed value, the or_put_value() family of functions must handle
11790  * their own padding, this is because "lengthval" and "writeval" can be
11791  * used to place values into the disk representation of instances and
11792  * there can be no padding in there.
11793  */
11794 
11795  return packed_length;
11796 }

11800 mr_index_writeval_char (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)

11804 
11805 /*
11806  * See commentary in mr_lengthval_char.
11807  */
11808 static int
11809 mr_data_writeval_char (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
11810 {
11811  return mr_writeval_char_internal (buf, value, INT_ALIGNMENT);
11812 }
11813 
11814 static int
11815 mr_writeval_char_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
11816 {
11817  int src_precision, src_length, packed_length, pad;
11818  char *src;
11819  int rc = NO_ERROR;
11820 
11821  src = db_get_string (value);
11822  if (src == NULL)
11823  {
11824  return rc;
11825  }
11826 
11827  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
11828 
11829  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
11830  {
11831  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
11832 
11833  if (src_length < 0)
11834  {
11835  src_length = strlen (src);
11836  }
11837 
11838  packed_length = STR_SIZE (src_precision, db_get_string_codeset (value));
11839 
11840  if (packed_length < src_length)
11841  {
11842  /* should have caught this by now, truncate silently */
11843  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, packed_length);
11844  }
11845  else
11846  {
11847  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, src_length);
11848  /*
11849  * Check for space padding, if this were a national string, we
11850  * would need to be padding with the appropriate space character !
11851  */
11852  pad = packed_length - src_length;
11853  if (pad)
11854  {
11855  int i;
11856  for (i = src_length; i < packed_length; i++)
11857  {
11858  rc = or_put_byte (buf, (int) ' ');
11859  }
11860  }
11861  }
11862  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11863  {
11864  return rc;
11865  }
11866  }
11867  else
11868  {
11869  /*
11870  * This is a "floating" precision value. Pack what we can based on the
11871  * string size. Note that for this to work, this can only be packed as
11872  * part of a domain tagged value and we must include a length prefix
11873  * after the domain.
11874  */
11875  packed_length = db_get_string_size (value);
11876  if (packed_length < 0)
11877  {
11878  packed_length = strlen (src);
11879  }
11880 
11881  /* store the size prefix */
11882  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
11883  {
11884  rc = or_put_int (buf, packed_length);
11885  }
11886  else
11887  {
11888  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) (&packed_length), OR_INT_SIZE);
11889  }
11890  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
11891  {
11892  /* store the data */
11893  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, packed_length);
11894  /* there is no blank padding in this case */
11895  }
11896  }
11897  return rc;
11898 }

11901 mr_index_readval_char (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,

11903 {
11904  return mr_readval_char_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);

11907 static int
11908 mr_data_readval_char (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
11909  int copy_buf_len)

11911  return mr_readval_char_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, INT_ALIGNMENT);

11913 
11914 static int
11915 mr_readval_char_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
11916  int copy_buf_len, int align)
11917 {
11918  int mem_length, padding;
11919  int str_length, precision;
11920  char *new_;
11921  int rc = NO_ERROR;
11922  precision = domain->precision;
11923  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
11924  {
11925  assert (false);
11926  return ER_FAILED;
11927  }
11928 
11929  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
11930  {
11931  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
11932  {
11933  mem_length = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
11934  }
11935  else
11936  {
11937  rc = or_get_data (buf, (char *) (&mem_length), OR_INT_SIZE);
11938  }
11939  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11940  {
11941  return rc;
11942  }
11943 
11944  if (value == NULL)
11945  {
11946  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
11947  }
11948  else if (!copy)
11949  {
11950  db_make_char (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, buf->ptr, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
11951  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
11952  value->need_clear = false;
11953  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
11954  }
11955  else
11956  {
11957  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
11958  {
11959  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
11960  new_ = copy_buf;
11961  }
11962  else
11963  {
11964  /* Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL terminator */
11965  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
11966  }
11967 
11968  if (new_ == NULL)
11969  {
11970  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
11971  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
11972  or_abort (buf);
11973 
11974  return ER_FAILED;
11975  }
11976  else
11977  {
11978  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
11979  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
11980  {
11981  if (new_ != copy_buf)
11982  {
11983  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
11984  }
11985  return rc;
11986  }
11987  new_[mem_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
11988  db_make_char (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
11989  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
11990  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
11991  }
11992  }
11993  }
11994  else
11995  {
11996  /*
11997  * Normal fixed width char(n) whose size can be determined by looking at
11998  * the domain.
11999  */
12000  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12001 
12002  if (disk_size != -1 && mem_length > disk_size)
12003  {
12004  /*
12005  * If we're low here, we could just read what we have and make a
12006  * smaller value. Still the domain should match at this point.
12007  */
12008  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
12009  or_abort (buf);
12010  return ER_FAILED;
12011  }
12012 
12013  if (value == NULL)
12014  {
12015  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12016  }
12017  else if (disk_size == 0)
12018  {
12019  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_CHAR, precision, 0);
12020  }
12021  else if (!copy)
12022  {
12023  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) buf->ptr, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &str_length);
12024  if (str_length == 0)
12025  {
12026  str_length = mem_length;
12027  }
12028  db_make_char (value, precision, buf->ptr, str_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12029  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12030  value->need_clear = false;
12031  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12032  }
12033  else
12034  {
12035  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
12036  {
12037  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
12038  new_ = copy_buf;
12039  }
12040  else
12041  {
12042  /*
12043  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
12044  * terminator
12045  */
12046  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
12047  }
12048  if (new_ == NULL)
12049  {
12050  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
12051  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), domain->precision, 0);
12052  or_abort (buf);
12053 
12054  return ER_FAILED;
12055  }
12056  else
12057  {
12058  int actual_size = 0;
12059  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
12060  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
12061  {
12062  if (new_ != copy_buf)
12063  {
12064  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
12065  }
12066  return rc;
12067  }
12068  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) new_, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &actual_size);
12069  if (actual_size == 0)
12070  {
12071  actual_size = mem_length;
12072  }
12073  new_[actual_size] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
12074  db_make_char (value, domain->precision, new_, actual_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12075  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12076  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
12077  }
12078  }
12079 
12080  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
12081  {
12082  /*
12083  * We should only see padding if the string is contained within a
12084  * packed value that had extra padding to ensure alignment. If we
12085  * see these, just pop them out of the buffer.
12086  */
12087  if (disk_size != -1)
12088  {
12089  padding = disk_size - mem_length;
12090  if (padding > 0)
12091  {
12092  rc = or_advance (buf, padding);
12093  }
12094  }
12095  }
12096  }
12097  return rc;
12098 }
12099

12101 mr_index_cmpdisk_char (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
12102 {
12103  assert (domain != NULL);
12104 
12105  return mr_cmpdisk_char_internal (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);
12106 }

12108 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
12109 mr_data_cmpdisk_char (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
12110 {
12111  assert (domain != NULL);
12112 
12113  return mr_cmpdisk_char_internal (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp, INT_ALIGNMENT);
12114 }

12116 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
12117 mr_cmpdisk_char_internal (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
12118  int align)
12119 {
12120  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
12121  int mem_length1, mem_length2, strc;
12122 
12123  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
12124  {
12125  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
12126  {
12127  mem_length1 = OR_GET_INT (mem1);
12128  mem_length2 = OR_GET_INT (mem2);
12129  }
12130  else
12131  {
12132  memcpy (&mem_length1, mem1, OR_INT_SIZE);
12133  memcpy (&mem_length2, mem2, OR_INT_SIZE);
12134  }
12135  mem1 = (char *) mem1 + OR_INT_SIZE;
12136  mem2 = (char *) mem2 + OR_INT_SIZE;
12137  }
12138  else
12139  {
12140  /*
12141  * Normal fixed width char(n) whose size can be determined by looking at
12142  * the domain.
12143  * Needs NCHAR work here to separate the dependencies on disk_size and
12144  * mem_size.
12145  */
12146  mem_length1 = mem_length2 = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12147  }
12148 
12149  strc = QSTR_CHAR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) mem1, mem_length1, (unsigned char *) mem2,
12150  mem_length2);
12151  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
12152 
12153  return c;
12154 }
12155 
12156 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
12157 mr_cmpval_char (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp, int collation)
12158 {
12159  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
12160  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
12161  int strc;
12162 
12163  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
12164  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
12165 
12166  /*
12167  * Check if the is_max_string flag set for each DB_VALUE.
12168  * If "value1" has the flag set, return 1, meaning that "value2" is Less Than "value1".
12169  * If "value2" has the flag set, return -1, meaning that "value1" is Greater Than "value2".
12170  */
12171 
12172  if (value1->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
12173  {
12174  if (value2->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
12175  {
12176  /* Both strings are max_string. Therefore equal. Even though this should not happen. */
12177  assert (false);
12178  return DB_EQ;
12179  }
12180  return DB_GT;
12181  }
12182  else
12183  {
12184  if (value2->data.ch.info.is_max_string != 0)
12185  {
12186  return DB_LT;
12187  }
12188  }
12189 
12190  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL || db_get_string_codeset (value1) != db_get_string_codeset (value1))
12191  {
12192  return DB_UNK;
12193  }
12194 
12195  if (collation == -1)
12196  {
12197  assert (false);
12198  return DB_UNK;
12199  }
12200 
12201  strc = QSTR_CHAR_COMPARE (collation, string1, (int) db_get_string_size (value1), string2,
12202  (int) db_get_string_size (value2));
12203  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
12204 
12205  return c;
12206 }
12207 
12208 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
12209 static int
12210 mr_cmpval_char2 (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int length, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
12211 {
12212  int c;
12213  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
12214  int len1, len2, string_size;
12215 
12216  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
12217  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
12218 
12219  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
12220  {
12221  return DB_UNK;
12222  }
12223 
12224  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
12225  len1 = MIN (string_size, length);
12226  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
12227  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);
12228 
12229  c = QSTR_CHAR_COMPARE (string1, len1, string2, len2);
12230  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (c);
12231 
12232  return c;
12233 }
12234 #endif

12267 static void
12268 mr_initmem_nchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
12269 {
12270 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
12271  int mem_length;
12272 
12273  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
12274

12276  memset (memptr, 0, mem_length);
12277 #endif
12278 }
12279 
12280 
12281 /*
12282  * Due to the "within tolerance" comparison of domains used for
12283  * assignment validation, we may get values in here whose precision is
12284  * less than the precision of the actual attribute. This prevents
12285  * having to copy a string just to coerce a value into a larger precision.
12286  * Note that the precision of the source value may also come in as -1 here
12287  * which is used to mean a "floating" precision that is assumed to be
12288  * compatible with the destination domain as long as the associated value
12289  * is within tolerance. This case is generally only seen for string
12290  * literals that have been produced by the parser. These literals will
12291  * not contain blank padding and strlen() or db_get_string_size() can be
12292  * used to determine the number of significant characters.
12293  */
12294 static int
12295 mr_setmem_nchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
12296 {
12297  int error = NO_ERROR;
12298  char *src, *mem;
12299  int src_precision, src_length, mem_length, pad;
12300 
12301  if (value == NULL)
12302  {
12303  return NO_ERROR;
12304  }
12305 
12306  /* Get information from the value */
12307  src = db_get_string (value);
12308  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
12309  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
12310 
12311  if (src == NULL)
12312  {
12313  return NO_ERROR;
12314  }
12315 
12316  /* Check for special NTS flag. This may not be necessary any more. */
12317  if (src_length < 0)
12318  {
12319  src_length = strlen (src);
12320  }
12321 
12322  /*
12323  * The only thing we really care about at this point, is the byte
12324  * length of the string. The precision could be checked here but it
12325  * really isn't necessary for this operation.
12326  * Calculate the maximum number of bytes we have available here.
12327  */
12328  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12329 
12330  if (mem_length < src_length)
12331  {
12332  /*
12333  * should never get here, this is supposed to be caught during domain
12334  * validation, need a better error message.
12335  */
12336  error = ER_OBJ_DOMAIN_CONFLICT;
12337  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "");
12338  }
12339  else
12340  {
12341  /* copy the value into memory */
12342  mem = (char *) memptr;
12343  memcpy (mem, src, src_length);
12344 
12345  /*
12346  * Check for space padding, if this were a national string, we would need
12347  * to be padding with the appropriate space character !
12348  */
12349  pad = mem_length - src_length;
12350  if (pad)
12351  {
12352  int i;
12353 
12354  for (i = src_length; i < mem_length; i++)
12355  {
12356  mem[i] = ' ';
12357  }
12358  }
12359  }
12360 
12361  return error;
12362 }
12363 
12364 /*
12365  * We always ensure that the string returned here is NULL terminated
12366  * if the copy flag is on. This technically shouldn't be necessary but there
12367  * is a lot of code scattered about (especially applications) that assumes
12368  * NULL termination.
12369  */
12370 static int
12371 mr_getmem_nchar (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
12372 {
12373  int mem_length;
12374  char *new_;
12375 
12376  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
12377  {
12378  assert (false);
12379  return ER_FAILED;
12380  }
12381  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) mem, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &mem_length);
12382  if (mem_length == 0)
12383  {
12384  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12385  }
12386 
12387  if (!copy)
12388  {
12389  new_ = (char *) mem;
12390  }
12391  else
12392  {
12393  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
12394  if (new_ == NULL)
12395  {
12396  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12397  return er_errid ();
12398  }
12399  memcpy (new_, (char *) mem, mem_length);
12400  /* make sure that all outgoing strings are NULL terminated */
12401  new_[mem_length] = '\0';
12402  }
12403 
12404  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
12405  {
12406  assert (false);
12407  return ER_FAILED;
12408  }
12409  db_make_nchar (value, domain->precision, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12410  if (copy)
12411  {
12412  value->need_clear = true;
12413  }
12414 
12415  return NO_ERROR;
12416 }

12419 mr_data_lengthmem_nchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
12420 {
12421  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
12422 
12423  return STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12424 }

12426 static int
12427 mr_index_lengthmem_nchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
12428 {
12429  int mem_length;
12430 
12431  assert (!(IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision) && memptr == NULL));
12432 
12433  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
12434  {
12435  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12436  }
12437  else
12438  {
12439  memcpy (&mem_length, memptr, OR_INT_SIZE);
12440  mem_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
12441  }
12442 
12443  return mem_length;
12444 }

12446 static void
12447 mr_data_writemem_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
12448 {
12449  int mem_length;
12450 
12451  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12452 
12453  /*
12454  * We simply dump the memory image to disk, it will already have been padded.
12455  * If this were a national character string, at this point, we'd have to
12456  * decide now to perform a character set conversion.
12457  */
12458  or_put_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
12459 }
12460 
12461 static void
12462 mr_data_readmem_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
12463 {
12464  int mem_length, padding;
12465 
12466  if (mem == NULL)
12467  {
12468  /*
12469  * If we passed in a size, then use it. Otherwise, determine the
12470  * size from the domain.
12471  */
12472  if (size > 0)
12473  {
12474  or_advance (buf, size);
12475  }
12476  else
12477  {
12478  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12479  or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12480  }
12481  }
12482  else
12483  {
12484  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12485 
12486  if (size != -1 && mem_length > size)
12487  {
12488  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
12489  or_abort (buf);
12490  }
12491  or_get_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
12492 
12493  /*
12494  * We should only see padding if the string is contained within a packed
12495  * value that had extra padding to ensure alignment. If we see these,
12496  * just pop them out of the buffer. This shouldn't ever happen for
12497  * the "getmem" function, only for the "getval" function.
12498  */
12499  if (size != -1)
12500  {
12501  padding = size - mem_length;
12502  if (padding > 0)
12503  {
12504  or_advance (buf, padding);
12505  }
12506  }
12507  }
12508 }

12511 mr_freemem_nchar (void *memptr)

12513 }

12515 static void
12516 mr_initval_nchar (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)

12519 }
12520 
12521 static int
12522 mr_setval_nchar (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
12523 {
12524  int error = NO_ERROR;
12525  int src_precision, src_length;
12526  char *src_string, *new_;
12527 
12528  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
12529  if (src == NULL || (DB_IS_NULL (src) && db_value_precision (src) == 0))
12530  {
12531  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_NCHAR, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
12532  }
12533  else if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
12534  {
12535  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_NCHAR, db_value_precision (src), 0);
12536  }
12537  else
12538  {
12539  /* Get information from the value */
12540  src_string = db_get_string (src);
12541  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
12542  src_length = db_get_string_size (src); /* size in bytes */
12543 
12544  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_NCHAR, src_precision, 0);
12545 
12546  /* shouldn't see a NULL string at this point, treat as NULL */
12547  if (src_string != NULL)
12548  {
12549  if (!copy)
12550  {
12551  db_make_nchar (dest, src_precision, src_string, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
12552  db_get_string_collation (src));
12553  }
12554  else
12555  {
12556  /* Check for NTS marker, may not need to do this any more */
12557  if (src_length < 0)
12558  {
12559  src_length = strlen (src_string);
12560  }
12561 
12562  /* make sure the copy gets a NULL terminator */
12563  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
12564  if (new_ == NULL)
12565  {
12566  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12567  error = er_errid ();
12568  }
12569  else
12570  {
12571  memcpy (new_, src_string, src_length);
12572  new_[src_length] = '\0';
12573  db_make_nchar (dest, src_precision, new_, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
12574  db_get_string_collation (src));
12575  dest->need_clear = true;
12576  }
12577  }
12578  }
12579  }
12580  return error;
12581 }
12582 
12583 
12584 static int
12585 mr_index_lengthval_nchar (DB_VALUE * value)
12586 {
12587  return mr_data_lengthval_nchar (value, 1);
12588 }
12589 
12590 static int
12591 mr_data_lengthval_nchar (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
12592 {
12593  int packed_length, src_precision;
12594  char *src;
12595  INTL_CODESET src_codeset = (INTL_CODESET) db_get_string_codeset (value);
12596 
12597  src = db_get_string (value);
12598  if (src == NULL)
12599  {
12600  return 0;
12601  }
12602 
12603  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
12604  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
12605  {
12606  /* Would have to check for charset conversion here ! */
12607  packed_length = STR_SIZE (src_precision, src_codeset);
12608  }
12609  else
12610  {
12611  /* Precision is "floating", calculate the effective precision based on the string length. Should be rounding this
12612  * up so it is a proper multiple of the charset width ? */
12613  packed_length = db_get_string_size (value);
12614  if (packed_length < 0)
12615  {
12616  packed_length = strlen (src);
12617  }
12618 
12619 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
12620  /*
12621  * If this is a client side string, and the disk representation length
12622  * is requested, Need to return the length of a converted string.
12623  *
12624  * Note: This is only done to support the 'floating precision' style of
12625  * fixed strings. In this case, the string is treated similarly to a
12626  * variable length string.
12627  */
12628  if (!db_on_server && packed_length > 0 && disk && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SRVR_STR (src_codeset))
12629  {
12630  int unconverted;
12631  int char_count = db_get_string_length (value);
12632  char *converted_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, src_codeset));
12633 
12634  intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) src, char_count, src_codeset, (unsigned char *) converted_string,
12635  lang_charset (), &unconverted);
12636 
12637  if (converted_string)
12638  {
12639  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) converted_string, (char_count - unconverted), src_codeset,
12640  &packed_length);
12641  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, converted_string);
12642  }
12643  }
12644 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
12645 
12646  /* add in storage for a size prefix on the packed value. */
12647  packed_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
12648  }
12649 
12650  /*
12651  * NOTE: We do NOT perform padding here, if this is used in the context
12652  * of a packed value, the or_put_value() family of functions must handle
12653  * their own padding, this is because "lengthval" and "writeval" can be
12654  * used to place values into the disk representation of instances and
12655  * there can be no padding in there.
12656  */
12657 
12658  return packed_length;
12659 }
12660 
12661 
12662 static int
12663 mr_index_writeval_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
12664 {
12665  return mr_writeval_nchar_internal (buf, value, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);
12666 }
12667 
12668 /*
12669  * See commentary in mr_lengthval_nchar.
12670  */
12671 static int
12672 mr_data_writeval_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
12673 {
12674  return mr_writeval_nchar_internal (buf, value, INT_ALIGNMENT);
12675 }
12676 
12677 static int
12678 mr_writeval_nchar_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
12679 {
12680  int src_precision, src_size, packed_size, pad;
12681  char *src;
12682  INTL_CODESET src_codeset;
12683  int pad_charsize;
12684  char pad_char[2];
12685  char *converted_string = NULL;
12686  int rc = NO_ERROR;
12687 
12688  src = db_get_string (value);
12689  if (src == NULL)
12690  {
12691  return rc;
12692  }
12693 
12694  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
12695  src_size = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
12696  src_codeset = (INTL_CODESET) db_get_string_codeset (value);
12697 
12698  if (src_size < 0)
12699  {
12700  src_size = strlen (src);
12701  }
12702 
12703 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
12704  if (!db_on_server && src_size > 0 && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SRVR_STR (src_codeset))
12705  {
12706  int unconverted;
12707  int char_count = db_get_string_length (value);
12708 
12709  converted_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, src_codeset));
12710  (void) intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) src, char_count, src_codeset, (unsigned char *) converted_string,
12711  lang_charset (), &unconverted);
12712  /* Reset the 'src' of the string */
12713  src = converted_string;
12714  src_precision = src_precision - unconverted;
12715  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) converted_string, (char_count - unconverted), src_codeset, &src_size);
12716  src_codeset = lang_charset ();
12717  }
12718  intl_pad_char (src_codeset, (unsigned char *) pad_char, &pad_charsize);
12719 #else
12720  /*
12721  * (void) lang_srvr_space_char(pad_char, &pad_charsize);
12722  *
12723  * Until this is resolved, set the pad character to be an ASCII space.
12724  */
12725  pad_charsize = 1;
12726  pad_char[0] = ' ';
12727  pad_char[1] = ' ';
12728 #endif
12729 
12730  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
12731  {
12732  packed_size = STR_SIZE (src_precision, src_codeset);
12733 
12734  if (packed_size < src_size)
12735  {
12736  /* should have caught this by now, truncate silently */
12737  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, packed_size);
12738  }
12739  else
12740  {
12741  if ((rc = or_put_data (buf, src, src_size)) == NO_ERROR)
12742  {
12743  /*
12744  * Check for space padding, if this were a national string, we
12745  * would need to be padding with the appropriate space character!
12746  */
12747  pad = packed_size - src_size;
12748  if (pad)
12749  {
12750  int i;
12751  for (i = src_size; i < packed_size; i += pad_charsize)
12752  {
12753  rc = or_put_byte (buf, pad_char[0]);
12754  if (i + 1 < packed_size && pad_charsize == 2)
12755  {
12756  rc = or_put_byte (buf, pad_char[1]);
12757  }
12758  }
12759  }
12760  }
12761  }
12762  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
12763  {
12764  goto error;
12765  }
12766  }
12767  else
12768  {
12769  /*
12770  * This is a "floating" precision value. Pack what we can based on the
12771  * string size. Note that for this to work, this can only be packed as
12772  * part of a domain tagged value and we must include a size prefix after
12773  * the domain.
12774  */
12775 
12776  /* store the size prefix */
12777  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
12778  {
12779  rc = or_put_int (buf, src_size);
12780  }
12781  else
12782  {
12783  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) (&src_size), OR_INT_SIZE);
12784  }
12785 
12786  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
12787  {
12788  /* store the data */
12789  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, src_size);
12790  /* there is no blank padding in this case */
12791  }
12792  }
12793 
12794 error:
12795  if (converted_string)
12796  {
12797  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, converted_string);
12798  }
12799 
12800  return rc;
12801 }
12802 
12803 static int
12804 mr_index_readval_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
12805  int copy_buf_len)
12806 {
12807  return mr_readval_nchar_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);
12808 }
12809 
12810 static int
12811 mr_data_readval_nchar (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
12812  int copy_buf_len)
12813 {
12814  return mr_readval_nchar_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, INT_ALIGNMENT);
12815 }
12816 
12817 static int
12818 mr_readval_nchar_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
12819  int copy_buf_len, int align)
12820 {
12821  int mem_length, padding;
12822  char *new_;
12823  int rc = NO_ERROR;
12824 
12825  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
12826  {
12827  assert (false);
12828  return ER_FAILED;
12829  }
12830 
12831  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
12832  {
12833  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
12834  {
12835  mem_length = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
12836  }
12837  else
12838  {
12839  rc = or_get_data (buf, (char *) (&mem_length), OR_INT_SIZE);
12840  }
12841  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
12842  {
12843  return ER_FAILED;
12844  }
12845 
12846  if (value == NULL)
12847  {
12848  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12849  }
12850  else if (!copy)
12851  {
12852  db_make_nchar (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, buf->ptr, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12853  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12854  value->need_clear = false;
12855  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12856  }
12857  else
12858  {
12859  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
12860  {
12861  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
12862  new_ = copy_buf;
12863  }
12864  else
12865  {
12866  /*
12867  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
12868  * terminator
12869  */
12870  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
12871  }
12872 
12873  if (new_ == NULL)
12874  {
12875  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
12876  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
12877  or_abort (buf);
12878 
12879  return ER_FAILED;
12880  }
12881  else
12882  {
12883  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
12884  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
12885  {
12886  if (new_ != copy_buf)
12887  {
12888  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
12889  }
12890  return rc;
12891  }
12892  new_[mem_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
12893  db_make_nchar (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12894  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12895  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
12896  }
12897  }
12898  }
12899  else
12900  {
12901  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
12902 
12903  if (disk_size != -1 && mem_length > disk_size)
12904  {
12905  /*
12906  * If we're low here, we could just read what we have and make a
12907  * smaller value. Still the domain should match at this point.
12908  */
12909  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
12910  or_abort (buf);
12911 
12912  return ER_FAILED;
12913  }
12914 
12915  if (value == NULL)
12916  {
12917  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12918  }
12919  else if (!copy)
12920  {
12921  int str_length;
12922 
12923  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) buf->ptr, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &str_length);
12924  if (str_length == 0)
12925  {
12926  str_length = mem_length;
12927  }
12928  db_make_nchar (value, domain->precision, buf->ptr, str_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12929  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12930  value->need_clear = false;
12931  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
12932  }
12933  else
12934  {
12935  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
12936  {
12937  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
12938  new_ = copy_buf;
12939  }
12940  else
12941  {
12942  /*
12943  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
12944  * terminator
12945  */
12946  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
12947  }
12948 
12949  if (new_ == NULL)
12950  {
12951  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
12952  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), domain->precision, 0);
12953  or_abort (buf);
12954 
12955  return ER_FAILED;
12956  }
12957  else
12958  {
12959  int actual_size = 0;
12960 
12961  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
12962  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
12963  {
12964  if (new_ != copy_buf)
12965  {
12966  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
12967  }
12968 
12969  return rc;
12970  }
12971  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) new_, domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), &actual_size);
12972  if (actual_size == 0)
12973  {
12974  actual_size = mem_length;
12975  }
12976  new_[actual_size] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
12977  db_make_nchar (value, domain->precision, new_, actual_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
12978  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
12979  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
12980  }
12981  }
12982 
12983  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
12984  {
12985  /* We should only see padding if the string is contained within a packed value that had extra padding to
12986  * ensure alignment. If we see these, just pop them out of the buffer. */
12987  if (disk_size != -1)
12988  {
12989  padding = disk_size - mem_length;
12990  if (padding > 0)
12991  {
12992  rc = or_advance (buf, padding);
12993  }
12994  }
12995  }
12996  }
12997 
12998  /* Check if conversion needs to be done */
12999 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13000  if (value && !db_on_server && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SQLTEXT (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain)) && !DB_IS_NULL (value))
13001  {
13002  int unconverted;
13003  int char_count;
13004  char *temp_string = db_get_nchar (value, &char_count);
13005 
13006  if (char_count > 0)
13007  {
13008  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain)));
13009  (void) intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) temp_string, char_count, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13010  (unsigned char *) new_, LANG_SYS_CODESET, &unconverted);
13011  db_value_clear (value);
13012  db_make_nchar (value, domain->precision, new_, STR_SIZE (char_count, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain)),
13013  TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13014  value->need_clear = true;
13015  }
13016  }
13017 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
13018 
13019  return rc;
13020 }

13024 {

13026

13031 mr_data_cmpdisk_nchar (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
13032 {
13033  assert (domain != NULL);

13038 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
13039 mr_cmpdisk_nchar_internal (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order,
13040  int *start_colp, int align)
13041 {
13042  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
13043  int mem_length1, mem_length2, strc;
13044 
13045  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
13046  {
13047  /*
13048  * This is only allowed if we're unpacking a "floating" domain CHAR(n) in
13049  * which case there will be a byte size prefix.
13050  */
13051  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
13052  {
13053  mem_length1 = OR_GET_INT (mem1);
13054  mem_length2 = OR_GET_INT (mem2);
13055  }
13056  else
13057  {
13058  memcpy (&mem_length1, mem1, OR_INT_SIZE);
13059  memcpy (&mem_length2, mem2, OR_INT_SIZE);
13060  }
13061  mem1 = (char *) mem1 + OR_INT_SIZE;
13062  mem2 = (char *) mem2 + OR_INT_SIZE;
13063  }
13064  else
13065  {
13066  mem_length1 = mem_length2 = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
13067  }
13068 
13069  strc = QSTR_NCHAR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) mem1, mem_length1, (unsigned char *) mem2,
13070  mem_length2, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
13071  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
13072 
13073  return c;
13074 }
13075 
13076 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
13077 mr_cmpval_nchar (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp, int collation)
13078 {
13079  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
13080  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
13081  int strc;
13082 
13083  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
13084  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
13085 
13086  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL || db_get_string_codeset (value1) != db_get_string_codeset (value2))
13087  {
13088  return DB_UNK;
13089  }
13090 
13091  if (collation == -1)
13092  {
13093  assert (false);
13094  return DB_UNK;
13095  }
13096 
13097  strc = QSTR_NCHAR_COMPARE (collation, string1, (int) db_get_string_size (value1), string2,
13098  (int) db_get_string_size (value2), db_get_string_codeset (value2));
13099  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
13100 
13101  return c;
13102 }

13104 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
13105 static int
13106 mr_cmpval_nchar2 (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int length, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
13107 {
13108  int c;
13109  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
13110  int len1, len2, string_size;
13111 
13112  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
13113  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
13114 
13115  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
13116  {
13117  return DB_UNK;

13119 
13120  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
13121  len1 = MIN (string_size, length);
13122  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
13123  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);
13124 
13125  c = nchar_compare (string1, len1, string2, len2, db_get_string_codeset (value2));
13126  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (c);
13127 
13128  return c;
13129 }

13163 
13164 static void
13165 mr_initmem_varnchar (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
13166 {
13167  *(char **) mem = NULL;
13168 }
13169 
13170 
13171 /*
13172  * The main difference between "memory" strings and "value" strings is that
13173  * the length tag is stored as an in-line prefix in the memory block allocated
13174  * to hold the string characters.
13175  */
13176 static int
13177 mr_setmem_varnchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
13178 {
13179  int error = NO_ERROR;
13180  char *src, *cur, *new_, **mem;
13181  int src_precision, src_length, new_length;
13182 
13183  /* get the current memory contents */
13184  mem = (char **) memptr;
13185  cur = *mem;
13186 
13187  if (value == NULL || (src = db_get_string (value)) == NULL)
13188  {
13189  /* remove the current value */
13190  if (cur != NULL)
13191  {
13192  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
13193  mr_initmem_varnchar (memptr, domain);
13194  }
13195  }
13196  else
13197  {
13198  /*
13199  * Get information from the value. Ignore precision for the time being
13200  * since we really only care about the byte size of the value for
13201  * varnchar.
13202  * Whether or not the value "fits" should have been checked by now.
13203  */
13204  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
13205  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
13206  if (src_length < 0)
13207  {
13208  src_length = strlen (src);
13209  }
13210 
13211  /*
13212  * Currently we NULL terminate the workspace string.
13213  * Could try to do the single byte size hack like we have in the
13214  * disk representation.
13215  */
13216  new_length = src_length + sizeof (int) + 1;
13217  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, new_length);
13218  if (new_ == NULL)
13219  {
13220  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
13221  error = er_errid ();
13222  }
13223  else
13224  {
13225  if (cur != NULL)
13226  {
13227  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
13228  }
13229 
13230  /* pack in the length prefix */
13231  *(int *) new_ = src_length;
13232  cur = new_ + sizeof (int);
13233  /* store the string */
13234  memcpy (cur, src, src_length);
13235  /* NULL terminate the stored string for safety */
13236  cur[src_length] = '\0';
13237  *mem = new_;
13238  }
13239  }
13240 
13241  return error;
13242 }
13243 
13244 static int
13245 mr_getmem_varnchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
13246 {
13247  int error = NO_ERROR;
13248  int mem_length;
13249  char **mem, *cur, *new_;
13250 
13251  /* get to the current value */
13252  mem = (char **) memptr;
13253  cur = *mem;
13254 
13255  if (cur == NULL)
13256  {
13257  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, domain->precision, 0);
13258  value->need_clear = false;
13259  }
13260  else
13261  {
13262  /* extract the length prefix and the pointer to the actual string data */
13263  mem_length = *(int *) cur;
13264  cur += sizeof (int);
13265 
13266  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
13267  {
13268  assert (false);
13269  return ER_FAILED;
13270  }
13271 
13272  if (!copy)
13273  {
13274  db_make_varnchar (value, domain->precision, cur, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13275  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13276  value->need_clear = false;
13277  }
13278  else
13279  {
13280  /* return it with a NULL terminator */
13281  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
13282  if (new_ == NULL)
13283  {
13284  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
13285  error = er_errid ();
13286  }
13287  else
13288  {
13289  memcpy (new_, cur, mem_length);
13290  new_[mem_length] = '\0';
13291  db_make_varnchar (value, domain->precision, new_, mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13292  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13293  value->need_clear = true;
13294  }
13295  }
13296  }
13297  return error;
13298 }
13299 
13300 
13301 /*
13302  * For the disk representation, we may be adding pad bytes
13303  * to round up to a word boundary.
13304  *
13305  * NOTE: We are currently adding a NULL terminator to the disk representation
13306  * for some code on the server that still manufactures pointers directly into
13307  * the disk buffer and assumes it is a NULL terminated string. This terminator
13308  * can be removed after the server has been updated. The logic for maintaining
13309  * the terminator is actually in the or_put_varchar, family of functions.
13310  */
13311 static int
13312 mr_data_lengthmem_varnchar (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
13313 {
13314  char **mem, *cur;
13315  int len;
13316 
13317  len = 0;
13318  if (!disk)
13319  {
13320  len = tp_VarNChar.size;
13321  }
13322  else if (memptr != NULL)
13323  {
13324  mem = (char **) memptr;
13325  cur = *mem;
13326  if (cur != NULL)
13327  {
13328  len = *(int *) cur;
13329  len = or_packed_varchar_length (len);
13330  }
13331  }
13332 
13333  return len;
13334 }

13350  if (cur != NULL)
13351  {
13352  len = *(int *) cur;
13353  cur += sizeof (int);
13354  or_packed_put_varchar (buf, cur, len);
13355  }
13356 }

13363  * but that may also include any padding byte that added to bring us up to

13395 static int
13396 mr_setval_varnchar (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
13397 {
13398  int error = NO_ERROR;
13399  int src_precision, src_length;
13400  char *src_str, *new_;
13401 
13402  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
13403  if (src == NULL || (DB_IS_NULL (src) && db_get_string (src) == 0))
13404  {
13405  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0);
13406  }
13407  else if (DB_IS_NULL (src) || (src_str = db_get_string (src)) == NULL)
13408  {
13409  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, db_value_precision (src), 0);
13410  }
13411  else
13412  {
13413  /* Get information from the value. */
13414  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
13415  src_length = db_get_string_size (src);
13416  if (src_length < 0)
13417  {
13418  src_length = strlen (src_str);
13419  }
13420 
13421  /* should we be paying attention to this? it is extremely dangerous */
13422  if (!copy)
13423  {
13424  error = db_make_varnchar (dest, src_precision, src_str, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
13425  db_get_string_collation (src));
13426  }
13427  else
13428  {
13429  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
13430  if (new_ == NULL)
13431  {
13432  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, src_precision, 0);
13433  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
13434  error = er_errid ();
13435  }
13436  else
13437  {
13438  memcpy (new_, src_str, src_length);
13439  new_[src_length] = '\0';
13440  db_make_varnchar (dest, src_precision, new_, src_length, db_get_string_codeset (src),
13441  db_get_string_collation (src));
13442  dest->need_clear = true;
13443  }
13444  }
13445  }
13446 
13447  return error;
13448 }

13487 
13488 /*
13489  * Ignoring precision as byte size is really the only important thing for
13490  * varnchar.
13491  */
13492 static int
13493 mr_lengthval_varnchar_internal (DB_VALUE * value, int disk, int align)
13494 {
13495  int src_size, len, rc = NO_ERROR;
13496  const char *str;
13497  bool is_temporary_data = false;
13498  int compressed_size = 0;
13499 
13500 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13501  INTL_CODESET src_codeset;
13502 #endif
13503 
13504  len = 0;
13505  if (value != NULL && (str = db_get_string (value)) != NULL)
13506  {
13507  src_size = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
13508  if (src_size < 0)
13509  {
13510  src_size = strlen (str);
13511  }
13512 
13513  /* Test and try compression. */
13514  if (!DB_TRIED_COMPRESSION (value))
13515  {
13516  /* It means that the value has never passed through a compression process. */
13517  rc = pr_do_db_value_string_compression (value);
13518  }
13519  /* We are now sure that the value has been through the process of compression */
13520  compressed_size = db_get_compressed_size (value);
13521  /* If the compression was successful, then we use the compression size value */
13522  if (compressed_size > 0)
13523  {
13524  /* Compression successful so we use the compressed_size from the value. */
13525  len = compressed_size + PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
13526  is_temporary_data = true;
13527  }
13528  else
13529  {
13530  /* Compression failed so we use the uncompressed size of the value. */
13531  len = src_size;
13532  }
13533 
13534  if (len >= OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION && is_temporary_data == false)
13535  {
13536  /* The compression failed but the size of the string calls for the new encoding. */
13537  len += PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
13538  is_temporary_data = true;
13539  }
13540 
13541 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13542  src_codeset = (INTL_CODESET) db_get_string_codeset (value);
13543 
13544  /*
13545  * If this is a client side string, and the disk representation length
13546  * is requested, Need to return the length of a converted string.
13547  */
13548  if (!db_on_server && src_size > 0 && disk && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SRVR_STR (src_codeset))
13549  {
13550  int unconverted;
13551  int char_count = db_get_string_length (value);
13552  char *converted_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, src_codeset));
13553 
13554  intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) str, char_count, src_codeset, (unsigned char *) converted_string,
13555  lang_charset (), &unconverted);
13556 
13557  if (converted_string)
13558  {
13559  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) converted_string, (char_count - unconverted), src_codeset, &len);
13560  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, converted_string);
13561  }
13562  }
13563 #endif
13564  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
13565  {
13566  len = or_packed_varchar_length (len);
13567  }
13568  else
13569  {
13570  len = or_varchar_length (len);
13571  }
13572  }
13573 
13574  if (is_temporary_data == true)
13575  {
13576  len -= PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
13577  }
13578 
13579  return len;
13580 }
13581 
13582 static int
13583 mr_writeval_varnchar_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
13584 {
13585  int src_size, size, compressed_size;
13586  INTL_CODESET src_codeset;
13587  char *str, *string, *compressed_string;
13588  int rc = NO_ERROR;
13589 
13590  if (value != NULL && (str = db_get_string (value)) != NULL)
13591  {
13592  src_size = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
13593  if (src_size < 0)
13594  {
13595  src_size = strlen (str);
13596  }
13597 
13598  src_codeset = (INTL_CODESET) db_get_string_codeset (value);
13599 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13600  if (!db_on_server && src_size > 0 && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SRVR_STR (src_codeset))
13601  {
13602  int unconverted;
13603  int char_count = db_get_string_length (value);
13604  char *converted_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, src_codeset));
13605 
13606  (void) intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) str, char_count, src_codeset,
13607  (unsigned char *) converted_string, lang_charset (), &unconverted);
13608 
13609  if (converted_string)
13610  {
13611  intl_char_size ((unsigned char *) converted_string, (char_count - unconverted), src_codeset, &src_size);
13612  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
13613  {
13614  or_packed_put_varchar (buf, converted_string, src_size);
13615  }
13616  else
13617  {
13618  or_put_varchar (buf, converted_string, src_size);
13619  }
13620  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, converted_string);
13621  return rc;
13622  }
13623  }
13624 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
13625 
13626  if (!DB_TRIED_COMPRESSION (value))
13627  {
13628  /* Check for previous compression. */
13629  rc = pr_do_db_value_string_compression (value);
13630  }
13631 
13632  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13633  {
13634  return rc;
13635  }
13636 
13637  compressed_size = db_get_compressed_size (value);
13638  compressed_string = DB_GET_COMPRESSED_STRING (value);
13639 
13640  if (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE && src_size < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
13641  {
13642  rc = pr_write_uncompressed_string_to_buffer (buf, str, src_size, align);
13643  }
13644  else
13645  {
13646  /* String has been prompted to compression before. */
13647  assert (compressed_size != DB_NOT_YET_COMPRESSED);
13648  if (compressed_string == NULL)
13649  {
13650  assert (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE);
13651  string = value->data.ch.medium.buf;
13652  }
13653  else
13654  {
13655  assert (compressed_size > 0);
13656  string = compressed_string;
13657  }
13658  if (compressed_size == DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE)
13659  {
13660  size = 0;
13661  }
13662  else
13663  {
13664  size = compressed_size;
13665  }
13666  rc = pr_write_compressed_string_to_buffer (buf, string, size, src_size, align);
13667  }
13668  }
13669 
13670  return rc;
13671 }
13672 
13673 static int
13674 mr_readval_varnchar_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
13675  int copy_buf_len, int align)
13676 {
13677  int pad, precision;
13678 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13679  INTL_CODESET codeset;
13680 #endif
13681  char *new_ = NULL, *start = NULL, *string = NULL, *compressed_string = NULL;
13682  int str_length, decompressed_size = 0, compressed_size = 0;
13683  char *decompressed_string = NULL;
13684  int rc = NO_ERROR;
13685  bool compressed_need_clear = false;
13686 
13687  if (value == NULL)
13688  {
13689  if (size == -1)
13690  {
13691  rc = or_skip_varchar (buf, align);
13692  }
13693  else
13694  {
13695  if (size)
13696  {
13697  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
13698  }
13699  }
13700  }
13701  else
13702  {
13703  if (domain != NULL)
13704  {
13705  precision = domain->precision;
13706 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13707  codeset = TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain);
13708 #endif
13709  }
13710  else
13711  {
13712  precision = DB_MAX_VARNCHAR_PRECISION;
13713 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13714  codeset = LANG_SYS_CODESET;
13715 #endif
13716  }
13717 
13718  /* Branch according to convention based on size */
13719  if (!copy)
13720  {
13721  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
13722  {
13723  assert (false);
13724  return ER_FAILED;
13725  }
13726 
13727  /* Get the decompressed and compressed size of the string stored in buffer.
13728  * If compressed_size is set to -1, then the string is not compressed at all.
13729  * If compressed_size is set to 0, the string was attempted to be compressed, however it failed.
13730  */
13731  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (buf, &compressed_size, &decompressed_size);
13732  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13733  {
13734  return rc;
13735  }
13736 
13737  if (compressed_size > 0)
13738  {
13739  str_length = compressed_size;
13740  string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, decompressed_size + 1);
13741  if (string == NULL)
13742  {
13743  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
13744  decompressed_size * sizeof (char));
13745  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
13746  return rc;
13747  }
13748 
13749  start = buf->ptr;
13750 
13751  /* Getting data from the buffer. */
13752  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (buf, string, compressed_size, decompressed_size);
13753 
13754  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13755  {
13756  goto cleanup;
13757  }
13758  string[decompressed_size] = '\0';
13759  db_make_varnchar (value, precision, string, decompressed_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13760  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13761  value->need_clear = true;
13762 
13763  compressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, compressed_size + 1);
13764  if (compressed_string == NULL)
13765  {
13766  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
13767  (compressed_size + 1) * sizeof (char));
13768  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
13769  goto cleanup;
13770  }
13771 
13772  memcpy (compressed_string, start, compressed_size);
13773  compressed_string[compressed_size] = '\0';
13774  compressed_need_clear = true;
13775  }
13776  else
13777  {
13778  /* If there is no decompression, then buf->ptr points to the data stored in buffer. */
13779  str_length = decompressed_size;
13780  db_make_varnchar (value, precision, buf->ptr, decompressed_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13781  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13782  value->need_clear = false;
13783  compressed_size = DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE;
13784  }
13785 
13786  db_set_compressed_string (value, compressed_string, compressed_size, compressed_need_clear);
13787 
13788  or_skip_varchar_remainder (buf, str_length, align);
13789  }
13790  else
13791  {
13792  if (size == 0)
13793  {
13794  /* its NULL */
13795  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, precision, 0);
13796  }
13797  else
13798  { /* size != 0 */
13799  if (size == -1)
13800  {
13801  /* Standard packed varnchar with a size prefix */
13802  ; /* do nothing */
13803  }
13804  else
13805  { /* size != -1 */
13806  /* Standard packed varnchar within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the
13807  * disk representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the additional
13808  * padding. */
13809  start = buf->ptr;
13810  } /* size != -1 */
13811 
13812  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (buf, &compressed_size, &decompressed_size);
13813  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13814  {
13815  return ER_FAILED;
13816  }
13817 
13818  if (compressed_size <= 0)
13819  {
13820  assert (compressed_size == 0);
13821  str_length = decompressed_size;
13822  }
13823  else
13824  {
13825  str_length = compressed_size;
13826  }
13827 
13828  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= str_length + 1)
13829  {
13830  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
13831  new_ = copy_buf;
13832  }
13833  else
13834  {
13835  /*
13836  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge
13837  * NULL terminator
13838  */
13839  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str_length + 1);
13840  }
13841 
13842  if (new_ == NULL)
13843  {
13844  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
13845  if (domain)
13846  {
13847  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
13848  }
13849  or_abort (buf);
13850  return ER_FAILED;
13851  }
13852  else
13853  {
13854  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
13855  {
13856  /* read the kludge NULL terminator */
13857  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, str_length + 1);
13858  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
13859  {
13860  /* round up to a word boundary */
13861  rc = or_get_align32 (buf);
13862  }
13863  }
13864  else
13865  {
13866  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, str_length);
13867  }
13868 
13869  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13870  {
13871  if (new_ != copy_buf)
13872  {
13873  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
13874  }
13875  return ER_FAILED;
13876  }
13877 
13878  if (compressed_size > 0)
13879  {
13880  /* String was compressed */
13881  lzo_uint decompression_size = 0;
13882 
13883  assert (decompressed_size > 0);
13884 
13885  /* Handle decompression */
13886  decompressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, decompressed_size + 1);
13887 
13888  if (decompressed_string == NULL)
13889  {
13890  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
13891  (size_t) decompressed_size * sizeof (char));
13892  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
13893  goto cleanup;
13894  }
13895 
13896  /* decompressing the string */
13897  rc = lzo1x_decompress ((lzo_bytep) new_, (lzo_uint) compressed_size,
13898  (lzo_bytep) decompressed_string, &decompression_size, NULL);
13899  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
13900  {
13901  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL, 0);
13902  rc = ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL;
13903  goto cleanup;
13904  }
13905 
13906  if (decompression_size != (lzo_uint) decompressed_size)
13907  {
13908  /* Decompression failed. It shouldn't. */
13909  assert (false);
13910  }
13911  /* The compressed string stored in buf is now decompressed in decompressed_string
13912  * and is needed now to be copied over new_. */
13913 
13914  compressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, compressed_size + 1);
13915  if (compressed_string == NULL)
13916  {
13917  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
13918  (size_t) (compressed_size + 1) * sizeof (char));
13919  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
13920  goto cleanup;
13921  }
13922 
13923  memcpy (compressed_string, new_, compressed_size);
13924  compressed_string[compressed_size] = '\0';
13925  compressed_need_clear = true;
13926 
13927  if (new_ != copy_buf)
13928  {
13929  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
13930  }
13931 
13932  new_ = decompressed_string;
13933  str_length = decompressed_size;
13934  }
13935 
13936  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
13937  {
13938  rc = ER_FAILED;
13939  goto cleanup;
13940  }
13941 
13942  new_[str_length] = '\0';
13943  db_make_varnchar (value, precision, new_, str_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain),
13944  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13945  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
13946 
13947  if (compressed_string == NULL)
13948  {
13949  compressed_size = DB_UNCOMPRESSABLE;
13950  compressed_need_clear = false;
13951  }
13952 
13953  db_set_compressed_string (value, compressed_string, compressed_size, compressed_need_clear);
13954 
13955  if (size == -1)
13956  {
13957  /* Standard packed varnchar with a size prefix */
13958  ; /* do nothing */
13959  }
13960  else
13961  { /* size != -1 */
13962  /* Standard packed varnchar within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the
13963  * disk representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the
13964  * additional padding. */
13965  pad = size - (int) (buf->ptr - start);
13966  if (pad > 0)
13967  {
13968  rc = or_advance (buf, pad);
13969  }
13970  } /* size != -1 */
13971  } /* else */
13972  } /* size != 0 */
13973  }
13974 
13975  /* Check if conversion needs to be done */
13976 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
13977  if (!db_on_server && DO_CONVERSION_TO_SQLTEXT (codeset) && !DB_IS_NULL (value))
13978  {
13979  int unconverted;
13980  int char_count;
13981  char *temp_string = db_get_nchar (value, &char_count);
13982 
13983  if (char_count > 0)
13984  {
13985  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, STR_SIZE (char_count, codeset));
13986  (void) intl_convert_charset ((unsigned char *) temp_string, char_count, codeset, (unsigned char *) new_,
13987  LANG_SYS_CODESET, &unconverted);
13988  db_value_clear (value);
13989  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
13990  {
13991  rc = ER_FAILED;
13992  goto cleanup;
13993  }
13994  db_make_varnchar (value, precision, new_, STR_SIZE (char_count, codeset), codeset,
13995  TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
13996  value->need_clear = true;
13997  }
13998  }
13999 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */
14000  }
14001 
14002 cleanup:
14003  if (decompressed_string != NULL && rc != NO_ERROR)
14004  {
14005  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, decompressed_string);
14006  }
14007 
14008  if (new_ != NULL && new_ != copy_buf && rc != NO_ERROR)
14009  {
14010  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
14011  }
14012 
14013  if (rc != NO_ERROR && compressed_string != NULL)
14014  {
14015  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, compressed_string);
14016  }
14017  return rc;
14018 }
14019 
14020 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14021 mr_index_cmpdisk_varnchar (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order,
14022  int *start_colp)
14023 {
14024  assert (domain != NULL);
14025 
14026  return mr_data_cmpdisk_varnchar (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp);
14027 }

14029 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14030 mr_data_cmpdisk_varnchar (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
14031 {
14032  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c = DB_UNK;
14033  char *str1, *str2;
14034  int str_length1, str1_compressed_length = 0, str1_decompressed_length = 0;
14035  int str_length2, str2_compressed_length = 0, str2_decompressed_length = 0;
14036  OR_BUF buf1, buf2;
14037  char *string1 = NULL, *string2 = NULL;
14038  bool alloced_string1 = false, alloced_string2 = false;
14039  int rc = NO_ERROR;
14040  int strc;
14041 
14042  assert (domain != NULL);
14043 
14044  str1 = (char *) mem1;
14045  str2 = (char *) mem2;
14046 
14047  /* generally, data is short enough */
14048  str_length1 = OR_GET_BYTE (str1);
14049  str_length2 = OR_GET_BYTE (str2);
14050  if (str_length1 < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION && str_length2 < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
14051  {
14052  str1 += OR_BYTE_SIZE;
14053  str2 += OR_BYTE_SIZE;
14054  strc = QSTR_NCHAR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) str1, str_length1, (unsigned char *) str2,
14055  str_length2, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14056  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
14057  return c;
14058  }
14059 
14060  assert (str_length1 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION
14061  || str_length2 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
14062 
14063  /* String 1 */
14064  or_init (&buf1, str1, 0);
14065  if (str_length1 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
14066  {
14067  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (&buf1, &str1_compressed_length, &str1_decompressed_length);
14068  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14069  {
14070  goto cleanup;
14071  }
14072 
14073  string1 = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str1_decompressed_length + 1);
14074  if (string1 == NULL)
14075  {
14076  /* Error report */
14077  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, str1_decompressed_length);
14078  goto cleanup;
14079  }
14080  alloced_string1 = true;
14081 
14082  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (&buf1, string1, str1_compressed_length, str1_decompressed_length);
14083  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14084  {
14085  goto cleanup;
14086  }
14087 
14088  str_length1 = str1_decompressed_length;
14089  string1[str_length1] = '\0';
14090  }
14091  else
14092  {
14093  /* Skip the size byte */
14094  string1 = buf1.ptr + OR_BYTE_SIZE;
14095  }
14096 
14097  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14098  {
14099  ASSERT_ERROR ();
14100  goto cleanup;
14101  }
14102 
14103  /* String 2 */
14104  or_init (&buf2, str2, 0);
14105  if (str_length2 == OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
14106  {
14107  rc = or_get_varchar_compression_lengths (&buf2, &str2_compressed_length, &str2_decompressed_length);
14108  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14109  {
14110  goto cleanup;
14111  }
14112 
14113  string2 = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str2_decompressed_length + 1);
14114  if (string2 == NULL)
14115  {
14116  /* Error report */
14117  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, str2_decompressed_length);
14118  goto cleanup;
14119  }
14120 
14121  alloced_string2 = true;
14122 
14123  rc = pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (&buf2, string2, str2_compressed_length, str2_decompressed_length);
14124  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14125  {
14126  goto cleanup;
14127  }
14128 
14129  str_length2 = str2_decompressed_length;
14130  string2[str_length2] = '\0';
14131  }
14132  else
14133  {
14134  /* Skip the size byte */
14135  string2 = buf2.ptr + OR_BYTE_SIZE;
14136  }
14137 
14138  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14139  {
14140  ASSERT_ERROR ();
14141  goto cleanup;
14142  }
14143 
14144  /* Compare the strings */
14145  strc = QSTR_NCHAR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, (unsigned char *) string1, str_length1, (unsigned char *) string2,
14146  str_length2, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14147  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
14148  /* Clean up the strings */
14149  if (string1 != NULL && alloced_string1 == true)
14150  {
14151  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string1);
14152  }
14153 
14154  if (string2 != NULL && alloced_string2 == true)
14155  {
14156  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string2);
14157  }
14158 
14159  return c;
14160 
14161 cleanup:
14162  if (string1 != NULL && alloced_string1 == true)
14163  {
14164  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string1);
14165  }
14166 
14167  if (string2 != NULL && alloced_string2 == true)
14168  {
14169  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, string2);
14170  }
14171 
14172  return DB_UNK;
14173 }

14175 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14176 mr_cmpval_varnchar (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
14177  int collation)
14178 {
14179  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
14180  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
14181  int strc;
14182 
14183  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
14184  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
14185 
14186  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL || db_get_string_codeset (value1) != db_get_string_codeset (value1))
14187  {
14188  return DB_UNK;
14189  }
14190 
14191  if (collation == -1)
14192  {
14193  assert (false);
14194  return DB_UNK;
14195  }
14196 
14197  strc = QSTR_NCHAR_COMPARE (collation, string1, (int) db_get_string_size (value1), string2,
14198  (int) db_get_string_size (value2), db_get_string_codeset (value2));
14199  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (strc);
14200 
14201  return c;
14202 }

14224  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);

14262  * TYPE BIT

14264 
14265 static void
14266 mr_initmem_bit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
14267 {
14268 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
14269  int mem_length;
14270 
14271  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
14272  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14273 
14274  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14275  memset (memptr, 0, mem_length);
14276 #endif
14277 }
14278 
14279 
14280 /*
14281  * Due to the "within tolerance" comparison of domains used for
14282  * assignment validation, we may get values in here whose precision is
14283  * less than the precision of the actual attribute. This prevents
14284  * having to copy a string just to coerce a value into a larger precision.
14285  * Note that the precision of the source value may also come in as -1 here
14286  * which is used to mean a "floating" precision that is assumed to be
14287  * compatible with the destination domain as long as the associated value
14288  * is within tolerance. This case is generally only seen for string
14289  * literals that have been produced by the parser. These literals will
14290  * not contain blank padding and strlen() or db_get_string_size() can be
14291  * used to determine the number of significant characters.
14292  */
14293 static int
14294 mr_setmem_bit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
14295 {
14296  int error = NO_ERROR;
14297  char *src, *mem;
14298  int src_precision, src_length, mem_length, pad;
14299 
14300  if (value == NULL)
14301  {
14302  return NO_ERROR;
14303  }
14304 
14305  /* Get information from the value */
14306  src = db_get_string (value);
14307  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
14308  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
14309 
14310  if (src == NULL)
14311  {
14312  return NO_ERROR;
14313  }
14314 
14315  /*
14316  * The only thing we really care about at this point, is the byte
14317  * length of the string. The precision could be checked here but it
14318  * really isn't necessary for this operation.
14319  * Calculate the maximum number of bytes we have available here.
14320  */
14321  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14322  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14323 
14324  if (mem_length < src_length)
14325  {
14326  /*
14327  * should never get here, this is supposed to be caught during domain
14328  * validation, need a better error message.
14329  */
14330  error = ER_OBJ_DOMAIN_CONFLICT;
14331  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "");
14332  }
14333  else
14334  {
14335  /* copy the value into memory */
14336  mem = (char *) memptr;
14337  memcpy (mem, src, src_length);
14338 
14339  /* Check for padding */
14340  pad = mem_length - src_length;
14341  if (pad)
14342  {
14343  int i;
14344 
14345  for (i = src_length; i < mem_length; i++)
14346  {
14347  mem[i] = '\0';
14348  }
14349  }
14350  }
14351 
14352  return error;
14353 }
14354 
14355 static int
14356 mr_getmem_bit (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
14357 {
14358  int mem_length;
14359  char *new_;
14360 
14361  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14362  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14363 
14364  if (!copy)
14365  {
14366  new_ = (char *) mem;
14367  }
14368  else
14369  {
14370  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
14371  if (new_ == NULL)
14372  {
14373  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14374  return er_errid ();
14375  }
14376  memcpy (new_, (char *) mem, mem_length);
14377  }
14378 
14379  db_make_bit (value, domain->precision, new_, domain->precision);
14380  if (copy)
14381  {
14382  value->need_clear = true;
14383  }
14384 
14385  return NO_ERROR;
14386 }

14388 static int
14389 mr_data_lengthmem_bit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
14390 {
14391  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision));
14392  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14393 
14394  /* There is no difference between the disk & memory sizes. */
14395  return STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14396 }
14397 
14398 static void
14399 mr_data_writemem_bit (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
14400 {
14401  int mem_length;
14402 
14403  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14404  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14405 
14406  /*
14407  * We simply dump the memory image to disk, it will already have been padded.
14408  * If this were a national character string, at this point, we'd have to
14409  * decide now to perform a character set conversion.
14410  */
14411  or_put_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
14412 }
14413 
14414 static void
14415 mr_data_readmem_bit (OR_BUF * buf, void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
14416 {
14417  int mem_length, padding;
14418 
14419  if (mem == NULL)
14420  {
14421  /* If we passed in a size, then use it. Otherwise, determine the size from the domain. */
14422  if (size > 0)
14423  {
14424  or_advance (buf, size);
14425  }
14426  else
14427  {
14428  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14429  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14430  or_advance (buf, mem_length);
14431  }
14432  }
14433  else
14434  {
14435  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14436  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14437  if (size != -1 && mem_length > size)
14438  {
14439  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
14440  or_abort (buf);
14441  }
14442  or_get_data (buf, (char *) mem, mem_length);
14443 
14444  /*
14445  * We should only see padding if the string is contained within a packed
14446  * value that had extra padding to ensure alignment. If we see these,
14447  * just pop them out of the buffer. This shouldn't ever happen for the
14448  * "getmem" function, only for the "getval" function.
14449  */
14450  if (size != -1)
14451  {
14452  padding = size - mem_length;
14453  if (padding > 0)
14454  {
14455  or_advance (buf, padding);
14456  }
14457  }
14458  }
14459 }

14461 static void
14462 mr_freemem_bit (void *memptr)
14463 {
14464 }
14465 
14466 static void
14467 mr_initval_bit (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)
14468 {
14469  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_BIT, precision, scale);
14470 }
14471 
14472 static int
14473 mr_setval_bit (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
14474 {
14475  int error = NO_ERROR;
14476  int src_precision, src_length, src_number_of_bits = 0;
14477  char *src_string, *new_;
14478 
14479  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
14480  if (src == NULL || (DB_IS_NULL (src) && db_value_precision (src) == 0))
14481  {
14482  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_BIT, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
14483  }
14484  else if (DB_IS_NULL (src))
14485  {
14486  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_BIT, db_value_precision (src), 0);
14487  }
14488  else
14489  {
14490  /* Get information from the value */
14491  src_string = db_get_bit (src, &src_number_of_bits);
14492  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
14493  src_length = db_get_string_size (src); /* size in bytes */
14494 
14495  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_BIT, src_precision, 0);
14496 
14497  /* shouldn't see a NULL string at this point, treat as NULL */
14498  if (src_string != NULL)
14499  {
14500  if (!copy)
14501  {
14502  db_make_bit (dest, src_precision, src_string, src_number_of_bits);
14503  }
14504  else
14505  {
14506 
14507  /* make sure the copy gets a NULL terminator */
14508  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
14509  if (new_ == NULL)
14510  {
14511  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14512  error = er_errid ();
14513  }
14514  else
14515  {
14516  memcpy (new_, src_string, src_length);
14517  db_make_bit (dest, src_precision, new_, src_number_of_bits);
14518  dest->need_clear = true;
14519  }
14520  }
14521  }
14522  }
14523  return error;
14524 }
14525 
14526 static int
14527 mr_index_lengthmem_bit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
14528 {
14529  int mem_length;
14530 
14531  assert (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision) || memptr != NULL);
14532  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14533 
14534  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
14535  {
14536  mem_length = domain->precision;
14537 
14538  return STR_SIZE (mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14539  }
14540  else
14541  {
14542  memcpy (&mem_length, memptr, OR_INT_SIZE);
14543 
14544  return STR_SIZE (mem_length, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain)) + OR_INT_SIZE;
14545  }
14546 
14547 }
14548 
14549 static int
14550 mr_index_lengthval_bit (DB_VALUE * value)
14551 {
14552  return mr_data_lengthval_bit (value, 1);
14553 }
14554 
14555 static int
14556 mr_data_lengthval_bit (DB_VALUE * value, int disk)
14557 {
14558  int packed_length, src_precision;
14559  char *src;
14560 
14561  src = db_get_string (value);
14562  if (src == NULL)
14563  {
14564  return 0;
14565  }
14566 
14567  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
14568  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
14569  {
14570  assert (db_get_string_codeset (value) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14571  packed_length = STR_SIZE (src_precision, db_get_string_codeset (value));
14572  }
14573  else
14574  {
14575  /*
14576  * Precision is "floating", calculate the effective precision based on the
14577  * string length.
14578  */
14579  packed_length = db_get_string_size (value);
14580 
14581  /* add in storage for a size prefix on the packed value. */
14582  packed_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
14583  }
14584 
14585  /*
14586  * NOTE: We do NOT perform padding here, if this is used in the context
14587  * of a packed value, the or_put_value() family of functions must handle
14588  * their own padding, this is because "lengthval" and "writeval" can be
14589  * used to place values into the disk representation of instances and
14590  * there can be no padding in there.
14591  */
14592 
14593  return packed_length;
14594 }
14595
