14597 static int
14598 mr_index_writeval_bit (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
14599 {
14600  return mr_writeval_bit_internal (buf, value, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);
14601 }
14602 
14603 /*
14604  * See commentary in mr_data_lengthval_bit.
14605  */
14606 static int
14607 mr_data_writeval_bit (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
14608 {
14609  return mr_writeval_bit_internal (buf, value, INT_ALIGNMENT);
14610 }
14611 
14612 static int
14613 mr_writeval_bit_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
14614 {
14615  int src_precision, src_length, packed_length, pad;
14616  char *src;
14617  int rc = NO_ERROR;
14618 
14619  src = db_get_string (value);
14620  if (src == NULL)
14621  {
14622  return rc;
14623  }
14624 
14625  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
14626  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
14627 
14628  if (!IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (src_precision))
14629  {
14630  assert (db_get_string_codeset (value) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14631  packed_length = STR_SIZE (src_precision, db_get_string_codeset (value));
14632 
14633  if (packed_length < src_length)
14634  {
14635  /* should have caught this by now, truncate silently */
14636  or_put_data (buf, src, packed_length);
14637  }
14638  else
14639  {
14640  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, src_length);
14641  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
14642  {
14643  /* Check for padding */
14644  pad = packed_length - src_length;
14645  if (pad)
14646  {
14647  int i;
14648 
14649  for (i = src_length; i < packed_length; i++)
14650  {
14651  rc = or_put_byte (buf, (int) '\0');
14652  }
14653  }
14654  }
14655  }
14656  }
14657  else
14658  {
14659  /*
14660  * This is a "floating" precision value. Pack what we can based on the
14661  * string size. Note that for this to work, this can only be packed
14662  * as part of a domain tagged value and we must include a length
14663  * prefix after the domain.
14664  */
14665  packed_length = db_get_string_length (value);
14666 
14667  /* store the size prefix */
14668  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
14669  {
14670  rc = or_put_int (buf, packed_length);
14671  }
14672  else
14673  {
14674  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) (&packed_length), OR_INT_SIZE);
14675  }
14676 
14677  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
14678  {
14679  /* store the data */
14680  rc = or_put_data (buf, src, BITS_TO_BYTES (packed_length));
14681  /* there is no blank padding in this case */
14682  }
14683  }
14684 
14685  return rc;
14686 }
14687 
14688 static int
14689 mr_index_readval_bit (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
14690  int copy_buf_len)
14691 {
14692  return mr_readval_bit_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, CHAR_ALIGNMENT);
14693 }
14694 
14695 static int
14696 mr_data_readval_bit (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
14697  int copy_buf_len)
14698 {
14699  return mr_readval_bit_internal (buf, value, domain, disk_size, copy, copy_buf, copy_buf_len, INT_ALIGNMENT);
14700 }
14701 
14702 static int
14703 mr_readval_bit_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk_size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
14704  int copy_buf_len, int align)
14705 {
14706  int mem_length, padding;
14707  int bit_length;
14708  char *new_;
14709  int rc = NO_ERROR;
14710 
14711  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
14712  {
14713  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
14714  {
14715  bit_length = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
14716  }
14717  else
14718  {
14719  rc = or_get_data (buf, (char *) (&bit_length), OR_INT_SIZE);
14720  }
14721  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14722  {
14723  return ER_FAILED;
14724  }
14725 
14726  mem_length = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_length);
14727  if (value == NULL)
14728  {
14729  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
14730  }
14731  else if (!copy)
14732  {
14733  db_make_bit (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, buf->ptr, bit_length);
14734  value->need_clear = false;
14735  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
14736  }
14737  else
14738  {
14739  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
14740  {
14741  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
14742  new_ = copy_buf;
14743  }
14744  else
14745  {
14746  /*
14747  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
14748  * terminator
14749  */
14750  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
14751  }
14752 
14753  if (new_ == NULL)
14754  {
14755  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
14756  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
14757  or_abort (buf);
14758 
14759  return ER_FAILED;
14760  }
14761  else
14762  {
14763  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
14764  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14765  {
14766  if (new_ != copy_buf)
14767  {
14768  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
14769  }
14770 
14771  return rc;
14772  }
14773  new_[mem_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
14774  db_make_bit (value, TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, new_, bit_length);
14775  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
14776  }
14777  }
14778  }
14779  else
14780  {
14781  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14782  mem_length = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14783 
14784  if (disk_size != -1 && mem_length > disk_size)
14785  {
14786  /*
14787  * If we're low here, we could just read what we have and make a
14788  * smaller value. Still the domain should match at this point.
14789  */
14790  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
14791  or_abort (buf);
14792 
14793  return ER_FAILED;
14794  }
14795 
14796  if (value == NULL)
14797  {
14798  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
14799  }
14800  else if (!copy)
14801  {
14802  db_make_bit (value, domain->precision, buf->ptr, domain->precision);
14803  value->need_clear = false;
14804  rc = or_advance (buf, mem_length);
14805  }
14806  else
14807  {
14808  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= mem_length + 1)
14809  {
14810  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
14811  new_ = copy_buf;
14812  }
14813  else
14814  {
14815  /*
14816  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
14817  * terminator
14818  */
14819  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length + 1);
14820  }
14821 
14822  if (new_ == NULL)
14823  {
14824  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
14825  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), domain->precision, 0);
14826  or_abort (buf);
14827 
14828  return ER_FAILED;
14829  }
14830  else
14831  {
14832  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, mem_length);
14833  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
14834  {
14835  if (new_ != copy_buf)
14836  {
14837  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
14838  }
14839 
14840  return rc;
14841  }
14842  new_[mem_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
14843  db_make_bit (value, domain->precision, new_, domain->precision);
14844  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
14845  }
14846  }
14847  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
14848  {
14849  /*
14850  * We should only see padding if the string is contained within a
14851  * packed value that had extra padding to ensure alignment. If we see
14852  * these, just pop them out of the buffer.
14853  */
14854  if (disk_size != -1)
14855  {
14856  padding = disk_size - mem_length;
14857  if (padding > 0)
14858  {
14859  rc = or_advance (buf, padding);
14860  }
14861  }
14862  }
14863  }
14864 
14865  return rc;
14866 }

14872

14878 {
14879  assert (domain != NULL);
14880 
14881  return mr_cmpdisk_bit_internal (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp, INT_ALIGNMENT);
14882 }
14883 
14884 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14885 mr_cmpdisk_bit_internal (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
14886  int align)
14887 {
14888  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
14889  int bit_length1, mem_length1, bit_length2, mem_length2, bitc;
14890 
14891  if (IS_FLOATING_PRECISION (domain->precision))
14892  {
14893  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
14894  {
14895  bit_length1 = OR_GET_INT (mem1);
14896  bit_length2 = OR_GET_INT (mem2);
14897  }
14898  else
14899  {
14900  memcpy (&bit_length1, mem1, OR_INT_SIZE);
14901  memcpy (&bit_length2, mem2, OR_INT_SIZE);
14902  }
14903  mem1 = (char *) mem1 + OR_INT_SIZE;
14904  mem_length1 = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_length1);
14905  mem2 = (char *) mem2 + OR_INT_SIZE;
14906  mem_length2 = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_length2);
14907  }
14908  else
14909  {
14910  assert (TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain) == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BITS);
14911  mem_length1 = mem_length2 = STR_SIZE (domain->precision, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain));
14912  }
14913 
14914  bitc = bit_compare ((unsigned char *) mem1, mem_length1, (unsigned char *) mem2, mem_length2);
14915  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
14916 
14917  return c;
14918 }
14919 
14920 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14921 mr_cmpval_bit (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp, int collation)
14922 {
14923  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
14924  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
14925  int bitc;
14926 
14927  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
14928  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
14929 
14930  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
14931  {
14932  return DB_UNK;
14933  }
14934 
14935  bitc = bit_compare (string1, (int) db_get_string_size (value1), string2, (int) db_get_string_size (value2));
14936  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
14937 
14938  return c;
14939 }
14940 
14941 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
14942 mr_cmpval_bit2 (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int length, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
14943 {
14944  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
14945  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
14946  int len1, len2, string_size;
14947  int bitc;
14948 
14949  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
14950  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
14951 
14952  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
14953  {
14954  return DB_UNK;
14955  }
14956 
14957  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
14958  len1 = MIN (string_size, length);
14959  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
14960  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);
14961 
14962  bitc = bit_compare (string1, len1, string2, len2);
14963  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
14964 
14965  return c;
14966 }

14996 /*
14997  * TYPE VARBIT
14998  */
14999 
15000 static void
15001 mr_initmem_varbit (void *mem, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
15002 {
15003  *(char **) mem = NULL;
15004 }
15005 
15006 
15007 /*
15008  * The main difference between "memory" strings and "value" strings is that
15009  * the length tag is stored as an in-line prefix in the memory block allocated
15010  * to hold the string characters.
15011  */
15012 static int
15013 mr_setmem_varbit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value)
15014 {
15015  int error = NO_ERROR;
15016  char *src, *cur, *new_, **mem;
15017  int src_precision, src_length, src_length_bits, new_length;
15018 
15019  /* get the current memory contents */
15020  mem = (char **) memptr;
15021  cur = *mem;
15022 
15023  if (value == NULL || (src = db_get_string (value)) == NULL)
15024  {
15025  /* remove the current value */
15026  if (cur != NULL)
15027  {
15028  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
15029  mr_initmem_varbit (memptr, domain);
15030  }
15031  }
15032  else
15033  {
15034  /*
15035  * Get information from the value. Ignore precision for the time being
15036  * since we really only care about the byte size of the value for varbit.
15037  * Whether or not the value "fits" should have been checked by now.
15038  */
15039  src_precision = db_value_precision (value);
15040  src_length = db_get_string_size (value); /* size in bytes */
15041  src_length_bits = db_get_string_length (value); /* size in bits */
15042 
15043  new_length = src_length + sizeof (int);
15044  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, new_length);
15045  if (new_ == NULL)
15046  {
15047  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15048  error = er_errid ();
15049  }
15050  else
15051  {
15052  if (cur != NULL)
15053  {
15054  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
15055  }
15056 
15057  /* pack in the length prefix */
15058  *(int *) new_ = src_length_bits;
15059  cur = new_ + sizeof (int);
15060  /* store the string */
15061  memcpy (cur, src, src_length);
15062  *mem = new_;
15063  }
15064  }
15065 
15066  return error;
15067 }
15068 
15069 static int
15070 mr_getmem_varbit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, DB_VALUE * value, bool copy)
15071 {
15072  int error = NO_ERROR;
15073  int mem_bit_length;
15074  char **mem, *cur, *new_;
15075 
15076  /* get to the current value */
15077  mem = (char **) memptr;
15078  cur = *mem;
15079 
15080  if (cur == NULL)
15081  {
15082  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARBIT, domain->precision, 0);
15083  value->need_clear = false;
15084  }
15085  else
15086  {
15087  /* extract the length prefix and the pointer to the actual string data */
15088  mem_bit_length = *(int *) cur;
15089  cur += sizeof (int);
15090 
15091  if (!copy)
15092  {
15093  db_make_varbit (value, domain->precision, cur, mem_bit_length);
15094  value->need_clear = false;
15095  }
15096  else
15097  {
15098  /* return it */
15099  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, BITS_TO_BYTES (mem_bit_length) + 1);
15100  if (new_ == NULL)
15101  {
15102  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15103  error = er_errid ();
15104  }
15105  else
15106  {
15107  memcpy (new_, cur, BITS_TO_BYTES (mem_bit_length));
15108  db_make_varbit (value, domain->precision, new_, mem_bit_length);
15109  value->need_clear = true;
15110  }
15111  }
15112  }
15113 
15114  return error;
15115 }

15118 /*
15119  * For the disk representation, we may be adding pad bytes
15120  * to round up to a word boundary.
15121  */
15122 static int
15123 mr_data_lengthmem_varbit (void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int disk)
15124 {
15125  char **mem, *cur;
15126  int len;
15127 
15128  len = 0;
15129  if (!disk)
15130  {
15131  len = tp_VarBit.size;
15132  }
15133  else if (memptr != NULL)
15134  {
15135  mem = (char **) memptr;
15136  cur = *mem;
15137  if (cur != NULL)
15138  {
15139  len = *(int *) cur;
15140  len = or_packed_varbit_length (len);
15141  }
15142  }
15143 
15144  return len;
15145 }

15161 static void
15162 mr_data_writemem_varbit (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
15163 {
15164  char **mem, *cur;
15165  int bitlen;
15166 
15167  mem = (char **) memptr;
15168  cur = *mem;
15169  if (cur != NULL)
15170  {
15171  bitlen = *(int *) cur;
15172  cur += sizeof (int);
15173  or_packed_put_varbit (buf, cur, bitlen);
15174  }
15175 }
15176 
15177 
15178 /*
15179  * The amount of memory requested is currently calculated based on the
15180  * stored size prefix. If we ever go to a system where we avoid storing the
15181  * size, then we could use the size argument passed in to this function but
15182  * that may also include any padding byte that added to bring us up to a word
15183  * boundary. Might want some way to determine which bytes at the end of a
15184  * string are padding.
15185  */
15186 static void
15187 mr_data_readmem_varbit (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
15188 {
15189  char **mem, *cur, *new_;
15190  int bit_len;
15191  int mem_length, pad;
15192  char *start;
15193  int rc = NO_ERROR;
15194 
15195  /* Must have an explicit size here - can't be determined from the domain */
15196  if (size < 0)
15197  {
15198  return;
15199  }
15200 
15201  if (memptr == NULL)
15202  {
15203  if (size)
15204  {
15205  or_advance (buf, size);
15206  }
15207  }
15208  else
15209  {
15210  mem = (char **) memptr;
15211  cur = *mem;
15212  /* should we be checking for existing strings ? */
15213 #if 0
15214  if (cur != NULL)
15215  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
15216 #endif
15217 
15218  new_ = NULL;
15219  if (size)
15220  {
15221  start = buf->ptr;
15222 
15223  /* KLUDGE, we have some knowledge of how the thing is stored here in order have some control over the
15224  * conversion between the packed length prefix and the full word memory length prefix. Might want to put this
15225  * in another specialized or_ function. */
15226 
15227  /* Get just the length prefix. */
15228  bit_len = or_get_varbit_length (buf, &rc);
15229 
15230  /*
15231  * Allocate storage for this string, including our own full word size
15232  * prefix.
15233  */
15234  mem_length = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_len) + sizeof (int);
15235 
15236  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, mem_length);
15237  if (new_ == NULL)
15238  {
15239  or_abort (buf);
15240  }
15241  else
15242  {
15243  /* store the length in our memory prefix */
15244  *(int *) new_ = bit_len;
15245  cur = new_ + sizeof (int);
15246 
15247  /* read the string */
15248  or_get_data (buf, cur, BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_len));
15249  /* align like or_get_varchar */
15250  or_get_align32 (buf);
15251  }
15252 
15253  /*
15254  * If we were given a size, check to see if for some reason this is
15255  * larger than the already word aligned string that we have now
15256  * extracted. This shouldn't be the case but since we've got a
15257  * length, we may as well obey it.
15258  */
15259  pad = size - (int) (buf->ptr - start);
15260  if (pad > 0)
15261  {
15262  or_advance (buf, pad);
15263  }
15264  }
15265  *mem = new_;
15266  }
15267 }
15268 
15269 static void
15270 mr_freemem_varbit (void *memptr)
15271 {
15272  char *cur;
15273 
15274  if (memptr != NULL)
15275  {
15276  cur = *(char **) memptr;
15277  if (cur != NULL)
15278  {
15279  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, cur);
15280  }
15281  }
15282 }

15285 mr_initval_varbit (DB_VALUE * value, int precision, int scale)

15288  value->need_clear = false;
15289 }

15291 static int
15292 mr_setval_varbit (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
15293 {
15294  int error = NO_ERROR;
15295  int src_precision, src_length, src_bit_length;
15296  char *src_str, *new_;
15297 
15298  assert (!db_value_is_corrupted (src));
15299  if (src == NULL || (DB_IS_NULL (src) && db_value_precision (src) == 0))
15300  {
15301  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARBIT, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0);
15302  }
15303  else if (DB_IS_NULL (src) || (src_str = db_get_string (src)) == NULL)
15304  {
15305  error = db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARBIT, db_value_precision (src), 0);
15306  }
15307  else
15308  {
15309  /* Get information from the value. */
15310  src_precision = db_value_precision (src);
15311  src_length = db_get_string_size (src);
15312  src_bit_length = db_get_string_length (src);
15313 
15314  /* should we be paying attention to this? it is extremely dangerous */
15315  if (!copy)
15316  {
15317  error = db_make_varbit (dest, src_precision, src_str, src_bit_length);
15318  }
15319  else
15320  {
15321  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, src_length + 1);
15322  if (new_ == NULL)
15323  {
15324  db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_VARBIT, src_precision, 0);
15325  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15326  error = er_errid ();
15327  }
15328  else
15329  {
15330  memcpy (new_, src_str, src_length);
15331  db_make_varbit (dest, src_precision, new_, src_bit_length);
15332  dest->need_clear = true;
15333  }
15334  }
15335  }
15336 
15337  return error;
15338 }

15378 static int
15379 mr_lengthval_varbit_internal (DB_VALUE * value, int disk, int align)
15380 {

15383

15385  if (value != NULL && (str = db_get_string (value)) != NULL)
15386  {

15388

15390  {

15392  }
15393  else
15394  {
15395  len = or_varbit_length (bit_length);
15396  }

15402 static int
15403 mr_writeval_varbit_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, int align)
15404 {
15405  int src_bit_length;
15406  char *str;
15407  int rc = NO_ERROR;
15408 
15409  if (value != NULL && (str = db_get_string (value)) != NULL)
15410  {
15411  src_bit_length = db_get_string_length (value); /* size in bits */
15412 
15413  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
15414  {
15415  rc = or_packed_put_varbit (buf, str, src_bit_length);
15416  }
15417  else
15418  {
15419  rc = or_put_varbit (buf, str, src_bit_length);
15420  }
15421  }
15422 
15423  return rc;
15424 }
15425 
15426 /*
15427  * Size can come in as negative here to create a value with a pointer
15428  * directly to disk.
15429  *
15430  * Note that we have a potential conflict with this as -1 is a valid size
15431  * to use here when the string has been packed with a domain/length prefix
15432  * and we can determine the size from there. In current practice, this
15433  * isn't a problem because due to word alignment, we'll never get a
15434  * negative size here that is greater than -4.
15435  */
15436 static int
15437 mr_readval_varbit_internal (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size, bool copy, char *copy_buf,
15438  int copy_buf_len, int align)
15439 {
15440  int pad, precision;
15441  int str_bit_length, str_length;
15442  char *new_, *start = NULL;
15443  int rc = NO_ERROR;
15444 
15445  if (value == NULL)
15446  {
15447  if (size == -1)
15448  {
15449  rc = or_skip_varbit (buf, align);
15450  }
15451  else
15452  {
15453  if (size)
15454  rc = or_advance (buf, size);
15455  }
15456  }
15457  else
15458  {
15459  if (domain != NULL)
15460  {
15461  precision = domain->precision;
15462  }
15463  else
15464  {
15465  precision = DB_MAX_VARBIT_PRECISION;
15466  }
15467 
15468  if (!copy)
15469  {
15470  str_bit_length = or_get_varbit_length (buf, &rc);
15471  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
15472  {
15473  db_make_varbit (value, precision, buf->ptr, str_bit_length);
15474  value->need_clear = false;
15475  rc = or_skip_varbit_remainder (buf, str_bit_length, align);
15476  }
15477  }
15478  else
15479  {
15480  if (size == 0)
15481  {
15482  /* its NULL */
15483  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_VARBIT, precision, 0);
15484  }
15485  else
15486  { /* size != 0 */
15487  if (size == -1)
15488  {
15489  /* Standard packed varbit with a size prefix */
15490  ; /* do nothing */
15491  }
15492  else
15493  { /* size != -1 */
15494  /* Standard packed varbit within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the disk
15495  * representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the additional
15496  * padding. */
15497  start = buf->ptr;
15498  } /* size != -1 */
15499 
15500  str_bit_length = or_get_varbit_length (buf, &rc);
15501  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
15502  {
15503  return ER_FAILED;
15504  }
15505  /* get the string byte length */
15506  str_length = BITS_TO_BYTES (str_bit_length);
15507 
15508  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= str_length + 1)
15509  {
15510  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
15511  new_ = copy_buf;
15512  }
15513  else
15514  {
15515  /*
15516  * Allocate storage for the string including the kludge NULL
15517  * terminator
15518  */
15519  new_ = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str_length + 1);
15520  }
15521 
15522  if (new_ == NULL)
15523  {
15524  /* need to be able to return errors ! */
15525  if (domain)
15526  {
15527  db_value_domain_init (value, TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain), TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE, 0);
15528  }
15529  or_abort (buf);
15530  return ER_FAILED;
15531  }
15532  else
15533  {
15534  /* do not read the kludge NULL terminator */
15535  rc = or_get_data (buf, new_, str_length);
15536  if (rc == NO_ERROR && align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
15537  {
15538  /* round up to a word boundary */
15539  rc = or_get_align32 (buf);
15540  }
15541 
15542  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
15543  {
15544  if (new_ != copy_buf)
15545  {
15546  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, new_);
15547  }
15548  return ER_FAILED;
15549  }
15550 
15551  new_[str_length] = '\0'; /* append the kludge NULL terminator */
15552  db_make_varbit (value, precision, new_, str_bit_length);
15553  value->need_clear = (new_ != copy_buf) ? true : false;
15554 
15555  if (size == -1)
15556  {
15557  /* Standard packed varbit with a size prefix */
15558  ; /* do nothing */
15559  }
15560  else
15561  { /* size != -1 */
15562  /* Standard packed varbit within an area of fixed size, usually this means we're looking at the
15563  * disk representation of an attribute. Just like the -1 case except we advance past the
15564  * additional padding. */
15565  pad = size - (int) (buf->ptr - start);
15566  if (pad > 0)
15567  {
15568  rc = or_advance (buf, pad);
15569  }
15570  } /* size != -1 */
15571  } /* else */
15572  } /* size != 0 */
15573  }
15574 
15575  }
15576  return rc;
15577 }
15578 
15579 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
15580 mr_index_cmpdisk_varbit (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
15581 {
15582  assert (domain != NULL);
15583 
15584  return mr_data_cmpdisk_varbit (mem1, mem2, domain, do_coercion, total_order, start_colp);
15585 }

15587 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
15588 mr_data_cmpdisk_varbit (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
15589 {
15590  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
15591  int bit_length1, bit_length2;
15592  int mem_length1, mem_length2, bitc;
15593  OR_BUF buf1, buf2;
15594  int error = NO_ERROR;
15595 
15596  assert (domain != NULL);
15597 
15598  or_init (&buf1, (char *) mem1, 0);
15599  bit_length1 = or_get_varbit_length (&buf1, &error);
15600  mem_length1 = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_length1);
15601  assert (error == NO_ERROR);
15602 
15603  or_init (&buf2, (char *) mem2, 0);
15604  bit_length2 = or_get_varbit_length (&buf2, &error);
15605  mem_length2 = BITS_TO_BYTES (bit_length2);
15606  assert (error == NO_ERROR);
15607 
15608  bitc = varbit_compare ((unsigned char *) buf1.ptr, mem_length1, (unsigned char *) buf2.ptr, mem_length2);
15609  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
15610 
15611  return c;
15612 }

15614 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
15615 mr_cmpval_varbit (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp,
15616  int collation)
15617 {
15618  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
15619  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
15620  int bitc;
15621 
15622  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
15623  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
15624 
15625  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
15626  {
15627  return DB_UNK;
15628  }
15629 
15630  bitc = varbit_compare (string1, (int) db_get_string_size (value1), string2, (int) db_get_string_size (value2));
15631  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
15632 
15633  return c;
15634 }
15635 
15636 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
15637 mr_cmpval_varbit2 (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int length, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
15638 {
15639  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT c;
15640  unsigned char *string1, *string2;
15641  int len1, len2, string_size;
15642  int bitc;
15643 
15644  string1 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value1);
15645  string2 = (unsigned char *) db_get_string (value2);
15646 
15647  if (string1 == NULL || string2 == NULL)
15648  {
15649  return DB_UNK;
15650  }
15651 
15652  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value1);
15653  len1 = MIN (string_size, length);
15654  string_size = (int) db_get_string_size (value2);
15655  len2 = MIN (string_size, length);
15656 
15657  bitc = varbit_compare (string1, len1, string2, len2);
15658  c = MR_CMP_RETURN_CODE (bitc);
15659 
15660  return c;
15661 }

15730 static int
15731 mr_setval_enumeration (DB_VALUE * dest, const DB_VALUE * src, bool copy)
15732 {
15733  char *str = NULL;
15734  bool need_clear = false;
15735 
15736  if (src == NULL || DB_IS_NULL (src))
15737  {
15738  return db_value_domain_init (dest, DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
15739  }

15755  else
15756  {
15757  str = db_get_enum_string (src);
15758  }
15759  }
15760

15762  db_make_enumeration (dest, db_get_enum_short (src), str, db_get_enum_string_size (src), db_get_enum_codeset (src),
15763  db_get_enum_collation (src));
15764  dest->need_clear = need_clear;
15765

15767 }

15791 /*
15792  * mr_setval_enumeration_internal () - make an enumeration value based on
15793  * index and domain.
15794  * return: NO_ERROR or error code.
15795  * value(in/out):
15796  * domain(in):
15797  * index(in): index of enumeration string
15798  * size(in):
15799  * copy(in):
15800  * copy_buf(in):
15801  * copy_buf_len(in):
15802  */
15803 static int
15804 mr_setval_enumeration_internal (DB_VALUE * value, TP_DOMAIN * domain, unsigned short index, int size, bool copy,
15805  char *copy_buf, int copy_buf_len)
15806 {
15807  bool need_clear = false;
15808  int str_size;
15809  char *str;
15810  DB_ENUM_ELEMENT *db_elem = NULL;
15811 
15812  if (domain == NULL || DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEMS_COUNT (domain) == 0 || index == 0 || index == DB_ENUM_OVERFLOW_VAL)
15813  {
15814  db_make_enumeration (value, index, NULL, 0, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
15815  value->need_clear = false;
15816  return NO_ERROR;
15817  }
15818 
15819  if (index > DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEMS_COUNT (domain) && DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEMS_COUNT (domain) > 0)
15820  {
15821  assert (false);
15822  return ER_FAILED;
15823  }
15824 
15825  db_elem = &DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEM (domain, index);
15826  str_size = DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING_SIZE (db_elem);
15827  if (!copy)
15828  {
15829  str = DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_elem);
15830  }
15831  else
15832  {
15833  if (copy_buf && copy_buf_len >= str_size + 1)
15834  {
15835  /* read buf image into the copy_buf */
15836  str = copy_buf;
15837  need_clear = false;
15838  }
15839  else
15840  {
15841  str = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, str_size + 1);
15842  if (str == NULL)
15843  {
15844  return ER_FAILED;
15845  }
15846  need_clear = true;
15847  }
15848  memcpy (str, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_elem), str_size);
15849  str[str_size] = 0;
15850  }
15851 
15852  db_make_enumeration (value, index, str, str_size, TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain), TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain));
15853  value->need_clear = need_clear;
15854 
15855  return NO_ERROR;
15856 }

15956 /*
15957  * pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer () - Uncompresses a data stored in buffer.
15958  *
15959  * return() : NO_ERROR or error code.
15960  * buf(in) : The buffer from which is needed decompression.
15961  * data(out) : The result of the decompression. !!! Needs to be alloc'ed !!!
15962  * compressed_size(in) : The compressed data size.
15963  * decompressed_size(in) : The uncompressed data size.
15964  */
15965 int
15966 pr_get_compressed_data_from_buffer (OR_BUF * buf, char *data, int compressed_size, int decompressed_size)
15967 {
15968  int rc = NO_ERROR;
15969 
15970  /* Check if the string needs decompression */
15971  if (compressed_size > 0)
15972  {
15973  lzo_uint decompression_size = 0;
15974  /* Handle decompression */
15975 
15976  /* decompressing the string */
15977  rc = lzo1x_decompress ((lzo_bytep) buf->ptr, (lzo_uint) compressed_size, (lzo_bytep) data, &decompression_size,
15978  NULL);
15979  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
15980  {
15981  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL, 0);
15982  return ER_IO_LZO_DECOMPRESS_FAIL;
15983  }
15984  if (decompression_size != (lzo_uint) decompressed_size)
15985  {
15986  /* Decompression failed. It shouldn't. */
15987  assert (false);
15988  }
15989  data[decompressed_size] = '\0';
15990  }
15991  else
15992  {
15993  /* String is not compressed and buf->ptr is pointing towards an array of chars of length equal to
15994  * decompressed_size */
15995 
15996  rc = or_get_data (buf, data, decompressed_size);
15997  data[decompressed_size] = '\0';
15998  }
15999 
16000  return rc;
16001 }
16002 
16003 /*
16004  * pr_get_compression_length() - Simulate a compression to find its length to be stored on the disk.
16005  *
16006  * return() : The length of the compression, based on the new encoding of varchar.
16007  * If the compression fails, then it returns charlen.
16008  * string(in) : The string to be compressed.
16009  * charlen(in) : The length of the string to be compressed.
16010  */
16011 int
16012 pr_get_compression_length (const char *string, int charlen)
16013 {
16014  lzo_voidp wrkmem;
16015  char *compressed_string = NULL;
16016  lzo_uint compressed_length = 0;
16017  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16018  int length = 0;
16019 
16020  length = charlen;
16021 
16022  if (!pr_Enable_string_compression) /* compression is not set */
16023  {
16024  return length;
16025  }
16026  wrkmem = (lzo_voidp) malloc (LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16027  if (wrkmem == NULL)
16028  {
16029  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16030  goto cleanup;
16031  }
16032 
16033  memset (wrkmem, 0x00, LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16034 
16035  /* Alloc memory for the compressed string */
16036  /* Worst case LZO compression size from their FAQ */
16037  compressed_string = (char *) malloc (LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (length));
16038  if (compressed_string == NULL)
16039  {
16040  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY,
16041  1, (size_t) (LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (length)));
16042  goto cleanup;
16043  }
16044 
16045  /* Compress the string */
16046  rc = lzo1x_1_compress ((lzo_bytep) string, (lzo_uint) length, (lzo_bytep) compressed_string, &compressed_length,
16047  wrkmem);
16048  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
16049  {
16050  /* We should not be having any kind of errors here. Because if this compression fails, there is not warranty
16051  * that the compression from putting data into buffer will fail as well. This needs to be checked but for now
16052  * we leave it as it is.
16053  */
16054  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_COMPRESS_FAIL, 4, FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD,
16055  fileio_get_zip_method_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD), FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL,
16056  fileio_get_zip_level_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL));
16057  goto cleanup;
16058  }
16059 
16060  if (compressed_length < (lzo_uint) (charlen - 8))
16061  {
16062  /* Compression successful */
16063  length = (int) compressed_length;
16064  }
16065  else
16066  {
16067  /* Compression failed */
16068  length = charlen;
16069  }
16070 
16071 cleanup:
16072  /* Free the working memory needed for compression */
16073  if (wrkmem != NULL)
16074  {
16075  free_and_init (wrkmem);
16076  }
16077 
16078  if (compressed_string != NULL)
16079  {
16080  free_and_init (compressed_string);
16081  }
16082 
16083  return length;
16084 }
16085 
16086 /*
16087  * pr_get_size_and_write_string_to_buffer ()
16088  * : Writes a VARCHAR or VARNCHAR to buffer and gets the correct size on the disk.
16089  *
16090  * buf(out) : Buffer to be written to.
16091  * val_p(in) : Memory area to be written to.
16092  * value(in) : DB_VALUE to be written.
16093  * val_size(out) : Disk size of the DB_VALUE.
16094  * align(in) :
16095  *
16096  * Note:
16097  * We use this to avoid double compression when it is required to have the size of the DB_VALUE, previous
16098  * to the write of the DB_VALUE in the buffer.
16099  */
16100 int
16101 pr_get_size_and_write_string_to_buffer (OR_BUF * buf, char *val_p, DB_VALUE * value, int *val_size, int align)
16102 {
16103  char *compressed_string = NULL, *string = NULL, *str = NULL;
16104  int rc = NO_ERROR, str_length = 0, length = 0;
16105  lzo_uint compression_length = 0;
16106  lzo_bytep wrkmem = NULL;
16107  bool compressed = false;
16108  int save_error_abort = 0;
16109 
16110  /* Checks to be sure that we have the correct input */
16111  assert (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR || DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_STRING);
16112  assert (db_get_string_size (value) >= OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
16113 
16114  save_error_abort = buf->error_abort;
16115  buf->error_abort = 0;
16116 
16117  string = db_get_string (value);
16118  str_length = db_get_string_size (value);
16119  *val_size = 0;
16120 
16121  if (!pr_Enable_string_compression) /* compression is not set */
16122  {
16123  length = str_length;
16124  compression_length = 0;
16125  str = string;
16126  goto after_compression;
16127  }
16128 
16129  /* Step 1 : Compress, if possible, the dbvalue */
16130  wrkmem = (unsigned char *) malloc (LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16131  if (wrkmem == NULL)
16132  {
16133  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16134  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
16135  goto cleanup;
16136  }
16137 
16138  memset (wrkmem, 0x00, LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16139 
16140  /* Alloc memory for the compressed string */
16141  /* Worst case LZO compression size from their FAQ */
16142  compressed_string = (char *) malloc (LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (str_length));
16143  if (compressed_string == NULL)
16144  {
16145  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
16146  (size_t) LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (str_length));
16147  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
16148  goto cleanup;
16149  }
16150 
16151  /* Compress the string */
16152  rc = lzo1x_1_compress ((lzo_bytep) string, (lzo_uint) str_length, (lzo_bytep) compressed_string, &compression_length,
16153  wrkmem);
16154  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
16155  {
16156  /* We should not be having any kind of errors here. Because if this compression fails, there is not warranty
16157  * that the compression from putting data into buffer will fail as well. This needs to be checked but for now
16158  * we leave it as it is.
16159  */
16160  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_COMPRESS_FAIL, 4, FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD,
16161  fileio_get_zip_method_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD), FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL,
16162  fileio_get_zip_level_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL));
16163  rc = ER_IO_LZO_COMPRESS_FAIL;
16164  goto cleanup;
16165  }
16166 
16167  if (compression_length < (lzo_uint) (str_length - 8))
16168  {
16169  /* Compression successful */
16170  length = (int) compression_length;
16171  compressed = true;
16172  str = compressed_string;
16173  }
16174  else
16175  {
16176  /* Compression failed */
16177  length = str_length;
16178  compression_length = 0;
16179  str = string;
16180  }
16181 after_compression:
16182  /*
16183  * Step 2 : Compute the disk size of the dbvalue.
16184  * We are sure that the initial string length is greater than 255, which means that the new encoding applies.
16185  */
16186 
16187  switch (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value))
16188  {
16189  case DB_TYPE_VARCHAR:
16190  case DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
16191  *val_size = or_packed_varchar_length (length + PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE) - PRIM_TEMPORARY_DISK_SIZE;
16192  break;
16193 
16194  default:
16195  /* It should not happen */
16196  assert (false);
16197  rc = ER_FAILED;
16198  goto cleanup;
16199  }
16200 
16201  /* Step 3 : Insert the disk representation of the dbvalue in the buffer */
16202 
16203  switch (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value))
16204  {
16205  case DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
16206  case DB_TYPE_STRING:
16207  rc = pr_write_compressed_string_to_buffer (buf, str, (int) compression_length, str_length, align);
16208  break;
16209 
16210  default:
16211  /* It should not happen. */
16212  assert (false);
16213  rc = ER_FAILED;
16214  goto cleanup;
16215  }
16216 
16217 cleanup:
16218 
16219  buf->error_abort = save_error_abort;
16220 
16221  if (compressed_string != NULL)
16222  {
16223  free_and_init (compressed_string);
16224  }
16225 
16226  if (wrkmem != NULL)
16227  {
16228  free_and_init (wrkmem);
16229  }
16230 
16231  if (rc == ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW)
16232  {
16233  return or_overflow (buf);
16234  }
16235 
16236  return rc;
16237 }
16238 
16239 /* pr_write_compressed_string_to_buffer() : Similar function to the previous implementation of
16240  * or_put_varchar_internal.
16241  *
16242  * buf(in/out) : Buffer to be written the string.
16243  * compressed_string(in) : The string to be written.
16244  * compressed_length(in) : Compressed length of the string. If it is 0, then no
16245  * compression happened.
16246  * decompressed_length(in) : Decompressed length of the string.
16247  * align(in) :
16248  */
16249 
16250 static int
16251 pr_write_compressed_string_to_buffer (OR_BUF * buf, char *compressed_string, int compressed_length,
16252  int decompressed_length, int align)
16253 {
16254  int storage_length = 0;
16255  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16256 
16257  assert (decompressed_length >= OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
16258 
16259  /* store the size prefix */
16260  rc = or_put_byte (buf, 0xFF);
16261  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16262  {
16263  return rc;
16264  }
16265 
16266  /* Store the compressed size */
16267  OR_PUT_INT (&storage_length, compressed_length);
16268  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) &storage_length, OR_INT_SIZE);
16269  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16270  {
16271  return rc;
16272  }
16273 
16274  /* Store the decompressed size */
16275  OR_PUT_INT (&storage_length, decompressed_length);
16276  rc = or_put_data (buf, (char *) &storage_length, OR_INT_SIZE);
16277  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16278  {
16279  return rc;
16280  }
16281 
16282  /* Get the string disk size */
16283  if (compressed_length > 0)
16284  {
16285  storage_length = compressed_length;
16286  }
16287  else
16288  {
16289  storage_length = decompressed_length;
16290  }
16291 
16292  /* store the string bytes */
16293  rc = or_put_data (buf, compressed_string, storage_length);
16294  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16295  {
16296  return rc;
16297  }
16298 
16299  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
16300  {
16301  /* kludge, temporary NULL terminator */
16302  rc = or_put_byte (buf, 0);
16303  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16304  {
16305  return rc;
16306  }
16307 
16308  /* round up to a word boundary */
16309  rc = or_put_align32 (buf);
16310  }
16311 
16312  return rc;
16313 }
16314 
16315 /*
16316  * pr_write_uncompressed_string_to_buffer() :- Writes a string with a size less than
16317  * OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION to buffer.
16318  *
16319  * return :- NO_ERROR or error code.
16320  * buf(in/out) :- Buffer to be written to.
16321  * string(in) :- String to be written.
16322  * size(in) :- Size of the string.
16323  * align() :-
16324  */
16325 
16326 static int
16327 pr_write_uncompressed_string_to_buffer (OR_BUF * buf, char *string, int size, int align)
16328 {
16329  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16330 
16331  assert (size < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION);
16332 
16333  /* Store the size prefix */
16334  rc = or_put_byte (buf, size);
16335  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16336  {
16337  return rc;
16338  }
16339 
16340  /* store the string bytes */
16341  rc = or_put_data (buf, string, size);
16342  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16343  {
16344  return rc;
16345  }
16346 
16347  if (align == INT_ALIGNMENT)
16348  {
16349  /* kludge, temporary NULL terminator */
16350  rc = or_put_byte (buf, 0);
16351  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16352  {
16353  return rc;
16354  }
16355 
16356  /* round up to a word boundary */
16357  rc = or_put_align32 (buf);
16358  }
16359 
16360  return rc;
16361 }
16362 
16363 /*
16364  * pr_data_compress_string() :- Does compression for a string.
16365  *
16366  * return :- NO_ERROR or error code.
16367  * string(in) :- String to be compressed.
16368  * str_length(in) :- The size of the string.
16369  * compressed_string(out) :- The compressed string. Needs to be alloced!!!!!
16370  * compressed_length(out) :- The size of the compressed string. If it's -1 after this, it means
16371  * :- compression failed, so the compressed_string can be free'd.
16372  *
16373  */
16374 int
16375 pr_data_compress_string (char *string, int str_length, char *compressed_string, int *compressed_length)
16376 {
16377  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16378  lzo_voidp wrkmem = NULL;
16379  lzo_uint compressed_length_local = 0;
16380 
16381  *compressed_length = 0;
16382 
16383  if (str_length < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
16384  {
16385  return rc;
16386  }
16387 
16388  if (!pr_Enable_string_compression) /* compression is not set */
16389  {
16390  *compressed_length = -1;
16391  return rc;
16392  }
16393 
16394  wrkmem = (lzo_voidp) malloc (LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16395  if (wrkmem == NULL)
16396  {
16397  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16398  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
16399  goto cleanup;
16400  }
16401  memset (wrkmem, 0x00, LZO1X_1_MEM_COMPRESS);
16402 
16403  /* Compress the string */
16404  rc = lzo1x_1_compress ((lzo_bytep) string, (lzo_uint) str_length, (lzo_bytep) compressed_string,
16405  &compressed_length_local, wrkmem);
16406  if (rc != LZO_E_OK)
16407  {
16408  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_IO_LZO_COMPRESS_FAIL, 4, FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD,
16409  fileio_get_zip_method_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_METHOD), FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL,
16410  fileio_get_zip_level_string (FILEIO_ZIP_LZO1X_DEFAULT_LEVEL));
16411  rc = ER_IO_LZO_COMPRESS_FAIL;
16412  goto cleanup;
16413  }
16414 
16415  if (compressed_length_local >= (lzo_uint) (str_length - 8))
16416  {
16417  /* Compression successful but its length exceeds the original length of the string. */
16418  /* We will also be freeing the compressed_string since we will not need it anymore. */
16419  *compressed_length = -1;
16420  }
16421  else
16422  {
16423  /* Compression successful */
16424  *compressed_length = (int) compressed_length_local;
16425 
16426  /* Clean the wrkmem */
16427  if (wrkmem != NULL)
16428  {
16429  free_and_init (wrkmem);
16430  }
16431  return rc;
16432  }
16433 
16434 cleanup:
16435  if (wrkmem != NULL)
16436  {
16437  free_and_init (wrkmem);
16438  }
16439 
16440  return rc;
16441 }
16442 
16443 /*
16444  * pr_clear_compressed_string() :- Clears the compressed string that might have been stored in a DB_VALUE.
16445  * This needs to succeed only for VARCHAR and VARNCHAR types.
16446  *
16447  * return () :- NO_ERROR or error code.
16448  * value(in/out) :- The DB_VALUE that needs the clearing.
16449  */
16450 
16451 int
16452 pr_clear_compressed_string (DB_VALUE * value)
16453 {
16454  char *data = NULL;
16455  DB_TYPE db_type;
16456 
16457  if (value == NULL || DB_IS_NULL (value))
16458  {
16459  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
16460  }
16461 
16462  db_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
16463 
16464  /* Make sure we clear only for VARCHAR and VARNCHAR types. */
16465  if (db_type != DB_TYPE_VARCHAR && db_type != DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR)
16466  {
16467  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
16468  }
16469 
16470  if (value->data.ch.info.compressed_need_clear == false)
16471  {
16472  return NO_ERROR;
16473  }
16474 
16475  if (value->data.ch.medium.compressed_size <= 0)
16476  {
16477  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
16478  }
16479 
16480  data = value->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf;
16481  if (data != NULL)
16482  {
16483  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, data);
16484  }
16485 
16486  db_set_compressed_string (value, NULL, 0, false);
16487 
16488  return NO_ERROR;
16489 }
16490 
16491 /*
16492  * pr_do_db_value_string_compression() :- Test a DB_VALUE for VARCHAR and VARNCHAR types and do string compression
16493  * :- for such types.
16494  *
16495  * return() :- NO_ERROR or error code.
16496  * value(in/out) :- The DB_VALUE to be tested.
16497  */
16498 
16499 int
16500 pr_do_db_value_string_compression (DB_VALUE * value)
16501 {
16502  DB_TYPE db_type;
16503  char *compressed_string, *string;
16504  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16505  int src_size = 0, compressed_size;
16506 
16507  if (value == NULL || DB_IS_NULL (value))
16508  {
16509  return rc; /* do nothing */
16510  }
16511 
16512  db_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (value);
16513 
16514  /* Make sure we clear only for VARCHAR and VARNCHAR types. */
16515  if (db_type != DB_TYPE_VARCHAR && db_type != DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR)
16516  {
16517  return rc; /* do nothing */
16518  }
16519 
16520  /* Make sure the value has not been through a compression before */
16521  if (value->data.ch.medium.compressed_size != 0)
16522  {
16523  return rc;
16524  }
16525 
16526  string = db_get_string (value);
16527  src_size = db_get_string_size (value);
16528 
16529  if (!pr_Enable_string_compression || src_size < OR_MINIMUM_STRING_LENGTH_FOR_COMPRESSION)
16530  {
16531  /* Either compression was disabled or the source size is less than the compression threshold. */
16532  value->data.ch.medium.compressed_buf = NULL;
16533  value->data.ch.medium.compressed_size = -1;
16534  return rc;
16535  }
16536 
16537  /* Alloc memory for compression */
16538  compressed_string = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (src_size));
16539  if (compressed_string == NULL)
16540  {
16541  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY,
16542  1, (size_t) (LZO_COMPRESSED_STRING_SIZE (src_size)));
16543  rc = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
16544  return rc;
16545  }
16546 
16547  rc = pr_data_compress_string (string, src_size, compressed_string, &compressed_size);
16548  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16549  {
16550  ASSERT_ERROR ();
16551  goto error;
16552  }
16553 
16554  if (compressed_size > 0)
16555  {
16556  /* Compression successful */
16557  db_set_compressed_string (value, compressed_string, compressed_size, true);
16558  return rc;
16559  }
16560  else
16561  {
16562  /* Compression failed */
16563  db_set_compressed_string (value, NULL, -1, false);
16564  goto error;
16565  }
16566 
16567 error:
16568  if (compressed_string != NULL)
16569  {
16570  db_private_free_and_init (NULL, compressed_string);
16571  }
16572 
16573  return rc;
16574 }

16656 static int

16658 {

16665

16669  db_value_domain_init (value, DB_TYPE_JSON, domain->precision, 0);

16675  {

16677  new_doc = json->document;

16683  {
16684  return error;
16685  }
16686  error = db_get_deep_copy_of_json (json, &json_copy);
16687  if (error != NO_ERROR)
16688  {
16689  return error;
16690  }
16691  json_schema = json_copy.schema_raw;
16692  new_doc = json_copy.document;
16693  }
16694 
16695  db_make_json (value, new_doc, copy);
16696  db_get_json_schema (value) = json_schema;
16697 
16698  return error;

16747 static void
16748 mr_data_readmem_json (OR_BUF * buf, void *memptr, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int size)
16749 {
16750  DB_JSON *json;
16751  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16752 
16753  json = (DB_JSON *) memptr;
16754  if (json == NULL)
16755  {
16756  if (size != 0)
16757  {
16758  if (or_advance (buf, size) != NO_ERROR)
16759  {
16760  assert (false);
16761  }
16762  }
16763  return;
16764  }
16765 
16766  if (size < 0)
16767  {
16768  assert (false);
16769  return;
16770  }
16771 
16772  if (size == 0)
16773  {
16774  mr_initmem_json (memptr, domain);
16775  return;
16776  }
16777 
16778  rc = db_json_deserialize (buf, json->document);
16779  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16780  {
16781  ASSERT_ERROR ();
16782  db_json_delete_doc (json->document);
16783  }
16784 }

16800  if (cur->document != NULL)
16801  {

16870 mr_data_writeval_json (OR_BUF * buf, DB_VALUE * value)
16871 {

16873

16875  {
16876  assert (false);
16877  return ER_FAILED;
16878  }
16879 
16880  if (buf->error_abort)
16881  {
16882  int estimated_length = mr_data_lengthval_json (value, true);
16883 
16884  if ((ptrdiff_t) estimated_length > ((ptrdiff_t) (buf->endptr - buf->ptr)))
16885  {
16886  /* this will make string_data_writeval jump because
16887  * of buffer overflow, leaking memory in the process,
16888  * we need to take care of it here
16889  */
16890  (void) or_overflow (buf);
16891  }
16892  }
16893 
16894  rc = db_json_serialize (*value->data.json.document, *buf);
16895  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16896  {
16897  ASSERT_ERROR ();
16898  }
16899 
16900  return rc;
16901 }

16931 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
16932 mr_data_cmpdisk_json (void *mem1, void *mem2, TP_DOMAIN * domain, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp)
16933 {
16934  char *first, *second;
16935  OR_BUF first_buf, second_buf;
16936  DB_VALUE json1, json2;
16937  JSON_DOC *doc1 = NULL, *doc2 = NULL;
16938  int rc = NO_ERROR;
16939 
16940  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT res = DB_UNK;
16941 
16942  first = (char *) mem1;
16943  second = (char *) mem2;
16944 
16945  or_init (&first_buf, first, 0);
16946  or_init (&second_buf, second, 0);
16947 
16948  rc = db_json_deserialize (&first_buf, doc1);
16949  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16950  {
16951  ASSERT_ERROR ();
16952  return res;
16953  }
16954 
16955  rc = db_json_deserialize (&second_buf, doc2);
16956  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
16957  {
16958  ASSERT_ERROR ();
16959  return res;
16960  }
16961 
16962  db_make_json (&json1, doc1, true);
16963  db_make_json (&json2, doc2, true);
16964 
16965  res = mr_cmpval_json (&json1, &json2, do_coercion, total_order, 0, 0);
16966  pr_clear_value (&json1);
16967  pr_clear_value (&json2);
16968 
16969  return res;
16970 }
16971 
16972 /* when total_order is true,
16973  * we force to string uncomparable types.
16974  * this is because "order by" uses total_order=true
16975  * and we don't want to fail. The standard says that
16976  * only scalar and nulls are comparable.
16977  *
16978  * we only return DB_UNK when either one is null and
16979  * total_order is false
16980  */
16981 static DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT
16982 mr_cmpval_json (DB_VALUE * value1, DB_VALUE * value2, int do_coercion, int total_order, int *start_colp, int collation)
16983 {
16984  JSON_DOC *doc1 = NULL, *doc2 = NULL;
16985  DB_JSON_TYPE type1 = DB_JSON_UNKNOWN;
16986  DB_JSON_TYPE type2 = DB_JSON_UNKNOWN;
16987  DB_VALUE scalar_value1, scalar_value2;
16988  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT cmp_result;
16989  bool is_value1_null = true, is_value2_null = true;
16990  int error_code;
16991 
16992  doc1 = db_get_json_document (value1);
16993  doc2 = db_get_json_document (value2);
16994 
16995  is_value1_null = DB_IS_NULL (value1) || ((type1 = db_json_get_type (doc1)) == DB_JSON_NULL);
16996  is_value2_null = DB_IS_NULL (value2) || ((type2 = db_json_get_type (doc2)) == DB_JSON_NULL);
16997 
16998  if (is_value1_null || is_value2_null)
16999  {
17000  if (!total_order)
17001  {
17002  return DB_UNK;
17003  }
17004 
17005  if (is_value1_null && is_value2_null)
17006  {
17007  return DB_EQ;
17008  }
17009 
17010  return is_value1_null ? DB_LT : DB_GT;
17011  }
17012 
17013  /* db_json_get_type shouldn't return DB_JSON_UNKNOWN, this represents a bug */
17014  assert (type1 != DB_JSON_UNKNOWN && type2 != DB_JSON_UNKNOWN);
17015 
17016  db_make_null (&scalar_value1);
17017  db_make_null (&scalar_value2);
17018 
17019  if (db_json_doc_is_uncomparable (doc1) || db_json_doc_is_uncomparable (doc2))
17020  {
17021  /* force string comp */
17022  char *str1 = NULL, *str2 = NULL;
17023 
17024  str1 = db_json_get_json_body_from_document (*doc1);
17025  str2 = db_json_get_json_body_from_document (*doc2);
17026 
17027  db_make_string (&scalar_value1, str1);
17028  db_make_string (&scalar_value2, str2);
17029 
17030  scalar_value1.need_clear = true;
17031  scalar_value2.need_clear = true;
17032  }
17033  else
17034  {
17035  /* This is not according to standard, in SQL/JSON standard
17036  * different types should not be compared, but rather throw
17037  * an error. We chose to also compare different scalar types
17038  * even when total_order is false.
17039  */
17040  error_code = db_convert_json_into_scalar (value1, &scalar_value1);
17041  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
17042  {
17043  /* this shouldn't happen */
17044  assert (false);
17045  pr_clear_value (&scalar_value1);
17046  return DB_UNK;
17047  }
17048 
17049  error_code = db_convert_json_into_scalar (value2, &scalar_value2);
17050  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
17051  {
17052  /* this shouldn't happen */
17053  assert (false);
17054  pr_clear_value (&scalar_value1);
17055  pr_clear_value (&scalar_value2);
17056  return DB_UNK;
17057  }
17058  }
17059 
17060  cmp_result = tp_value_compare_with_error (&scalar_value1, &scalar_value2, do_coercion, total_order, NULL);
17061 
17062  pr_clear_value (&scalar_value1);
17063  pr_clear_value (&scalar_value2);
17064  return cmp_result;
17065 }
